title: peanut butter c. c. bars
directions: Cream together brown sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Beat in egg, vanilla and salt.
Add flour gradually.
Add chocolate chips.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook the spaghetti until tender.
Rinse the spaghetti in cold water.
Cut the vegetables into bite size pieces.
Add the vegetables to the spaghetti.
Add the salad seasoning and Italian dressing.
Add a little at a time; taste to see if you need more. Refrigerate and serve once it is chilled.

title: cheddar beer soup
directions: Cook vegetables and drain. Melt margarine; stir in flour, salt and mustard. Cook over low heat until smooth. Remove from heat. Add milk and Worcestershire. Heat mixture until it coats the spoon. Add cheese. Cook over medium heat until cheese melts. Stir in beer and vegetables; bring to a simmer. Cook about 15 minutes. Serve with preferred garnishes (croutons, paprika, whatever).

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix together.
Let come to boil.
Pour over dumplings.
Bake at 425° until brown and apples are done.

title: asparagus-chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water until half done.
Prepare mixture:
Combine cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise and cheese; stir until well blended.

title: chicken cutlets with sautéed mushrooms
directions: Heat 1 Tbsp. oil in large non-stick skillet.
Sprinkle chicken on both sides with salt and pepper.
Add to hot oil and cook over high heat 2 minutes each side.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Add remaining 2 Tbsp. oil to skillet.
Add mushrooms and red pepper and cook, stirring over medium heat, 8 minutes or until mushrooms are lightly browned.
Stir in garlic.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and cook 1 minute more.
Return browned chicken breasts and any juices to skillet.
Place one slice of cheese on top of each. Cover and cook over medium-low heat until cheese melts, about 3 minutes.
Spoon mushroom mixture over chicken and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Combine almonds and 3 tablespoons sugar in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until almonds are coated and sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Cool and store in an airtight container, if desired.
Combine sugar, parsley, oil, vinegar and Tabasco sauce in bowl.
Mix well.
Chill several hours.
Combine lettuce, celery, onions and mandarin oranges in bowl.
Add chilled dressing.
Toss.
Sprinkle with almonds.

title: sportsman's sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana fritters
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, baking powder, soda and salt in large bowl.
Gradually blend in water, beating with a whisk until smooth.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and jello; let stand overnight or at least 4 hours.
Add pineapple, mandarin oranges and Cool Whip.
Mix well and let set a few hours before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and form into ball.
Chill in fridge and serve with crackers.

title: salisbury steak skillet supper
directions: In medium bowl with fork, combine bread crumbs, egg, catsup and salt until well blended.
Mix in ground beef.
Shape into a large patty about 1 inch thick; or several small ones.
In large skillet, over medium-low heat, heat oil; brown beef patty on each side.
Meanwhile, in small bowl, mix soup and wine.
Drain excess fat from skillet.
Add soup mixture, potatoes and frozen green beans around beef patty in skillet.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes longer, stirring vegetables once during cooking.
Makes 4 servings; 415 calories per serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut up chicken in casserole dish. Mix all other ingredients. Pour on chicken.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft.
Add all of the other ingredients; simmer for 10 minutes.
Use with chicken, pork or beef.

title: jessie's bread
directions: Mix desired amount of garlic salt, chili peppers and margarine.
Spread on French bread that has been cut in half lengthwise.
Mix cheese with mayonnaise and spread on bread. Broil until lightly brown and bubbly.

title: quick and easy individual size pizzas
directions: Flatten biscuits on a baking sheet.
Cover with spaghetti sauce and cheese.
Add optional items.
Bake according to biscuit directions.
One package makes 10 individual size pizzas.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: caponata (italian relish)
directions: Cut unpeeled eggplant into 1/2-inch cubes.
Pour oil into 12 to 14-inch frying pan.
Add eggplant; cover and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until eggplant softens slightly (about 5 minutes).
Uncover and continue to cook, stirring, until eggplant is browned (10 to 15 or more minutes).
Add bell peppers, onion and garlic.
Stir until onion is soft.
Add garden marinara sauce; continue to cook, uncovered, until a thick sauce forms (about 10 more minutes).
Add olives; season to taste with salt and pepper.
Let cool to room temperature, then pack into four 1-pint canning jars or freezer containers, leaving 1 inch headspace.
Cover tightly; store in refrigerator for up to 1 week or in freezer for up to 6 months.
This may be served on crackers cold or at room temperature.
Makes about 4 pints.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
In a large bag combine sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Drop biscuits into bag. Shake until each piece is coated.
Stack biscuit pieces in tube pan.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in butter.
Reserve 1 c. of cheese for top.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour in casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.

title: granola muffins
directions: Combine bran and boiling water; let stand.
Mix margarine, sugar and salt.
Add to bran mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk, flour, soda and granola.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375° to 400°.
Batter will keep in refrigerator for 4 weeks.
Yields 24 muffins.

title: sauce for spareribs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate pork spareribs overnight or for 2 days, if desired.
Drain ribs.
Place on broiler pan.
Add hot water to pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Good hot or cold.

title: pasta bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook pasta while doing the following: In a large pan brown meat with garlic; drain fat.
Add all remaining items except cheeses.
Cover and simmer at least 15 minutes.
Add cooked pasta and simmer about 5 minutes.
Pour into buttered 10 x 13-inch pan and top with cheeses.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti soup
directions: Brown meat.
Add vegetables, bouillon cubes and tomatoes. Cook about 20 minutes.
Add spaghetti sauce and spices.
Cook until done.
More water may be added, if necessary.
Other vegetables may be added or substituted, if you wish.
Combine with spaghetti.

title: district two (no tomato) vegetable soup
directions: *Add any other vegetable, but no tomatoes and no red cabbage.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Put water, oil and chocolate in top of double boiler.
Melt chocolate mixture and set aside.
Sift flour with salt and soda. Beat eggs and add sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture alternately with chocolate mixture.
Mix only until flour is blended.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, using 9-inch greased pans.

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: Mix coconut, milk, chocolate and vanilla in a large bowl. Drop by teaspoonfuls, 1 inch apart, onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Press down ends of coconut with back of spoon.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Remove soup from can and place in a 1-quart casserole dish. Heat 7 to 9 minutes; stir occasionally.
Add the cream cheese that has been cut into squares.
Heat for 3 minutes.
After 1 minute, stir.
At the end of 3 minutes, stir until the dip is smooth and creamy.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer.
Divide into 2 bread pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: vegetarian split pea soup
directions: Place split peas in a large pan and add enough cold water to cover.
Let soak 15 minutes and drain.
Return peas to same pan and add water and bring to boil.
Reduce heat, simmer 45 minutes. Heat oil in large skillet, add onion, saute until golden brown, add garlic and saute 3 minutes.
Add onion, garlic, carrots, celery and peas.
Mix in cumin; season with salt and pepper. Simmer until peas and vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes. Serve.

title: milk chocolate cream pie
directions: Place chocolate in a small bowl.
In small saucepan, bring 1/2 cup of the cream to a simmer.
Pour over the chocolate.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes, then stir until smooth.

title: clara's egg noodles
directions: Combine and knead into ball.
Divide and roll out into circles into desired thickness.
Lay circles out to dry.
Cut into desired lengths.
Bag and store in freezer.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese and Ranch salad dressing. Mix until smooth. Add bell pepper, onions and olives. Stir good. Spread 1 tablespoon mixture on flour tortillas. Roll up tight. Refrigerate until ready to serve, then cut up into wheels and serve.

title: pecan pilaf(mock wild rice)
directions: Melt butter and saute onions five minutes.
Add rice, stirring until rice is coated with butter.
Add chicken broth and seasoning.
Cover, cook 18 to 20 minutes.
Stir in parsley and pecans.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into parts and rinse and pat dry.
Combine garlic, sour cream, lemon juice and seasonings.
Coat chicken in sour cream mixture and chill, covered, for several hours or overnight. Butter a large shallow baking dish.
Roll chicken pieces in crumbs and arrange in single layer in baking dish.
Drizzle with melted butter and bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until chicken is tender and golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: caramel-apple coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8-inch square baking pan.
In a large bowl, combine the flour, granulated sugar, baking powder and salt.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in 1 stick butter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
With fork, stir in milk and egg, mixing lightly until mixture just clings together and forms a soft dough.

title: egg custard
directions: Cream together.
Place	in
an 8 or 9-inch pie pan with uncooked crust.
Grate nutmeg on top of mixture.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° for 30 minutes.

title: flan or caramel custard
directions: Prepare Caramel first using 1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup sugar mixed in a small saucepan.
Cook on medium, rinsing the sides of the pan down with a squirt bottle of water when sugar condensed on sides of pan.
Keep cooking water and sugar mixture until it turns an amber color (will take a good 10 minutes or so) and immediately pour into the bottom of custard cups or large round casserole dish.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream the margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk; stir well.
Mix all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in zucchini and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: shellfish tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain liquor from mushrooms and add milk to make 1/2 cup.
Combine with white sauce and sherry.

title: stuffed soft crab
directions: Dry soft crabs with paper towels.
Remove all cartilage from crabmeat.
Place soft crabs in shallow baking pan.
Remove top shell from crabs and stuff each crab cavity with about 3 tablespoons crabmeat.
Replace top shell.
Melt butter and pour evenly over crabs.
Bake at 400° until shells turn red and crabs brown slightly, about 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings, 2 crabs each.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix together; store in airtight container.
Add hot water.

title: laredo roast
directions: Coat meat with the mixture.
Put in foil and secure, leaving the ends unsealed.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 6 hours. Remove from refrigerator; seal ends.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour per pound.
This makes its own gravy.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil your potato slices until tender, then drain.
Put in mixing bowl and beat.
Add other ingredients, adding milk last and slowly beat.
Place in unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until brown.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Combine pears and sugar; let stand 1 hour.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves.
Add pears to sifted mixture, stirring just until blended.
Add eggs, oil and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; finish cooling on wire rack.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling point.
Add Jell-O (two different flavors) while heating.
Add cream cheese while mixture is still very hot.
Blend until smooth.
Remove from heat and add 2 cups ice water.
Refrigerate until mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in Cool Whip; add nuts and pour into Jell-O mold.
Color schemes can be matched by varying Jell-O flavors.

title: myra's lettuce dressing
directions: Add water to vinegar and sugar to make a full cup.
Stir well and set aside.
Mix bacon grease, flour and salt well.
Pour with vinegar mix and stir like gravy.
Pour over lettuce and onions. GOOD AS SNUFF!

title: quick brunswick stew
directions: Defrost corn in package on High for 3 minutes; set aside. Preheat 9-inch browning dish on High for 6 minutes.
Add oil; cook chicken on High for 1 to 2 minutes per side or until brown.
Place in 1 layer in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch microproof dish, skin side down, with thicker portions at the outer edge of dish.
Mix all other ingredients including corn, in a small bowl.
Pour mixture over the chicken.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook on High for 8 minutes. Turn chicken and spoon sauce on top.
Cook, covered, on High for 8 minutes.
Allow to stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: coconut granola bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine brown sugar, peanut butter, corn syrup, butter and vanilla.
Combine the remaining ingredients; add to peanut butter mixture and stir to coat.
Press into two greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire racks.
Cut into bars.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Put
crackers in heavy paper bag.
Dump in the rest and shake well.
Remove to a dish to serve.

title: tallerine
directions: Cook onion, bell pepper and garlic in slightly greased skillet. Add ground beef, salt and pepper.
Drain grease.
Put tomato paste, 1/2 cup water, whole tomatoes, Ro-Tel, taco mix and corn in skillet and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Put cooked noodles in deep casserole dish and add all ingredients.
Top with cheese alternately and place in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni main dish(a fast meal)
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Add stewed broccoli and browned Polish sausage or cubed ham.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix and chill.
Roll in small balls and then in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Flatten with bottom of a glass.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375° to 400°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Shred 2 packages dried beef.
Mix with other ingredients. Shape into a ball.
Shred third package of dried beef.
Roll cheese ball in shredded beef.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread.	Put 1/2 cornmeal mixture in skillet.
Put a layer of filling then the remaining cornbread mixture.
Bake 425° for 25 minutes.

title: herbed pasta and vegetables
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
Saute garlic and vegetables in oil about 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice, basil and pepper.
Toss with pasta; heat gently and sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage barbecue
directions: Fry sausage out of casing with onion, mashing sausage as it cooks.
When almost done, add cut up peppers, mushrooms and sauce.
Simmer until peppers are cooked a little.
Salt may be needed but no other seasonings.

title: fish cakes
directions: Grind chicken, celery and onion.
Combine all ingredients. Use an ice cream dipper to form patties.
Roll in bread crumbs. Fry in deep fat at 350°, then bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with Tartex sauce.

title: toffee crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.

title: fluffle
directions: In electric mixer bowl, beat eggs for 2 minutes.
Add milk, flour, sugar and salt.
Scrape sides and mix again.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion and salt.
Let stand for 2 hours. Drain.
Mix vinegar and sugar, but do not heat.
Pour over cucumbers and toss.
Put into containers and freeze.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Chop vegetables to desired size pieces.
If desired, other vegetables may be added.
Add as much salad seasoning as you desire.
Pour on the salad dressing and refrigerate until cool.
Mix well before serving.

title: cactus cooler
directions: Steep together ruby mist, traditional and peppermint tea bags in 1/2 gallon boiling water for 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add 3 quarts cold water and apple and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Serve over ice.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound meat into serving pieces.
Dredge in flour, seasoned salt and pepper mixture.
Brown on both sides.
Pour tomatoes over meat.
Combine onions, tomato sauce, green pepper and garlic. Pour over steak.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add carrots and cook 1 hour.
Serve with hot rice if desired.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well.
Serve 2 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: tacos skillet style
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add beans, catsup, salt and pepper. Heat thoroughly.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Serve on toasted rolls.
Yields 12 servings.

title: spicy oat bran pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a medium bowl, beat oil, sugar and pumpkin combined.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and allspice into another bowl.
Stir in oat bran and oats.
Stir dry ingredients and raisins into pumpkin mixture until combined.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan; cut into bars.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine thawed potatoes, margarine, onions, sour cream, soup and cheese.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish and top with crushed potato chips.
Place in oven and bake for 1 hour or until brown on top. Yield:
10 servings.

title: exquisite pie
directions: Mix
together
melted
butter, sugar, eggs, vinegar and vanilla.
Beat well and add coconut, raisins and pecans.
Pour into unbaked
pie crust.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350° (until puffed across top).

title: andrea's pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and whip with metal whip or a fork until batter is smooth.
Drop by spoonful into hot oiled skillet. Bake until bubbles come to the top, then flip and bake on other side.

title: chicken divan
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine in a small saucepan. Stir in flour and cook for 1 minute.
Stir in chicken bouillon until thickened.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Place asparagus spears in a shallow baking dish or four individual casserole dishes.
Put chicken over asparagus and top with sauce.
Sprinkle with parsley and bread crumbs.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
(From The Living Heart Diet.)

title: crumb cake
directions: Rub together the shortening, brown sugar and flour. Take out 1 cup of this mixture. Now, add the raisins, nutmeg, cloves, egg, sour milk and soda. Put in flat tin and sprinkle cup of crumbs over top. Bake in moderate oven 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: hungry man's dip
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage and onion.
In a crock-pot, melt cheese and add Ro-Tel tomatoes and meat mixtures.
Serve in crock-pot.
This makes a nice amount.

title: aunt alma's cranberry salad
directions: Wash and salt cranberries.
Combine berries, water and sugar in saucepan.
Cook until berries pop open.
Dissolve unflavored gelatin in small amount of water.
Remove berries from heat source; add gelatin.
Mix.
Stir in marshmallows; add fruit if desired.
Cool.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: fesmire chicken
directions: Cover chicken with all ingredients and put over rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade eggnog
directions: Separate eggs.
Put yolks in very large pot and refrigerate whites.
Add sugar to yolks and blend thoroughly.
Slowly, add 1/2 bourbon to yolks and sugar (too fast will scramble the eggs!). Next, add the rest of the alcohol (you don't need to do this slowly).
Add the milk.
Beat the whipping cream until it peaks, then fold into mixture.
Finally, whip the egg whites and fold into the mixture.
This delicious brew will keep for several weeks!

title: lettuce salad
directions: Layer vegetables in a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: whole fruit shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Whirl until blended. Pour into tall glass.
Makes one serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter pan.
Cover
bottom
of pan with 1 1/2 c. Minute rice. Add
can
of French-style green beans, drained.	Add cut up, cooked
chicken or turkey.	Add cream of chicken soup that has been
mixed
with 3/4 soup can of milk and 1/4 cup of water. Season with seasoned salt. Top with French fried onion rings that have been crushed, and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fettucine alfredo with chicken
directions: In a skillet, saute garlic and chicken, cut into strips, in the olive oil.
Set aside.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Set aside to cool, then crumble.
Cook the noodles in boiling water according to package directions.
Rinse them under cold water and drain.
In a skillet, melt butter; add flour and cook for a few minutes. Pour milk into mixture in thin stream and stir briskly with wire whisk.
Add cheese and parsley and fold in chicken and bacon. Season with ground pepper.
Cook for a few minutes.
Add fettucine and serve with salad and fresh bread.
Serves 4.

title: mexican pork chops and beans
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix flour, salsa, lime juice, chili and garlic powders together.
Pour into shallow casserole.
Place chops on top of salsa; spoon beans and peppers around the chops. Cover tightly.
Bake about 40 minutes until chops are tender. Spoon sauce over chops to serve.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In casserole dish, put 1 layer of asparagus, 1 layer of sliced eggs, 1 layer of soup, 1 layer of cheese, 1 layer of peas, 1 layer of asparagus, 1 layer of sliced eggs, 1 layer of soup, 1 layer of cheese and 1 layer of peas.
Melt 1 stick butter and crumble crackers into butter.
Let crackers absorb butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Cook until cheese melts, about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oven roasted pork and veggies
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Generously spray roasting pan with Pam cooking spray.
Place tenderloins in pan.
Insert meat thermometer in thickest part of tenderloins.
Place potatoes, carrots and onion around meat.
Sprinkle with rosemary, sage and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes, until meat thermometer registers 165° and veggies are tender.
Stir veggies occasionally.

title: basic molded gelatin salads
directions: Prepare gelatin (choose a flavor to make an interesting combination with the foods you are going to add) according to the directions on the package, adding the lemon juice or vinegar for sharpness.
Use 1 3/4 cups liquid instead of the 2 cups called for in the directions.
Chill.
When partially set (about the consistency of cold egg whites), add the food to make the salad. Pour into 6 or 8 individual molds and chill.

title: peach pie
directions: Make batter of dry ingredients and milk. Mix well. Pour into greased pan. Pour 29 ounce can sliced peaches over batter. Bake at 350° until brown. Top with your favorite topping.

title: microwave pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Combine flavorings in medium bowl.
Place ice cream in large bowl.
Divide into fourths.
Microwave at 50% (Medium) 45 to 60 seconds, or until slightly softened.
Do not let ice cream melt! Mix flavorings at lowest speed of electric mixer until well distributed.
Spoon filling into pie shell.
Top with chopped walnuts or pecans.
Freeze for 2 hours or overnight.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients in a large Dutch oven, and bring mixture to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat.
Cook 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth, reserving broth.
Set chicken aside to cool slightly.
Pour broth through wire mesh strainer into a large bowl.
Discard cooked vegetables. Remove and discard fat from broth.
Return broth to Dutch oven. Cook noodles according to package directions, omitting salt and fat. Drain and set aside.
Add chopped onion, sliced celery and sliced carrots to chicken broth.
Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in chopped chicken and noodles.
Add 1/2 tsp. salt and remaining ingredients.
Cook until thoroughly heated. Yield:
10 cups. Freezes well.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl with wooden spoon.
Put mixture in a round pie dish or in muffin pans.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: cream wafers
directions: Mix butter, cream and flour thoroughly. Chill 1 hour. Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board. Cut into 1 1/2-inch rounds. Transfer to waxed paper heavily sprinkled with sugar. Coat both sides.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Prick with fork in 4 places.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes at 375° until slightly puffed. Using filling, put 2 together.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook the carrots until crisp-tender; drain.
Combine all remaining ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Add carrots, stir until well mixed.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 to 4 hours.
Serve cold as salad or warm it and use as a side dish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli longer than package directions for more tender broccoli, about 18 to 20 minutes; drain.
Mix mayonnaise, cream of mushroom soup and cheese with broccoli and spread in a casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top, melt butter and spread on top of crackers.
Bake at 350° until crackers are browned.

title: sausage and potato casserole
directions: In a large casserole dish, layer everything and pour the sauce over it!
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: fresh berry pie
directions: Combine first three ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Stir in water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until clear. Set aside to cool.
Stir berries into cooled mixture.
Pour into pastry shell.
Chill 3 or 4 hours or until firm.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Add onion and bell pepper mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake until melted.

title: world's greatest cookies
directions: In a blender or food processor, combine oats, cornflakes, coconut, and pecans.
Reduce to a fine mixture and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine flour, soda, and salt.
Mix until well blended and set aside.

title: enchiladas supreme(serves 6)
directions: Simmer chicken in saltwater until tender. Remove the broth and cool to room temperature. Remove meat from carcass and cut into coarse pieces. Combine chicken meat, 2 cans chopped chilies, ripe olives, pimientos, cumin, garlic salt, 1/2 can chicken soup and enchilada sauce. Refrigerate.

title: ham balls
directions: Combine ham,
pork,
beef, egg, cracker crumbs and milk in order given.
Form into balls.
Arrange in baking pan.
Mix soup, vinegar, brown
sugar
and mustard.
Pour sauce over ham balls and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
These freeze well.

title: marinated cabbage slaw
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
Mix and bring to a boil; boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over cabbage while still hot; mix well. Chill at least 24 hours before eating.
This will keep for months.

title: chicken-zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini until tender; drain.
Combine all ingredients except stuffing mix and melted margarine.
Combine stuffing mix and margarine.
Spread half of the stuffing mix in bottom of a large baking dish. Add zucchini mixture.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ranch cheese ball
directions: Stir Ranch mix and softened cream cheese together. Mix well. Shape into a ball. Roll in chopped pecans and chill until ready to serve.

title: apple dip i
directions: Cream the cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth. Add peanuts, then add sour cream and mix until thin enough to dip.

title: wilted salad
directions: Toss lettuce, radishes and onions in a large bowl; set aside. In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel. Add vinegar, lemon juice, sugar and pepper to hot drippings. Stir well and cook slightly until bubbly.
Pour hot dressing over salad and toss gently.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle on top.

title: sour cream cucumbers
directions: Arrange cucumbers in serving dish.
Layer as needed.
Mix all other ingredients thoroughly and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand for 2 or 3 hours (refrigerated) before serving.

title: crown pork roast
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Position rack in lower half of oven. Season with salt and pepper. Brush meat with 4 tablespoons olive oil. Place meat in heavy-duty roasting pan with rack (large enough not to crowd sides). Roast 15 minutes. Reduce heat after 45 minutes until meat is well browned and meat thermometer registers 170° to 180° (about 1 1/2 to 2 hours). Spread season mixture over meat (inside and out).

title: apple cream pie
directions: Line 10-inch pie shell; fill with sliced apples.
Pour cream mixture over top of apples.
Top with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Delicious warm with ice cream.

title: carrot nugget salad
directions: Mix soup, vinegar, oil and sugar together.
Boil until well blended.

title: mexican dish
directions: Cook meat and onion; remove from heat and drain.
Add next 4 ingredients; mix well.
Cook until mixture is hot throughout. Crumble enough Doritos to cover bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Add half of meat mixture; top with grated cheese to cover lightly.
Repeat layers (Doritos, meat, cheese).
Bake at 400° until cheese melts (approximately 20 minutes).
Our family likes this served with pinto beans, green salad and cornbread.

title: harvard beets (lo-cal)
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add beets.
Cook until heated.

title: curried fruit
directions: Melt together margarine, sugar and curry powder.
Stir constantly.
When hot and blended, pour over drained fruit. Cover; bake at 325° for one hour.
Excellent with chicken pot pie and as general side dish.

title: good-n-easy chocolate cake
directions: Sift
dry ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Make three wells.
Put
vanilla in one, vinegar in second and shortening in third. Pour cold
water
over
all
and
beat thoroughly 2 minutes.
(Using a mixer, makes a
finer
textured cake.) Makes a large cake, 9 x 13 or 2 (9-inch) pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry-apple pie
directions: Partially bake crust (5 minutes).
Set aside.
Clean and cook cranberries in water until popped.
Drain.
Put apples in shell. Top with cranberries.
Sprinkle sugar over fruit.
Dot with butter. Crisscross strips of dough over top.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes; 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour in top of double boiler.
Add milk and stir slowly into flour mixture. Cook over boiling water until thick (15 to 20 minutes), stir to prevent lumping.
Pat 1/2 thickened mixture into beaten egg yolks, then combine in double boiler and cook 1 to 2 more minutes.
Blend in vanilla.
Cool, fold in bananas or place in bottom of crust.
Pour into cooled pie crust.
Top with whipped cream.

title: microwave taco salad
directions: Brown meat and onions on High for 4 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes. Stir, then drain.
Add beans, water and taco seasoning.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 to 13 minutes on Medium until thick and bubbly, stirring once.
Combine lettuce, tomatoes and pepper in a salad bowl.
Spoon meat mixture over vegetables in bowl.
Top with cheeses and chips.
Serve immediately with sauce.
Top with sour cream.

title: angel pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cornstarch, in double boiler.
At boiling point, add cornstarch dissolved in a little cold water. Cool until glossy; set aside to cool.
After cooled, fold in 3 stiffly beaten egg whites, slightly sweetened.
Spoon into baked crust.
Cover with sweetened whipped cream.
Add drop of vanilla to the whipped cream.
Keep cool in refrigerator.
Makes 2 (8-inch) pies.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Layer pork chops in an ovenproof container.
On each chop, sprinkle brown sugar, squeeze and leave a slice of lemon, and shake some ketchup over that.
Treat subsequent layers the same. Cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.
Take cover off and bake for approximately 15 more minutes.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix rice, fruit cocktail (drained), sugar and apple together and then fold in Cool Whip.
You can use any fruit like bananas if you are going to use it up right away.
Otherwise the bananas will turn dark and get mushy.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together until light and fluffy. Add flour and baking powder with orange juice and vanilla.
Fold in apples with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from pan 1 hour after baking.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cut tips off wings; cut again at the joint.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over chicken wings.
Marinate overnight.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add chiles and simmer 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce; simmer 15 minutes.
Quickly dip tortillas in hot fat so they stay quite soft; drain.
Put a spoonful of meat mixture on each tortilla.
Roll up and place side by side in dripper pan. Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour over rolled tortillas. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine
cream	cheese,
sour
cream and taco seasoning mix. Put in
pie dish.
Put taco sauce on top of cream cheese mixture. Next,
layer
grated
Monterey
Jack
cheese,
fine shredded lettuce,
chopped
and
pitted black olives, chopped tomatoes, chopped
green peppers and chopped scallions (green onions), the tops and bottoms.
Serve with corn chips.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed. When cooled, crumble cake in large bowl. Pour in pineapple, cherry pie filling and Cool Whip. Mix all together. Sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate.

title: savory italian bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, onion, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and nuts.
In another bowl, whisk together the olive oil, buttermilk, eggs and pesto, if desired. Stir in the zucchini and add liquid mixture to the dry ingredients.
Stir just to moisten thoroughly.
Spoon the batter into greased pans.
Bake at 350° until tester comes out clean. Cool in the pans for 10 minutes, then remove to a rack to cool completely.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Chop cranberries.
Place cranberries in bowl with sugar; let set in refrigerator overnight.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients when ready to serve.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In a large saucepan, heat the butter and saute the onions for 5 minutes. Add beef or lamb.
Sprinkle with flour.
Blend in beef broth and tomatoes. Stir over medium heat until bubbly and thickened. Simmer 5 minutes.
Mix in carrots, peas and herbs. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour into 3-quart casserole. Combine potatoes and eggs. Spread evenly over stew. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top is brown.

title: caramel pie
directions: Boil can of condensed milk in water for 3 hours. This causes milk to turn to caramel. Pour caramel into pie shell. Add 3/4 cup chopped roasted pecans over caramel. Add Cool Whip and garnish with 1/4 cup pecans.

title: crock-pot ranch beans
directions: Put onions and hamburger into crock-pot and add the following: pork and beans, barbecue sauce, mustard, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook on low for about 8 hours.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a tube pan for 2 1/2 hours at 300°. Remove from oven; leave in pan. Mix 1/2 cup fresh orange juice and 1 cup confectioners sugar and pour over cake while it is hot. Cool on rack and wrap in foil. Put in the refrigerator for a day.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: "shake-n-bake" mixture for chicken or pork chops
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use to coat pieces of meat.
Drizzle melted butter over all pieces and bake uncovered at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: marian's veggie pie(lite recipe)
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in water.
Mix all together.
Put in one pie shell.
Cover with second shell.
Bake at 450° for the first 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Sprinkle pecans on bottom of a long cake pan; then sprinkle coconut.
Mix cake according to directions on box and pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, butter and vanilla. Drop by spoonfuls over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli flowerets, onion, cheese and bacon together. Just before serving, whip together and add Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.

title: bread pudding
directions: Tear bread into pieces.
Mix together all ingredients and bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: floating fruit parfaits
directions: Divide fruit among 6 parfait glasses. Stir water into gelatin until dissolved. Stir in cold water and ice cubes until ice melts. Pour 3/4 cup gelatin over strawberries in glasses. Refrigerate 20 minutes, until set but not firm. Stir 1 cup whipped topping into remaining gelatin with whisk until smooth. Spoon over gelatin in glasses. Refrigerate 1 hour. Garnish with remaining whipped topping. Makes 6 servings.

title: banana split pie
directions: Make pie crust from graham cracker crumbs and one stick of oleo.
Beat eggs, sugar and other stick of oleo together for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain pineapple; slice bananas.
Add mixture of eggs, sugar and oleo to pie crust.
Top with a layer of sliced bananas and a layer of pineapple.
Top the pie with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed nuts.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine ingredients and heat to boiling, but do not boil.
Add dash of rum or brandy.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add well-beaten egg and vanilla.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Turn into a well-buttered and floured bread pan.
Bake slowly in moderate oven for 1 hour.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onions and drain.
Combine Ranch dressing and taco seasoning and add this and all other ingredients to meat mixture.
Let cook until heated thoroughly.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon salsa out with a spoon with holes in it so as not to get too much juice, so dip doesn't get runny.

title: simple punch
directions: Combine water, pineapple juice, sugar and citric acid in large container.
Chill 24 hours.
Ladle into punch cups.
May freeze mixture and serve as slushy punch.
Thaw for several hours before serving.
Yields 30 servings.

title: ripe tomato chow chow
directions: Bring to a boil; simmer for 15 minutes.
Pack and seal in hot jars.

title: chocolate sheet cake and icing
directions: In mixing bowl, mix sugar, flour, soda and salt. Boil butter, water and cocoa.
Pour over dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased sheet pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: bratwurst and kraut
directions: Spread one can of sauerkraut in bottom of crock-pot.
Lay bratwurst on top of kraut.
Top with second can of kraut.
Pour beer over all.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Serve.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Melt 1 tablespoon shortening in large black iron skillet.
Bake about 20 minutes, until brown on top.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix starch with enough cold water to make a smooth paste.
Add boiling water and cook until glossy.
Stir in soap flakes while mixture is warm.
When cool, add powdered paint or food coloring. Mixture can be kept for a week if placed in a jar with a tight lid.

title: indian wedding cake
directions: Stir well with fork (do not blend). Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix Oreo cookies, sugar and butter in mixing bowl.
Place mixture in 13x9x2 inch pan.
Spread half of the ice cream over Oreo mixture.
Spread hot fudge over ice cream.
Repeat with ice cream.
Spread Cool Whip over ice cream.
Garnish with chopped nuts and cherries.
Freeze overnight before serving.

title: squash dish
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add onion to hamburger; salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in Worcestershire sauce and soup; stir into hamburger.
Layer hamburger, squash and cheese in casserole dish. Bake in 300° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix ingredients, leaving the Doritos to be added right before you eat.
Does not keep well.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly with a fork.
Pack into loaf pan 8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inches.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand in pan for 5 minutes, turn out on heat proof platter.
Top with cheese and return to oven (warm, but with heat off for a few minutes) to soften cheese.
Yields about 8 servings.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers solidly into clean jars.
Combine next 4 ingredients with 6 cups water in saucepan.
Heat to boiling point. Pour over cucumbers, leaving 3/4-inch headspace.
Add dill and garlic.
Place lids on jars loosely.
Put in 200° oven until cucumbers change color.
Remove from oven.
Seal jars tightly.

title: swedish creamed corn
directions: Beat all together except corn and butter, then add corn. Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan with butter.
Add mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat in saucepan, stirring continuously, until all ingredients are melted.
Serve over cake and ice cream.

title: angel jello dessert
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O in boiling water; add sugar and stir to dissolve.
Add frozen lemonade, let stand until thick.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed on box.
Mix into Jell-O and pour over cake. Coconut may be added, if desired.
Refrigerate until set.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Mix all ingredients in casserole.
Cover with brown sugar and bake in a casserole at 350° for one hour.

title: corn fritters
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.

Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Combine milk and eggs; gradually add to flour mixture, and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Add cheese, sugar, salt, pepper, and corn; stir until cheese melts. Pour corn mixture into a greased 8 inch square pan and freeze until firm.
Heat 1 inch of oil to 375°.
Cut frozen corn mixture into 4 inch strips; dip each strip in beaten eggs and roll in cracker crumbs.
Fry frozen strips in hot oil until golden brown on all sides; drain on paper towels.

title: midlo monte sandwich
directions: Make French toast.
Add warmed turkey and cheese to toast. Serve.

title: oatmeal carrot cookies
directions: Preheat oven to
Lightly spray a 7 1/2 x 11 1/2 x 2 inch baking pan with vegetable oil.
Cover raisins in a small bowl with boiling water.
Soak 15 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl,
cream together margarine and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add egg.
Beat well.
Add carrots, cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon rind.
Mix well.
Add raisins and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour in pan and bake until done.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine salad dressing mix with dill weed and oil.
Pour over crackers.
Stir to coat or mix in large Ziploc bag.
Place in oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir gently halfway through baking.

title: banana beauty cake
directions: Grease and flour one 9-inch square or two 8-inch round pans.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to boil.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter.
Add cereal.
Drop by spoonfuls on metal tray or waxed paper.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut up eggplant in small cubes; cook in salt water until tender.
Brown beef and onion in shortening.
Mix with eggplant; season with salt and pepper.
Add milk, soup, beaten egg and 1/2 cup crumbs.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased baking dish; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: toll house pie
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add flour and sugar, blending well. Add nuts, butter and chocolate chips.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serve warm.

title: old-fashioned chocolate loaf cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Need a bread loaf pan with an 8-cup capacity.
Line or spray pan and set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and set aside.
Melt chocolate in double boiler until smooth and set aside to cool slightly.
In large bowl, cream butter.
Add vanilla and 1 cup sugar (reserve 1/4 cup sugar).
Beat thoroughly.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add chocolate and beat until blended.
Add sifted dry ingredients and beat.
Beat egg whites on moderately high speed until whites hold a soft shape.
Fold whites into thick chocolate mixture.
Turn mixture into prepared pan.
Bake in preheated oven.
Cool.
Wrap cake in plastic wrap and let stand at room temperature overnight before serving.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in salt water; drain well.
Combine soup and cheese; add cabbage.
Sprinkle with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: maruya
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Set aside.
Mix eggs, Carnation evaporated milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Dip Saba in batter and deep-fat fry.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Roll in sugar.

title: eldorado casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Brown beef and onion; add garlic, olives and tomato sauce. Combine sour cream, cottage cheese and chilies in a bowl.
Crush 1/2 bag of chips.
Layer in bottom of casserole dish, 1/2 meat, 1/2 cheese mixture and 1/2 grated cheese.
Top with crushed chips. Makes 2.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Heat through only.

title: butterscotch balls
directions: Melt butterscotch bits over hot water, not boiling.
Add Karo, sugar, orange juice, lemon juice, chopped nuts and uncooked rolled oats.
Cool in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Roll into small balls and then into granulated sugar.
Keep in closed container.

title: antipasto salad bowl
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Whip Dream Whip until stiff.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Put pie filling on top.
Chill. Makes 2 pies.

title: slow cooker pot roast
directions: In slow cooker, mix cream of mushroom soup, dry onion soup mix and water. Place roast in slow cooker and coat with soup mixture. Cook on high for 3 to 4 hours or low for 8 to 9 hours.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, mayo, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Add celery, pickle relish, grapes and pecans.
Just a touch of lemon juice is good.
Mix well.

title: night before casserole
directions: Mix all
ingredients together and refrigerate overnight or at least 6 to	12 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into muffin pans or bread pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Beat together egg yolk, lemon juice, lemon rind and butter until thick and lemon colored. Combine sugar, flour and salt. Add to the egg mixture alternately with milk, beat after each addition.

title: spuddle casserole
directions: Peel, cut up and boil potatoes until tender.
Drain potatoes and whip with sour cream and milk until they are the consistency of creamy mashed potatoes.
Saute green onions (tops, too) in the butter until they are translucent.
Add onions, Bac*Os, 3/4 cup of the Cheddar cheese, salt, pepper and garlic salt to the potato mixture and mix well.
Pour into a buttered 3 qt casserole dish. Sprinkle top with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350°
for approximately 30 min. or until bubbly.
Serves 8 - 10.

title: autumn pork chop squash dinner
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray. Cut squash in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and pulp.
Cut into 1-inch thick slices. Arrange squash slices in prepared pan. Sprinkle evenly with the dried fruit.
In a small bowl, combine apple cider and allspice.
Mix well.
Pour over fruit and squash.
Place pork chops over mixture in pan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake for 1 hour or until pork chops and squash are tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook butter, sugar, milk and cocoa.
Boil for 3 minutes; remove
from stove.
Add salt, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir well.
Drop onto wax paper until set.

title: hummus with ginger
directions: Combine 1/2 of chickpeas in Cuisinart.
Add all other ingredients except parsley.
When pureed, add rest of chickpeas and mix until pureed.
Stir in parsley, leaving a few tablespoons to sprinkle on top before serving.
Serve with pita bread.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Put bread, cheese and sausage in 3-quart casserole.
Pour soup and 1 1/4 cups milk over this.
Beat eggs, 2 1/2 cups milk, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin pecan dessert
directions: Line a 13x9x2 baking pan with wax paper and coat paper with non-stick spray, set aside.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and flour and stir well.
Add eggs and beat with electric mixer 2 1/2 minutes.
Add milk and vanilla. Stir in pecans and coconut (optional).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes in 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Makes 1 large or 2 small.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger with onions.
Drain green beans, using 1/4 cup
of
bean
juice
and heat.
Drain grease off meat and place in
x 9-inch casserole dish.
Add mushroom soup with green beans and pour over meat mixture.
Layer with cheese and cover mixture completely with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° until Tater Tots are brown, approximately 20 minutes.

title: quick and easy cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and then the nuts and chocolate chips. Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until firm.
Remove from cookie sheet; dust with powdered sugar while still warm.
Yield:
40 to 50 cookies.

title: diane's texas hot meat dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and onion.
Add salt.
Melt Velveeta cheese into hamburger mix.
Add chilies and tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips!

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Lay on rice that has been mixed with water and mushroom soup.
Cover with aluminum foil. Cook at 300° to 325° about 1 hour or until chicken is done and rice is tender.
Uncover to brown the last few minutes.

title: little pizzas
directions: In a microwave dish, layer of cream cheese, 1 can chili with beans, salsa (mild or hot; amount desired) and sprinkle a package of shredded Cheese cheese.
Microwave approximately 5 minutes. Bake restaurant-style tortilla chips, if desired.
Shred lettuce. Add all ingredients to lettuce.
Eat with chips.

title: bean salad
directions: Heat sugar, oil and vinegar just until sugar is dissolved. Drain green, wax and garbanzo beans, then rinse and drain kidney beans.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Blend milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in electric blender on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand about 5 minutes; then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
(Great way to have pie without having to make a pastry.)

title: sausage log
directions: Brown sausage; drain and chop fine.
Mix sausage with cheese and eggs in a large bowl.
Mix hot roll mix according to directions on box.
Roll the dough out and fill with sausage mixture, then roll up and bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes. This recipe is enough to make 2 logs.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: goulash mix
directions: Brown meat thoroughly in your favorite oil or grease.
Add onions.
Continue to stir until onions are glazed or turn yellow. Add spices (next 4 ingredients) to taste.
Continue stirring and add only 1 cup of water and cooking wine.
Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours and thicken gravy before serving with cornstarch and remaining 1 cup of water.

title: sweet summer peas
directions: Shell peas if using fresh ones (there should be about 3 cups). In 3-quart saucepan over high heat, heat 3/4 cup water to boiling; add peas and heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 3 to 5 minutes, until peas are tender.
Drain peas. Rinse under running cold water to cool.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: In large bowl, combine vanilla frosting, peanut butter and margarine with fork until well mixed.
Form into 1-inch balls. Chill 1 hour.
In small saucepan, melt remaining frosting over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Dip chilled balls in melted frosting; allow excess to drip off.
Place on cooling rack over waxed paper.
Let stand at room temperature until dry, about 6 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, drain and crumble.
Wash and chop broccoli into chunks.
Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine butter, raisins, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and walnuts, mixing to form a rugged paste.
Fill each cored apple with 1/4 of the paste.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Crush crackers and mix with melted butter.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 2/3 of this mixture.
Beat egg yolks until light. Add 3/4 cup of the sugar and pineapple, including juice.
Bring to a boil (2 or 3 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O.
Stir well.
Cool.
Beat egg whites stiff with 3/4 cup sugar.
Add vanilla.
Fold into cooled egg yolk mixture.
Pour into pan. Cover with remaining crumbs.
Chill 24 hours or overnight.

title: one dish dinner
directions: Wash and peel potatoes, boil until done and mash.
Add salt, pepper, butter and milk to taste.
Drain green beans.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Spread hamburger in bottom of a baking dish. Add beans on top of hamburger.
Add mashed potatoes on top of beans.
Cover potatoes with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: abigail's soft molasses cakes
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Beat butter, sugar, molasses and egg until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with cold water.
Beat until blended.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart on greased baking sheet.

title: helen's favorite cake dessert
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
When cool, slice crosswise through middle of cake.
(Dental floss works well for slicing.)
Mix drained pineapple with whipped topping.
Spread over bottom half.
Replace upper half of cake, frosting with remaining pineapple and whipped topping.
Can decorate with maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: almond tarts mandelformar(35 tarts)
directions: Work butter and sugar until creamy and fluffy.
Add egg yolk, almonds and flour and mix thoroughly.
Chill. Butter small fluted tins and, with floured thumbs, coat inside with dough.

title: peaches 'n' cream dessert
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Roll into rectangle 14 x 10-inch.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased pan; press up sides.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Blend butter and
sugar;
beat	in eggs.
Add pineapple and juice.
Stir in
bread.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 hour in oval casserole dish.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with fork until smooth.
Stir in nuts and spread evenly in pan.
Mix brown sugar and cocoa together and then sprinkle over cake mixture.
Pour hot tap water over batter. Bake 40 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes, then serve with ice cream.

title: pressure cooked brunswick stew
directions: About 1 hour before serving, combine all ingredients.
Cover pressure cooker and bring to 15 pounds pressure as manufacturer directs.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: meringue
directions: Beat with an electric mixer until stiff peaks form.
Put on pie and make sure meringue is sealed to pie crust.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Melt margarine, add sugar, and beat eggs in one at time.
Add flour mix well.
Add vanilla and chocolate.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Bake in large bowl.
Can also be cooked in the microwave for approximately 8 to 10 minutes, according to microwave temperature.

title: pia colada
directions: Place coconut milk, pineapple juice, rum and ice in blender container. Blend until frothy. Pour into 4 tall glasses. Garnish each drink with pineapple wedge and maraschino cherry. Makes 4 drinks.

title: scottish oat scones
directions: Combine flour, oats, sugar, baking powder, cream of tartar and salt.
Combine butter, milk and egg and add to the dry ingredients.
Mix just until moistened.
Stir in raisins.
Shape the dough into a ball and pat it out into an 8-inch circle.
Cut into 8 wedges.
Place the wedges on a greased baking sheet and bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.

title: grapefruit ice
directions: Boil water and sugar together.
Cool.
Add lemon juice and grapefruit.
Pour into a freezing container.
Freeze.
Shred before serving.

title: pumpkin cream roll-ups
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy, add pumpkin.
Mix flour and spices together, fold into pumpkin mixture.
Grease a 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet and cover with wax paper.
Grease and flour wax paper.
Spread batter evenly on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Place cake on a dampened dish towel.
Roll up and place on a cake rack until cooled.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: In a double boiler, cook all ingredients except butter until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Chill.
This will keep for several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream the butter and cream cheese.
Gradually beat in the sifted sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in the vanilla. Frost between layers, top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle top with chopped walnuts or pecans (optional).

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in large shallow roasting pan.
In heavy 1 1/2 to 2-quart saucepan, stir in sugar, margarine and corn syrup. Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat.
Without stirring, boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over popcorn, stirring to coat well.
Bake in a 250° oven, stirring every 15 minutes, 1 hour.
Remove from oven. Spoon popcorn onto large pieces of foil.
Break apart as popcorn cools.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: berries with cream
directions: Stir together and set overnight in refrigerator.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Brown meat slightly in pan.
Mix meat and all ingredients together in crock-pot.
Put enough water to cover everything. Cook for 8 hours on slow.

title: company peas
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add all ingredients except peas. Cook, uncovered, stirring frequently, until celery is tender, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Add peas and heat thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Sift together cake flour, soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Add dry mixture alternately with applesauce and bananas to oil and sugar and egg mixture.
Stir in nuts, dates and raisins.
Batter will be stiff. Pour into greased cake or loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: italian sausage soup with tortellini
directions: Brown sausage in a 5-quart Dutch oven.
Remove sausage and drain.
Reserve 1 tablespoon liquid or drippings.

title: kids giant soap bubbles
directions: You will need a coat hanger bent into a large loop.
Leave the hanger part to use as the handle.
Mix 1/2 cup detergent with 5 cups water and stir.
Add 2 tablespoons of glycerine.

title: black olive cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, butter and other ingredients. Mix well and shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts, cheese or pieces of dried beef depending on taste.

title: sunsational muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Add carrots, apple, raisins, coconut and nuts.
Stir together moist ingredients and add to mixture, stirring only until mixture is moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and press into 8-inch square pan.
Bake for about 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour on crust and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: tabasco pickles
directions: Drain pickles and cut into rounds approximately 1/4 to 1/3-inches.
Discard stems.
Place sugar and Tabasco in large container that will hold all the pickles.
Can use a plastic wash basin.
Mix as best as possible.
Add sliced pickles and stir to melt sugar.
When all is melted, return to gallon jar and replace lid.
Place in refrigerator and shake at least twice a day for 3 days.
Ready to eat on the 4th day.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Place cucumbers and onions in a large container and sprinkle with salt.
Mix and let set 2 hours.
Drain.
Mix the sugar and vinegar well.
Pour over cucumbers.
Toss until well coated. Pack into desired containers and freeze.
Will keep in refrigerator for 3 weeks.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Layer ingredients in 9 x 13 pan in order given.
Cut 1 stick margarine in small pieces and spread over cake.
Bake at 350 degrees until light brown about 35-45 minutes.

title: donna's chicken divan
directions: Saute onions and chili in butter.
Combine all liquids and add onion and chile.
Tear tortillas into pieces, place in casserole in layers of chicken and cheese, ending with cheese.
Pour liquid over all and refrigate overnight, or several hours.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: don't move it rice
directions: Brown rice, garlic and onion in oil in skillet.
Pour in 1 cup tomato juice and 1 cup chicken broth.
Let cook slowly.
(After adding liquid, don't stir anymore.)
Let cook dry and add a little broth.
Let cook dry again.
Keep adding a little broth until rice is done.
Move gently with fork to see if it is done.
Rice is dry when served.
Add cut up chicken or turkey and toss through rice.

title: oysters and bacon
directions: Shuck oysters and lay on baking pan in bottom shell.
Place a small piece of bacon on top of the oyster and sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce.
Broil until bacon is done.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix well and form into a ball.
Roll into finely chopped nuts.
Top with pimento olives.

title: peanut butter-honey balls
directions: Mix together peanut butter and honey in bowl.
Stir well; slowly add milk powder and mix well.
Add cereal.
Shape into balls.
Ready to eat.
No cooking.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cheese and wiener crescents
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Slit wieners to within 1/2 inch of ends. Insert 3 strips of cheese in each split.
Separate dough; wrap dough over wiener, keeping cheese up.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, cheese side up.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.

title: miracle whip cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage into a large bowl.
In a small bowl, place sugar and add enough vinegar to moisten, then add Miracle Whip to taste. Pour over cabbage and mix.
Let stand for 2 to 3 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts and mix.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove loaf from pan and cool.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil; add butter and peanut butter. Stir until melted. Add cereal and mix well. Drop on waxed paper.

title: cold cucumber chive soup
directions: Grate cucumber; add other ingredients and chill.
Garnish with chives.

title: cushaw pie
directions: Combine
first
3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pie
crust.
Bake at 350° to 400° for about 20 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: 9 layer dip
directions: On a flat platter, combine sour cream and Ranch pack together, mix well.
Put on the platter. Top with onion and all three cheeses.
Add the vegetables one at a time.
Looks like a pizza dip.
Great for showers or a snack.

title: peanut candy
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave. Add peanut butter and mix well. Add remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper or foil. Makes 100 pieces.

title: delicious mound bars
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar; pat into crust in a 9 x 12-inch rectangular pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 minutes.

title: great raspberry pie
directions: Boil the water, cornstarch and sugar until thickened.
Add jello and cool.
Add berries.
Enough for 1 pie.
Put into baked pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: scallops with linguine and vegetables
directions: Boil 2 quarts water.
Add linguine; return to boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Add carrot to linguine and cook 6 to 7 minutes more uncovered until pasta is tender.
Drain and keep warm.
In large skillet, melt butter and add garlic, onion and mushrooms.
Cook on medium-high heat 3 minutes.
Add scallops, parsley and lemon pepper. in a small bowl, stir wine, cornstarch and instant chicken broth.
Add to skillet with the scallops, parsley and lemon pepper. Cook until scallops are opaque and the sauce is thin and bubbly. Serve over warm pasta.
Serves 2 people.

title: ham mousse
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over milk in a saucepan.
Add egg yolks and salt; stir until blended.
Place over low heat, stir constantly, until gelatin dissolves and mixture thickens slightly, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; blend in sugar, mustard and vinegar. Chill until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon. Fold in green pepper, celery, onion and ham.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Turn into a 4-cup mold and chill until firm. Unmold.

title: veal marsala
directions: Veal should be cut scalloppine (thin).
Dredge veal in flour mixed with salt and pepper.
Pan fry garlic in oil and discard garlic.
Saute meat until brown, 2 or 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms, butter and wine and saute for 2 minutes longer.

title: breakfast egg pizza
directions: Separate crescent dough into 16 triangles.
Place on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
In a bowl, heat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over crust.
Sprinkle cheese over all.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine
cornmeal,
baking
powder
and salt in a bowl. Add egg
and milk; beat until smooth; stir in onion.
Heat fat or oil in
skillet
(have it at least 3 inches deep) to 375°. Drop batter
by
spoonfuls into fat.
Fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towel.
Makes about 20.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and bell pepper in oil until vegetables are limp.
Add crawfish, soup and water; mix well.
Add green onion tops and parsley; place in a casserole dish, topping with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: overnight salad
directions: In a bowl spread mayo over lettuce.
Add cauliflower, peas, water chestnuts and onion.
Spread in layers bacon, white sugar and Parmesan cheese.
Seal and refrigerate overnight.
You can use broccoli instead of peas.
You can also use green onions instead of red onions.

title: meal in one
directions: Combine potatoes, carrots, peas, onion, salt and pepper. Arrange vegetables and frankfurters in layers in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle each layer with flour.
Add milk.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: italian biscotti
directions: Mix together all ingredients to form dough batter.

Make a strip of wax paper for length of cookie sheet to put batter on it. Form loaf shape onto wax paper (use flour on hands if sticky). Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until golden brown, then remove biscotti while hot.
Place on cutting board while hot and slice. Put cookie back on cookie sheet and bake in oven, flat, for about 10 minutes.

title: mock lobster
directions: Add salt, vinegar and seafood seasoning to water and bring to a boil.
Add frozen fish and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: marinated italian garlic chicken(prep time: 5 minutes plus refrigerating; cooking time: 24
directions: Mix dressings and seasonings.
Pour dressing mixture over chicken.
Cover; refrigerate 20 minutes.
Drain.
Place chicken on grill over medium-hot coals (coals will have slight glow) or greased rack of broiler pan.
Grill or broil for 10 to 12 minutes on each side or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 48 graham crackers on cookie sheet with edges.
Bring to boil the oleo, butter and sugar.
Boil 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Pour over crackers.
Bake 8 to 11 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: Mix all.
Cover and refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Take out chunks. Roll on floured board 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out shapes.
Bake until brown around edges.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: christmas fudge pie
directions: Combine wafer crumbs with melted margarine.
Firmly press into bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cream 1/2 cup softened margarine.
Gradually add brown sugar, beating at medium speed of electric mixture until blended. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in melted chocolate and next 4 ingredients.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely on a wire rack.
Before serving, put a blop of whipped cream.
Drizzle a little chocolate syrup over it and set a cherry on top.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Arrange the 4 chicken breast halves in baking dish.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, basting every 15 or 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pierogi
directions: Put all ingredients in a food processor and blend until they make a ball of dough.
Sprinkle flour on a board and knead for a couple minutes.
Cut small portion of dough to roll out. Remainder of dough is put in plastic and stored in refrigerator until needed.
Roll thin on board.
Cut into circles and place a teaspoon of filling to one side.
Fold over and pinch edges together.
Boil carefully in salted water until it floats to the top.
Serve with melted butter and/or sour cream.
May also be fried in butter.

title: texas roll-ups
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Spread on the flour tortillas and roll up.
Cool in the refrigerator.
Before serving, cut into 1-inch pieces.

title: spicy sautéed fish
directions: Heat olive oil in heavy large skillet over medium-high heat. Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper. Add half of fish to skillet and saut until just opaque in center, about 3 minute per side. Transfer fish to platter. Repeat with remaining fish. Add parsley and crushed red pepper to same skillet; saut 1 minute. Add tomatoes, olive and garlic; saut until tomatoes are soft and juicy, about 2 minutes. Season sauce with salt and pepper; spoon over fish.

title: potato soup for a crock-pot
directions: Put all ingredients except milk in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours.
(High for 3 to 4 hours.)
Stir in milk during last hour.
Mash potatoes before serving.

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Drain marinade; reserve.
Chop artichokes and set aside. Saute onion and garlic in small amount of marinade. Beat eggs with fork and add crumbs and seasonings.
Stir in parsley, artichokes and onion-garlic mixture. Turn into buttered 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch Pyrex bake pan (2-quart).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until set when lightly touched.
Let cool in pan, then cut in 1-inch squares.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Melt chips and butter.
Add sugar and milk; blend well. Stirring constantly, bring to boil and cook 8 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Serve warm.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in greased casserole pan in this order: asparagus, eggs, bacon and soup.
Top with pimento.
Bake at 325° until warm.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: four-bean salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine all of the beans, green pepper and onions.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; stir until the sugar dissolves.
Pour over bean mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serves approximately 20.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In large kettle, heat oil.
Brown chopped beef; add onions, carrots, celery, tomatoes, water and bouillon.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 2 hours until beef is tender.
Add 1/3 cup barley; simmer another 50 minutes.

title: fuzzy navel cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a glass container.
Cover and let stand 24 hours at room temperature.
Combine all the rest of the ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: party tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Blend soup, water and cheese.
Cook over low heat stirring often until melted.
Add remaining ingredients and heat through.
(Ham may be substituted for meat.)

title: caesar salad with anchovies
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, lemon juice, dry mustard, egg, garlic and Worcestershire sauce well.
Put lettuce and bacon in a salad bowl. Add dressing and toss.
Top with cheese and croutons.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Melt margarine. Add seasoning salt and Worcestershire sauce; mix well with pecans. Bake at 250° for 1 hour and stir often.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain all vegetables well.
Heat sugar, vinegar, oil, water, salt and pepper.
Heat to dissolve sugar.
Let cool and pour over vegetables.
Let marinate overnight before serving.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Roll into 1-inch balls and refrigerate until chilled.
In top of double boiler, melt chocolate chips.
(The paraffin wax gives a smoother look to the chocolate covering.)
Place a layer of waxed paper onto a cookie sheet.
Using a toothpick, dip the chilled balls into the warm chocolate and place on the waxed paper.
Keep balls chilled before serving.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and margarine until well mixed with hands in a large bowl.
Roll into balls; place on a cookie sheet. Freeze for 20 minutes.
Melt chips and paraffin in a double boiler. Dip balls in chocolate mixture; drain on waxed paper.
Put in the refrigerator for 5 minutes, then dump the candy into a container and keep refrigerated.

title: scallops in wine cheese sauce
directions: Put scallops in saucepan with wine, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Drain, reserving 1 cup of broth.
Melt butter and blend in flour.
Add reserved broth and yogurt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in cheese and scallops.
Put in 6 shells or shallow baking dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and bake in a hot 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Low in calories.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry hamburger meat until done.
Add chili seasoning and ketchup.
Put chips in bottom of bowl.
Put hamburger meat on top of chips.
Top with onion, cheese, tomato and lettuce.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet, salt and pepper to taste.
Drain.
While hamburger is cooking, prepare noodles per directions.
Heat tomato and pizza sauces, water, mushrooms and oregano (simmer) until noodles and meat are done.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish with a small amount of sauce, then layer noodles, sauce and meat mixture and cheese 3 times.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: In a bowl, sift flour, baking powder and sugar.
Stir in milk and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch or 12 x 12-inch pan.
Top with any fruit.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and dot with butter.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Fruit will be on bottom and batter will make a crust.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat to boiling point, then cool.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Slice raw rhubarb and put in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle sugar and jello over top.
Put marshmallows over top of this.
Mix cake mix according to directions given and pour over top.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Turn out onto a platter. Serve warm with Cool Whip.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix well and bake in 3 layers at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water; pour over bread crumbs.
Cover; let stand.
Steam for 2 minutes.
Add hamburg, egg, flour, onion and all seasonings; mix well.
Make into small meatballs.
Brown in small amount of shortening.
Bake in covered casserole dish for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: 200 dollar cake
directions: Mix flour
and
sugar.
Boil
oleo, oil, water and Quik and then pour
it over the flour and sugar mixture.
Mix well. Stir in the
remaining ingredients.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet that has a 1-inch
edge.
Bake
at
400° for 20 minutes. You may make half the recipe in a 9 x 15-inch pan.

title: amazing cleaner
directions: This is for cleaning walls and removing wax from floors.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth. Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust. Pout 1 cup milk into bowl. Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes (mixture will be thick). Stir in pumpkin and spices with wire whisk; mix well. Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Store leftover pie in refrigerator.

title: dill pickles
directions: Place cukes in quart jars.
Add 3 or 4 buttons of garlic to each jar, 1 teaspoon dill seed and 1/4 teaspoon alum.
