Boil the vinegar, water and salt together.
Pour vinegar mixture over cukes.
Seal; let stand 6 weeks.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: raw potato dumplings
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop teaspoonfuls into salted boiling water.
If they fall apart, add more flour.
Boil 10 minutes after they float.
Stir often.
Drain in colander thoroughly.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients; add nuts.
Add eggs and undrained pineapple.
Stir by hand, not mixer.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch aluminum pan or glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes for aluminum pan and 40 minutes in glass dish. Cool.

title: refrigerated cheese torte
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Let it set until thick enough to whip.
Add whipped cream (Cool Whip).
Mix sugar, salt, vanilla and cottage cheese; mix both together.
Line torte pan with cake or crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: calzone
directions: Cook sausage; crumble and drain.
Add tomato sauce, green peppers and Italian seasoning and cook 10 minutes.
Prepare dough recipe as follows.
Place on a greased 10 x 15-inch baking pan. Spread sausage down long middle of dough.
Top sausage with ham, onions, olives and cheese.
Pull dough on sides up and pinch to close.
Pull ends and pinch closed.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° until bread is golden brown (approximately 30 minutes).

title: no-knead rolls
directions: Blend Crisco, sugar, and salt.
Pour boiling water over this mixture and stir until dissolved.
Add beaten egg and mix. Dissolve yeast in warm water, add to mixture.
Then add flour, mixing well after each cup.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to bake, grease pan.
Work a little flour into dough, enough to handle without being sticky.
You can roll out like biscuits (1/2 to 1 inch thick) or shape into balls.
Lay in pan with sides touching.
Let rise 1 hour or until doubled in size.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Line a glass baking dish or pan with aluminum foil with the shiny side up.
Place chops on the bottom.
Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce or other favorite seasonings on next.
Pour the can of Coke in the pan to the top of the chops, but not covering them.
Put salt and pepper on all the chops, then pour plenty of your favorite barbecue sauce on each one of them.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: set blueberry salad
directions: Combine the jello and boiling water.
Add the cream cheese while jello is warm; beat until smooth.
Mix all together and let set.
When set, spread topping on top.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream oleo and cream cheese until fluffy; add sugar gradually. Start adding flour after beating in 2 well-beaten eggs.
Then add 1 egg at a time alternating flour and ending with flour.
Bake in a tube pan at 300°.
Do not preheat oven.
Put pan of water in oven under cake.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 345°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Mix in egg, slightly beaten.
Sift flour and salt and combine with egg mixture; add vanilla and mix until batter is smooth.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls onto greased and floured cookie sheets leaving space between cookies.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until edges turn brown.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: oven french fries(7 grams fat, 0 cholesterol)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel potatoes and slice for French fries.
Lay them out on several layers of paper towels to absorb moisture.
Pat dry with another paper towel.
Potatoes should be as dry as possible.
Place them in a large bowl and drizzle with oil, tossing to coat evenly.
Lay a single layer on a large baking sheet.
Sprinkle dry dressing mix and parsley all over.
Bake 25 minutes, then flip them over with a turner.
Only do this once. Return to oven and increase heat to 450° for 3 to 5 minutes longer or until brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with applesauce and vinegar.
Fold in nuts and raisins.

title: spareribs with kraut
directions: Cut ribs into pieces.
Season with 2 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Place in Dutch oven; brown well.

Combine kraut (including liquid) with remaining ingredients; spoon over ribs. Simmer, covered, for 1 3/4 hours, or until ribs are done, basting with juices several times during the last hour of cooking.
Skim off excess fat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Put cheese on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: celery crunch
directions: Par-boil celery for 2 minutes.
Mix celery, chestnuts, and soup.
Pour into casserole; top with mixture of crushed crackers and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cook until thick while preparing Step 2. Stir occasionally.

title: broccoli casserole 2
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions and drain.
Combine soup, cheese, egg, milk and margarine and stir into broccoli. Stir in rice.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken rotel spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and chop. Leave water to cook spaghetti in. Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine. After cooking spaghetti, leave enough water to cover cooked spaghetti, then add cheese, peas, tomatoes and onions and bell pepper mixture. Salt and pepper to taste. Mix all ingredients well; pour into baking dish. Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: i can't believe it's a cookie
directions: Beat one egg; add sugar and peanut butter and mix.
Roll into balls, about 1-inch.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.
As soon as you take them out, remove them from the pan and press 1 chip onto the top of each cookie.
Ta-da, they're done.
Enjoy!

title: olive nut sandwich spread
directions: Refrigerate 24 hours.
Spread on thin toast.
Will keep weeks in refrigerator.

title: moldy mice
directions: Cream the butter and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Stir in vanilla, flour and nuts.
Roll into small balls, thumb size. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while hot. Cool and store in an airtight container.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: dish-in-one
directions: Break ground meat into chunks and brown.
Drain fat.
Making one or two layers in a greased casserole, put meat, onion, green pepper, corn and tomato slices.
Season with salt and pepper and garlic powder as you go along.
When all ingredients are layered, cover the top of casserole with bread pieces and then lay bacon pieces on top of bread.
(You can freeze or put in refrigerator at this point.)
Bake in a 375° oven until heated through and bacon is browned.

title: corn and bacon casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 2 Tbsp. of drippings. Crumble bacon and set aside. Saute onion in drippings until tender; add garlic, salt, and pepper. Stirring constantly, heat until bubbly then continue for 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in sour cream; mix until smooth. Add corn, parsley, chives and half of the bacon; mix well. Pour into 1 qt. baking dish; sprinkle with remaining bacon. Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: aunt edith's hot dog relish
directions: Cut toast into tiny squares. Spread on small dab of mayonnaise.
Top with piece of Vermont Cheddar cheese and tiny single ring of onion.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Cook rice: set aside.
Season shrimp using black pepper, season all.

After shrimp is seasoned, put 3 teaspoons of crisco oil in a frying pan. Put shrimp in hot oil; stir until done. Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in a pan until slightly brown. Add all other ingredients with the rice and stir in worcestershire sauce and soy sauce, dash of red pepper.
Stir and serve.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach, drain and squeeze dry .
Slice onion thin. Saute in butter until clear.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in a well-greased casserole (covered).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add the cinnamon candies and stir until dissolved.
Add applesauce and stir well.
Put into mold and chill until set.
Sprinkle nuts on top if you wish.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Put meat in 8-inch square dish.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese.
Combine biscuit mix, milk and eggs; beat until smooth.
Pour mixture over casserole, covering evenly. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lasagna\(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Cook beef in large skillet over medium-high heat until meat is brown, stirring to separate meat.
Drain fat.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Reduce heat to low.
Heat through, stirring occasionally. Set aside.
Combine cottage cheese and sour cream in medium bowl; blend well.

title: victoria's homemade cornbread
directions: Measure all ingredients into bowl in order listed.
Stir until just moistened.
Beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Pour into greased 9X9 pan and bake at 425 degrees for 20-25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Put crushed cornflakes on top; broil an additional 5 minutes.

title: pecan pie(georgia watkins)
directions: Mix and pour into two 9-inch pie shells.
Bake 40 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Thaw spinach for four minutes in microwave - drain. Chop and drain artichokes. Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350 degrees for thirty minutes.

title: okra in cheese sauce
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo until tender.
Add the flour, salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes and Velveeta cheese.
Cook just until the cheese is melted.
Pour over okra and bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Mix first three ingredients well and form around a cherry, making 1-inch balls.
Set on waxed paper lined cookie sheets and chill for at least 1 hour.
Melt 2 bags of chips and 1/3 bar of paraffin in a double boiler.
Dip cherries in chocolate to coat. Mix leftover dough with nuts and maple flavoring to make maple nut chocolates.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cook on High for 4 minutes. Then stir quick and cook on High 4 more minutes.
Then add butter and vanilla and cook on High 2 more minutes.
Then add baking soda; stir quickly and pour onto pizza pan (buttered).
Let cool and then break into pieces.

title: oyster cracker mix
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers.
Put crackers in shallow pan and pour mixture evenly over crackers, tossing to coat all crackers.
Bake in 200° oven 15 minutes.
Stir and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix and work together the oleo, peanut butter and sugar until smooth.
Roll into balls and put into refrigerator overnight. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in a double boiler.
Put a toothpick into the balls and dip into mixture, leaving top uncovered to resemble buckeyes.

title: coffee granola bars
directions: Note:
Oats can be quick cooking or old-fashioned.

title: my favorite pound cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites stiff and sit in refrigerator. Reserve 2/3 cup sugar
(from
original 2 2/3 cups).
Add to whites.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Gradually add flour.
Fold in egg
whites, cream and flavoring.
Bake in tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: potato-bacon soup(low-fat)
directions: Spray Pam in nonstick pan.
Add onions and bacon; cook over medium heat, stirring until onions are tender but not brown.
Stir in water and potatoes; bring to boiling.
Cover; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Mash slightly.
Stir in milk, butter flavor, salt and pepper.
Do not boil.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion together. Drain fat.
Place remaining ingredients together in a crock-pot or Dutch oven. Add hamburger mixture. Stir well. Cook on low for approximately 6 to 8 hours. Serve in bowl with grated Cheddar sprinkled on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients with 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle with onion rings and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Place flour in bowl; cut in shortening with pastry blender or fork.
Add milk all at once; mix lightly with fork.
Turn dough onto floured surface; knead slightly.
Pat or roll into desired thickness.
Cut out biscuits; place on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peas and asparagus casserole
directions: Layer the first 4 ingredients in a greased casserole.
Mix together the Cheez Whiz, asparagus juice, soup and grated cheese. Pour over casserole.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Heat at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of coloring and cocoa.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Sift flour and salt together, then blend with mixer at medium speed.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk to mixture.
Blend well.
Add vanilla. Combine vinegar and soda (foams) in a cup; add to batter.
Do not beat.
Stir gently.
Bake in well greased pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain off excess liquid.
Add all ingredients in a double boiler and cook until cheese is melted.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Place in bowl and mix with all other ingredients except potato chips. Pour mixture into buttered 2-quart casserole and top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Serves 4 to 6.

title: honey cornbread
directions: Combine the cornmeal, whole wheat flour, baking powder, salt and soda in a large mixing bowl.
Set side.
Combine buttermilk, oil, eggs and honey.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing well.
Pour batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut cornbread into 2-inch squares to serve.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Cut off 1/3 of top side of bread; carve out inside.
Combine the other ingredients and pour inside of bread.
Place top on bread.
Wrap with heavy-duty foil.
Bake in a 325° oven for 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chop suey
directions: Saute peppers, onion and celery with oil.
Add chicken and saute.
Add any seasonings you want to add and soy sauce to taste. Add to chicken broth.
Add bean sprouts and thicken.
Serve over rice.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine all ingredients into large mixing bowl. Pour equal amounts of mixture into 2 loaf pans. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick placed in center of loaf comes out clean.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Leave overnight before serving.

title: overnight buns
directions: At 3 p.m.:
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water and add 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix all together. Let rise until 10 p.m.
Form into buns on kitchen table.
Cover and leave overnight.
Bake in the morning at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Salt and pepper each.
Remove from skillet.
Pour in soup and heat.
Mix in other ingredients (reserve 1/2 can onion rings).
Put chops in casserole dish. Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour soup mixture over chops; cover and bake for 1 hour.
Uncover; top with remaining onions and brown for 5 minutes.

title: brussels sprouts
directions: Cook package on frozen Brussels sprouts as directed; drain. Put in baking dish (1 1/4 to 1 1/2-quarts).

title: meat loaf superb
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Shape mixture in an 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf in ungreased rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until done. Remove from oven; let stand a few minutes.
Transfer meat loaf to ovenproof platter.
Cut slits about 1/3 of the way through loaf at 1-inch intervals.
Place cheese triangles long side down in each slit.
Place loaf in oven for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is slightly melted.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Drain and stir in butter.
Add Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form mixture into crust in 10-inch greased pie plate.
In skillet, cook beef, onion and green pepper until vegetables are tender.
Drain grease.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt. Heat through and spread cottage cheese over bottom of crust.
Fill pie with meat mixture.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and heat until cheese melts.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine eggs, milk, vanilla, cinnamon and salt. Add bread cubes, brown sugar and raisins. Pour into 8 inch round pan. Bake 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: easy sweet rolls
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover bottom of pan with chopped nuts.
Place frozen rolls in pan.
Melt butter.
Add cinnamon, vanilla pudding, brown sugar and milk.
Mix well.
Do not cook. Pour over rolls.
Let set overnight.
Do not refrigerate.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together cranberry sauce, sugar, and Jello.
Bring it to a boil and let cool.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Cut flour in diet margarine; stir in vanilla and egg.
Add pecans, apples, raisins and dates; chill for 30 minutes.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten cookies with a fork coated with flour.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°. Makes 48 (2-inch) cookies.
Contains 37 calories per cookie.

title: glorified chicken bake
directions: In a 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange chicken.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Spoon soup over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Stir sauce; serve with chicken.
Makes 4 main dish servings. Preparation time:
5 minutes; cook time: 60 minutes.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix flour, white sugar and salt in a 9-inch pie pan. Separately mix the oil and milk together, then add to the dry mix in the pie pan.
Using fingers make a crust.
Mix brown sugar and flour.
Place on top of pie crust.
Pour milk on flour and brown sugar.
Place cubed butter on top of milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Must be bubbling to remove.
Will set as it cools.

title: barbecue tuna spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers.

title: firehouse scrod
directions: Chop garlic; add parsley, oregano, salt, pepper, bread crumbs, olive oil and bay scallops to a bowl and mix by hand.
Place the scrod on a flat baking pan and cover the scrod with the bay scallops mixture.
Add 1 teaspoon of butter on top of each piece and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 450° (preheat oven).
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients, one at a time.
Form into ball.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll cookie dough and cut out.
Add decorations.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes at 400°.

title: unspicy chili
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and fry together.
Season with garlic salt.
Drain grease off.
Mix in kettle with beans, tomato juice and taco mix.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cheese custard pie
directions: Mix in order.
Add 3/4 cup canned milk or enough to fill a 9-inch pie pan.
Put in unbaked crust.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: Cook broccoli in 1 can of broth, just barely tender.
Brown smoked ham in some margarine and pepper.
Add with additional ingredients.
Do not add cheese until removed from heat.
Stir in until melted.
Do not boil.

title: ham skillet supper recipe
directions: Brown ham in butter in 10-inch ovenproof skillet.
Add water and frozen peas. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; slowly stir in instant grits.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Bake in preheated hot (400°) oven about 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: spearmint tea
directions: Add spearmint leaves to 1 qt. boiling water.
Let steep 15-20 minutes. Strain.
Add the 3 qts. cold water and sweeten to taste. Serve over ice.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: heavenly doughnuts
directions: Beat well 4 egg yolks.
Beat in sugar and soft margarine. Stir in sour milk.
Sift together the rest of the ingredients, then stir into wet ingredients.
Chill dough about 2 hours.

title: coconut-pecan icing
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, margarine and vanilla.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Add coconut and pecans.
Beat until thick enough to spread.
Makes about 2 2/3 cups.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Layer half of chicken, then sprinkle with chili powder.
Next, add half of soups, tortillas, onion, pepper, cheese and chicken broth.
Begin second layer with the second half of chicken, soups, tortillas, onion, pepper, cheese and broth.
Spread tomatoes on top and a little cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cover for 30 minutes of the baking time or dish will dry out.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cut carrots on the bias in 1-inch chunks.
Cook, covered, in boiling water; drain.
In sauce pan mix sugar, cornstarch, ginger and salt.
Add juice; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in butter.
Toss with carrots.
Serves 4.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil until soft ball stage (238°) all ingredients except peanuts, vanilla and soda, then add raw peanuts.
Cook until golden brown (310°).
Remove from heat; add vanilla and soda. Stir well and pour quickly onto 2 buttered, warm cookie sheets. When cooled, break into pieces.

title: grace's chicken curry
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Saute onion slices until golden. Add 1/4 cup water.
Add cayenne and turmeric to taste.
Cut tomato up and add to pan to make sauce.
Brown/simmer until grease separates.
Add chicken pieces and garlic.
Cook until lightly browned.
Add 1 1/2 cups water and cook until tender and brown. Add a pinch of cinnamon, clove powder and fresh black pepper. Cook another few minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Brown sausage and onion, then add cream cheese, mustard, bread crumbs, parsley and garlic powder.
Mix well. Add sauerkraut and mix well. Refrigerate until cool.
Mix eggs and milk.
Shape sauerkraut mixture into walnut size balls.
Dip balls in flour, then egg mixture.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Deep fry and drain. Makes 70 to 75 sauerkraut balls.

title: pilaf
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add noodles and onion; fry until light golden brown.
Add rice and stir until coated with butter. Add broth and salt; stir well and simmer for 25 minutes, covered.

title: easy flaky pie crust
directions: Mix vinegar with milk; set aside.
Cut the shortening with pastry blender (or 2 knives) into the flour to which the salt has been added.
Mixture should be the size of peas.
Add milk, all at once; stir with a fork until blended.
With hands, gather together into ball of dough.
Makes 1 double crust and 1 single crust.
Any leftover crust may be frozen.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream together.
Chill for one hour, shape in balls the size of walnuts.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: koulourakia(easter cookies)
directions: Sift flour with baking powder.
Set aside.
In large bowl, beat at high speed the butter, sugar, 3 eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
At low speed, add flour mixture gradually.
Beat until combined.
Shape a heaping teaspoonful of dough into a 6-inch long rope; fold in half and twist together with two turns.
In small bowl, slightly beat remaining egg with one tablespoon water.
Place sesame seed on waxed paper.
Brush each cookie with beaten egg, then dip each, egg side down, into seed.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until firm. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: caramel meringue pie
directions: For filling:
First, separate yolks, setting whites asides. In saucepan, beat yolks; add milk, 1/2 cup sugar mixed with 1 tablespoon flour.
Stir until all is blended.
Place on low heat (best to use double boiler).

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil. Add eggs. Beat well. Add pumpkin, then water.

Sift together dry ingredients. Add to pumpkin mixture, then stir in raisins and nuts. Grease 3 loaf pans; do not flour. Set on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans. Wrap in foil.
Can be frozen.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 500°. Grease iron cornstick pan. Fill pan and bake at 500° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: georgia pecan pie
directions: Bake the same as other states.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and add tomato sauce.
Put in pepper shells.
Put in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain well.
Combine meat and green chilies in greased 11 x 14-inch baking dish.
Layer tortillas over top.
In separate bowl, mix cans of soup and pour over tortillas. Bake at 350° until hot.

title: surprise jello
directions: Combine dry jello, strawberries and cottage cheese; fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate well before serving.

title: cheese cupcakes(makes 24)
directions: Blend cream cheese, 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla until smooth.
Then add eggs.
Again, blend until smooth. Fill cups 3/4 full.
Use foil muffin baking cups.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: honey-wheat muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine egg, milk, honey and oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until done.
Remove from pans immediately.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Cook pie for 15 minutes, then reduce to 325° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package. Drain and rinse with cold water. Combine macaroni, cheese, tuna, pickles and onion in a large bowl. Stir together mayonnaise, salt, pepper and garlic. Pour over macaroni mixture and toss.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.

title: company's coming salad
directions: Dissolve and cool water and gelatin.
Add drained pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Chill in large, flat dish.
Heat pineapple juice; add flour, sugar and egg.
Cook until thick and cool.
Fold into whipped cream.
Spread over gelatin mixture. Sprinkle grated cheese over mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as the box said. Place rice in Pyrex dish.
Add broccoli soup. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pecans.
Form into one large or two small balls.
Roll into finely chopped pecans.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Take out of refrigerator 15 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: cheese crispy crackers
directions: Grate cheese and cream with oleo.
Add sifted dry ingredients. Fold in Rice Krispies.
Pinch off pieces about the size of a marble.
Roll and place on cookie sheet; mash down with a fork. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder together.
Add persimmon pulp.
Combine milk, eggs and cinnamon, then add to flour mixture. Add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan, until brown (approximately 40 minutes).

title: toasted mushrooms
directions: Clean and finely chop the mushrooms.
Saute 5 minutes in the butter.
Blend in flour, salt and monosodium glutamate (optional). Stir in light cream and cook until thick, about 5 minutes.
Add minced chives and lemon juice.

title: banana salad
directions: Slice bananas in halves lengthwise and lay cut side down on a paper towel.
Spread peanut butter on 1/2 of cut bananas, then put the 2 halves back together.
Next, slice the filled bananas in 1-inch chunks, the short way.
Put in bowl and set aside.
In saucepan, beat eggs with fork.
Add sugar and vinegar and stir. Place over medium heat and stir constantly until mixture thickens. Remove from heat; add margarine and set pan in cool water.
Stir until cool.
Pour over bananas.
If desired, sprinkle crushed peanuts over top of salad.
Can refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: apricot jello dessert
directions: In a pan add jello to boiling water and stir until dissolved. Add the marshmallows and stir until melted.
Let set until partially jelled.
Add cottage cheese, pineapple and juice and pecans.
Mix all of this with jello and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in large dish and garnish with apricot halves.

title: baked chicken breasts supreme
directions: In large bowl, combine first 8 ingredients.
Place chicken in mixture and turn to coat.
Cover and marinate overnight.
Remove from marinade and coat each piece with crumbs.
Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage lasagna wraps
directions: Cook and drain lasagna noodles.
Divide smoked sausage into 6 pieces.
Split lengthwise and stuff with 1/2 slice Mozzarella cheese.
Wrap each piece of sausage in a noodle.
Place in a baking dish and cover with 1 jar spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fancy spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck in 1/2 stick of butter.
Add sausage, onions and garlic bulbs.
Combine with other ingredients in a large pot.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
This freezes well.

title: blueberry topping
directions: Combine in a saucepan sugar and cornstarch.
Add blueberries and cook.
Stir until thick; then stir in lemon juice and butter. Set aside and cool.
Put this topping on a cheesecake or something that calls for blueberry filling.

title: tinoland manok(gingered chicken soup with papaya or chayote)
directions: Lightly pound chicken breasts. Season all sides with salt, pepper and lime juice. Cut into bite-sized pieces. Set aside. Pour oil into a heavy frying pan and place over medium-high heat. When oil is hot, add the onion and garlic and saute. Stirring constantly until onions are golden and garlic is crisp. Add the chicken and minced ginger. Continue sauteing; stir constantly until chicken has whitened. Transfer sauteed ingredients into a sauce pan and add three cups water. Bring soup to a boil, cover, lower heat and simmer until chicken is tender (about 15 minutes). Add the diced papaya (or chayote) and simmer 5-6 additional minutes. Correct seasonings to taste. Serve hot.

title: marinated raw mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients in a covered bowl.
Refrigerate for 2 days before serving.
Serves 8.

title: salisbury bourguignonne
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/3 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg and salt. Shape into 6 oval patties.
In skillet, cook bacon until crisp; remove and crumble.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings. Brown patties in drippings.
Stir in remaining soup, water, wine and seasonings.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over cooked noodles; garnish with bacon.

title: native american fry bread
directions: Combine ingredients and fry in 1/2 cup of hot grease.

title: ranch bacon cheddar dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve with your favorite dipping chips.

title: pina colada jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water to reserved juice to measure 1 1/2 cups; add to dissolved gelatin.
Stir in rum and coconut flavoring.
Remove 1 1/2 cups of mixture; chill until slightly thickened (about 1 hour). Also chill remaining gelatin until slightly thickened (about 45 minutes); fold in pineapple.
Pour into oiled 1-quart mold.
Chill 5 minutes.
Whip cream, gradually adding sugar, until soft peaks form.
Thoroughly fold into the 1 1/2 cups slightly thickened gelatin.
Pour over pineapple layer.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto serving dish.
Makes 6-8 servings (very generous servings).

title: strawberry fill ups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange biscuits in round cake pan. Make a hollow center with thumb in each biscuit.
Fill with strawberry preserves.
Brush each biscuit with egg, sugar and milk mixture.
Bake 15 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Pour melted butter and pecans in baking dish.
Toast at 350° for 10 minutes.
In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one by one, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in vanilla and 1 cup toasted pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: wheat rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups wheat flour, sugar, salt, yeast and margarine in a large bowl.
Gradually add warm water; stir well.
Add 2 cups wheat flour to thicken; mix in white flour.
Knead until well mixed.
Grease top of dough and cover.
Let rise for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Grease pan or cast iron skillet and shape rolls into size of golf balls.
Let rise 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook celery, onions and potatoes in water until potatoes are almost done.
Add California vegetables and bouillon cubes and cook
until done.
Add Velveeta cheese and cream of chicken soup, also
water chestnuts, if desired.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Blend sugar, oil, eggs and milk together.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking soda, then add to sugar mixture.
Pour boiling water over cereals and raisins, then add mixtures together.
This batter may be kept in refrigerator for several weeks.
Bake as needed.
The 2 different cereals offer different textures for a successful end result.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Butter bread; place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook and crumble sausage until brown; drain. Spoon over bread slices.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs with half and half and salt; mix well and pour over cheese. Cover; chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes, or until set.
Serves 8.

title: smothered steak
directions: Cut steak into servings; sprinkle with salt and pepper and dip in flour.
Fry in a couple of tablespoons of fat until brown on both sides.
Then add soup (use the can from which it came to measure the water) and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer on top of stove, turning over the pieces at least once.
Cook until it can be cut with a fork (from 1 1/2 to 2 hours).

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Crumble graham crackers in a Ziploc bag and pour into bowl. Melt butter and
put with graham crackers.
Stir and empty into glass baking dish.
Spread pudding across top.
Add additional graham crackers or Cool Whip on top if desired.

title: chocolate mint cheese cake
directions: Coat an 8 - 9-inch spring form pan with nonstick spray.
Break cookies using a food processor on pulse until fine crumbs form. Transfer 1/4 c. crumbs to a small bowl.
Cover and reserve.
Add butter to remaining crumbs and blend.
Press over bottom of prepared pan and place in the freezer.
Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in a small sauce pan.
Let stand 1 minute.
Heat over med-low until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Whisk cocoa into warm water, blend, set aside.

title: potato soup with rivels
directions: Boil potatoes in broth with celery, parsley, salt and pepper. When potatoes are almost soft, beat eggs and flour together with a fork until crumbly and sprinkle over soup.
Cook for 10 minutes more.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Press raw ground beef into 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with salt and onion.
Spread cream of chicken soup over beef.
Cover with vegetables.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican fiesta dip
directions: Spread bean dip on platter in 10-inch round circle (large plate).
Mix the avocados and lemon juice and mash; spread over beans.
Mix the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix together; spread over avocados.
Spread the green onion tops over all.
Add tomatoes to top of onions.
Add olives to top of tomatoes.
Top complete dip with cheese.
The circle makes a very colorful and attractive dip!
Serve with taco chips.
Serves 12 to 16 with a large package of taco chips.

title: ice cream jello
directions: Prepare jello as directed and add ice cream, by spoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Chill until slightly thickened and stir. Chill until set.
Ready to serve in 1 hour.

title: creole gumbo
directions: Pour cooking oil in to large frying pan over low heat and add sifted flour slowly.
Stir constantly to brown evenly.
It takes about an hour to make a roux correctly.
Cook until roux become the color of coffee with cream and smells like browned flour.

title: south african curry(serves 4)
directions: Fry onions in oil; add tomatoes and stir.
When it sticks, add vinegar, sugar and curry to create a sauce.
Blend sauce and set aside.
In a large covered skillet add meat, potatoes and frozen peas.
Add sauce, cover and simmer until potatoes are cooked. Serve with bowls of coconut, chutney, crushed pineapple and sliced bananas to garnish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salt water for 5 minutes.
Drain and cut into 1-inch pieces and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Place chicken over broccoli (add lemon pepper, if desired).
Mix together mayonnaise and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over soup.
Crumble 2 pieces of dry toast for bread crumbs and mix together with margarine.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon chiffon cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and lemon peel until blended. Press evenly over bottom and sides of an 9-inch spring-form pan that has been buttered.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool well.

title: eclair cake
directions: Bring water and margarine to boil.
Remove from heat and beat in flour with fork.
Add eggs (1 to 2 at a time) and beat until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan slightly greased with butter or shortening.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: cherry angel food cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on package.
Beat whipping cream and powdered sugar in chilled bowl until stiff.
Fold in cherries, cherry syrup and walnuts.
Frost cake.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon glaze cake
directions: As
soon
as
cake
is
taken from oven and while it is still hot, punch holes all through cake with a cooking fork or ice pick.
(Don't
worry,
it
will
not fall.) Pour glaze on cake.
A shiny, glazed film will cover the top of cake.
Isn't it fun to bake!

title: apple nut torte
directions: Beat eggs until thick. Add sugar and beat for 5 minutes at high speed. Add sifted dry ingredients. Fold in apples and nuts. Grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Cut into squares and serve with whipped cream.

title: meat-n-peas salad
directions: Cut meat into strips; add cheese, celery and drained peas. Combine mayonnaise, mustard and lemon juice; toss with meat mixture.
Chill.
Serve in lettuce cups with a dusting of paprika. Serves 4.

title: spareribs
directions: Place spareribs in roaster with sliced onion.
Make a sauce of vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, paprika, peppers, chili powder, catsup and water.
Pour over spareribs, cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally.
Turn spareribs once. Remove cover last 15 minutes for browning.

title: dessert dip for fresh fruit
directions: Cream cream cheese and orange juice until smooth; blend in Marshmallow Creme.
Serve with all kinds of fresh fruit.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix well. Place in an 8 x 8 glass pan. Press in the meat mixture. Lightly cover with tomato sauce. Cover with clear wrap. Microwave 7 minutes. Turn dish and microwave 7 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: 1. Boil chicken with onion, celery, and carrots (all chopped fine), pepper corns, marjoram, thyme,parsley, salt, and bay leaf. 2. When done boiling, chop enough chicken to make about 2 cups of bite size chunks.

Then mix chicken, cream of mushroom soup, broth (make sure the broth contains all of the onion, carrots, and celery you boiled), diced chilies, and 1/2 cups of the cheese. 3. Line the bottom of a casserole dish with torn pieces of tortilla and layer the mix over the top.
Do several layers this way and end up with chicken mix on top. 4. Top with remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat until well blended.
Beat egg into mixture.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water,
pie
filling,
nuts
and pineapple.
Chill until firm. When firm, ice with Cool Whip mixed with cream cheese.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar gradually; cream well. Add eggs one at a time.
Sift cocoa, flour, salt and baking powder several times.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Heat sugar, margarine and syrup over medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda, stirring fast until well blended.
Pour over popcorn.
Stir until well coated.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour out and separate.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream together butter or margarine and sugar for 20 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, lemon extract and 7-Up.
Pour into well-greased 12 cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: russian fluff with rice
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Drain off excess fat.
Place in baking dish. Combine peas, soup and rice; pour over meat mixture. Top with crushed chips or crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until hot.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Cream the cheese with small amount of milk, continuing to add milk and pudding mix.
Add Cool Whip last and beat on low. Crumble layer of cookies in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
(Save some to sprinkle on top.)
Layer in filling and chill.
Garnish with remaining crumbles.

title: crab and cheese appetizers
directions: Mix together and spread on English muffin halves.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Cut each muffin slice into fourths.
They may be served immediately or frozen on cookie sheets (after cooled).
After freezing (approximately 1 hour) on the cookie sheet, store in a Ziploc bag in the freezer.

title: chicken salad in croissants
directions: In medium bowl, combine chicken, celery and cashews.
Set aside. Mix mayonnaise and poultry seasoning.
Add to chicken mixture.
Toss lightly.
Chill.
Place lettuce on croissant, spoon chicken salad on lettuce and serve.

title: eclair cake
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch pan. Line bottom with crackers. Mix vanilla pudding with milk and stir in Cool Whip, putting part of the mixture over graham crackers. Layer graham crackers over pudding mixture until mixture is gone. Put another layer of graham crackers and cover with chocolate icing. Cover container with Reynolds Wrap. Cool 2 hours before serving.

title: barbecued baked beans
directions: Brown onion and bell pepper in margarine.
After browning onion and bell pepper, mix all ingredients together in baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar, milk and margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Lower heat and cook slowly for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in peanuts and vanilla.
Beat until candy thickens and loses its gloss, about 4 minutes.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: hamburger meat balls
directions: Mix together hamburger, oats, milk and onion.
Form into balls and brown.
Mix together catsup, water, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and vinegar.
Place hamburger balls in baking dish and pour sauce mixture over top.
Cover baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chinese barbecue(serves 4)
directions: Heat first 6 ingredients.
Pour over ribs and marinate.
Place on rack in foil lined pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, turning and basting with marinade.

title: friendship tea
directions: *So that all candy can be eaten, candy that is not wrapped can be attached using frosting.
Let pieces set for about 5 minutes before attaching new parts.

title: town house delights
directions: Cook on medium heat until thickened (mash dates).
Remove and stir in 1 cup chopped pecans.
Spread on Town House crackers; place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: glorified peas
directions: Chop green pepper and cook in butter until soft.
Add to soup, cheese and pimento.
Drain peas and stir with other ingredients. Cook on medium heat until bubbly.

title: kansas dirt cake
directions: Blend cookies in blender to make crumbs.
Pat 1/2 of crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Fold in 1 container of whipped topping.
Mix together instant pudding, milk and vanilla.
Fold in the cream cheese mixture.
Pour over cookie crumbs.
Top with second container of whipped topping and remaining Oreo cookie crumbs.

title: california quiche
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake shell for 4 minutes.
Spread onions and mushrooms over crust, then cover it with cheese.
Pour in egg mixture.
Bake pie for 12 minutes. Reduce oven heat to 350° and bake for another 15 minutes.
Turn the oven off and let it sit in the oven for 10 minutes and then on the counter for 10 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites to soft peaks; add sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Add Rice Krispies and chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Heat oven to 350° before starting mixing process.
Turn off oven when you put cookies in.
Leave at least 3 hours.
Better yet, leave overnight.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; add taco seasoning mix and water (amount on package).
Cool.
Mix everything together except dressing and chips.
Stir them in right before serving.

title: mushrooms rockefeller
directions: Lightly oil a 13 x 9 inch baking dish.	Preheat oven to 375°. Clean mushrooms and pull entire stem out of each mushroom cap; set aside.
Place caps in a single layer in baking dish.

title: magic chocolate sauce(to give even simple desserts a party air.  makes about 2 cups.)
directions: In top of double boiler, put Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk, chocolate and salt.
Cook over rapidly boiling water, stirring often, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Slowly stir in hot water until sauce is of desired thickness.
Stir in vanilla extract.
Serve hot or chilled.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Combine the first six ingredients.
Dip chicken in milk, then roll in the cornmeal mixture.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes, or until juices run clear.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: renee's salad dressing
directions: Mix water and salt. Sprinkle extremely lightly on lettuce and enjoy.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken and broccoli on bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry together.
Pour over meat, vegetable layer.
Top with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour (cover for last 10 minutes).

title: clam casino
directions: Use a casserole dish and spray with Pam.
Mix all ingredients together, omitting bacon.
Bake at 350° or 370° uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with bacon crumbs.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place top crust over.
Roll edges to seal.
Brush top crust with milk.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar and slash in several places.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: macaroni and bean soup(low-fat)
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and rinse.
In a large soup kettle, heat olive oil over medium-high heat.
Add carrots, celery and onion; saute until tender.
Add tomatoes with liquid, chicken broth, salt, pepper and water. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: candied fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and cream.
Coat cherries and nuts with 1 cup flour and mix remaining flour into batter.
Fold in cherries and nuts.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream together first three ingredients.
Add buttermilk and mix.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add prunes and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into 3 eight-inch greased and floured pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with a caramel or buttercream frosting or your own favorite frosting.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Boil Jell-O and pineapple for 3 minutes; cool.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: pecan bars
directions: Mix the flour, powdered sugar, oleo and salt and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Let cool.

title: taco salad
directions: Ground ground round and onions together; add seasoning, dice tomatoes and chop up lettuce.
My favorite is to put chips down first, then meat, pile cheese on.
Microwave until cheese melts, about 1 minute.
Then add tomatoes, lettuce and hot sauce to your liking.

title: cherry-chocolate cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat margarine and brown sugar with an electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add egg yolks, beating well.
Blend in melted chocolate, orange peel, cinnamon, vanilla and salt.
Stir in flour.
Place pecans and egg whites in 2 separate small bowls.
Slightly beat egg whites with a fork. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Dip each ball into egg whites; roll in pecans to coat.
Place balls 2-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheets.
Using your thumb, make slight indentation in top of each cookie.
Bake in 350° oven about 12 minutes or until edges are firm.
Cool cookies.
Fill centers of cooled cookies with a small spoonful of jelly or preserves.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream
sugar and butter together.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at
a
time; mix.
Combine flour and baking soda.
Add to mixture and
add
buttermilk
a little at a time.
Beat well. Add vanilla. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple nut cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan well.
Mix sugar, Wesson oil, eggs and apples.
Add flour and pecans slowly.
Add vanilla and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Mix the nuts in with the flour as this keeps them from going to the bottom of the cake.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Combine drained salmon, chicken soup, onion, parsley, 1 egg and 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Mix well and chill for one hour.
Shape into 3 inch patties.
Slightly beat the 2 remaining eggs.
Roll patties in flour, dip into egg, then coat with remaining bread crumbs. Chill an additional 2 hours.
Heat deep frying oil to 365°.
Add 4 croquettes at a time and fry about 3 minutes or until golden. Drain on paper towels.
Serve with cocktail or tartar sauce.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain and cut into 2-inch pieces.
Beat together Ricotta, eggs, sugar and flavoring and add to spaghetti. Turn into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan (greased) and bake at 350° for 1 hour or 1 hour and 15 minutes.
When cold can refrigerate.
When serving, sprinkle confectioners sugar on top and cut in squares.

title: lilliput meat balls
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, milk, onion and salt.
Shape mixture into little balls, using 1 teaspoon per ball.
Melt butter in a large, heavy skillet.
Brown balls nicely on all sides.
Pour off most of the fat from the pan.
Mix wine, catsup and oregano; pour over balls.
Add salt to taste.
Cover; simmer gently about 20 minutes, shaking gently from time to time to cook balls evenly. Serve in a chafing dish or a pottery casserole set over a candle warmer.
Provide toothpicks for spearing balls.
Makes about 60 tiny balls.

title: easy bake cornbread
directions: Add 1 Tbsp. oil to medium iron skillet and heat.
Mix meal and flour in mixing bowl.
Add buttermilk.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour excess hot oil from skillet into mixture and stir in.
Pour mixture into hot skillet and bake in 425° oven until golden brown.

title: lumpy dick
directions: Heat milk and salt to scalding in heavy pan.
Beat eggs well and pour over flour.
Mix carefully with fingers to form lumps; drop lumps into milk mixture and stir.
Let simmer.
If lumps are too large, break apart with fork.
Serve hot.
May be topped with cream or butter and salt and pepper or butter, sugar and cinnamon.

title: french baked beans
directions: Put cooked white beans into a baking dish.
Add tomatoes and sliced onion.
Add water.
Season with salt, pepper and sugar to taste.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Put into 13 x 10-inch dish and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Mix softened cream cheese and 1 cup sugar, then fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzels.
Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water, dissolve and add strawberries. Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Place chicken in bottom of dish. Cut up onion over chicken.
Dice cheese on chicken.
Mix soups and tomatoes together and pour over top.
Add chips! Bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple juice and all in baking dish.
Smooth pie filling over top, then pour dry cake mix over this; smooth out. Pour melted margarine over top, then cover with nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: paella
directions: Prepare yellow rice dinner according to package directions in large pan.
While rice is cooking, chop cooked ham or sausage and cooked chicken.
Warm shrimp, ham or sausage, chicken, peas and carrots in microwave.

title: bourbon roll
directions: Put crushed wafers into a large bowl and add fruit and nuts. Stir the bourbon into the sweetened milk and last mix into other ingredients.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Wrap in wax paper and chill at least 3 hours.
Slice and serve.

title: chili
directions: In a large skillet brown ground chuck with onions and peppers; drain.
Place in a large sauce pan.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, cumin, garlic powder, soup mix, kidney beans and juice, red pepper flakes.
Simmer 1 hour.
Make a paste with flour and add to mixture.
Stir well to thicken.
If too thick add tomato juice to thin.

title: butterscotch oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add salt, vanilla and eggs (slightly beaten).
Sift the flour and soda together; add to creamed mixture along with the oats.
Mix until smooth and roll into 2 rolls.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours.
Slice and bake on ungreased sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.
Bake at 400°.

title: southwestern vegetable salad
directions: In large bowl, combine corn and zucchini.
Add dressing and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Add avocado and radishes and toss lightly.
Arrange tomato slices on platter.
Top with vegetables.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water; stir constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in jello until dissolved. Pour over berries.
Mix well. Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate until set.
Top with whipped topping.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together; add cheese last.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cover and bake 5 hours at 250°. Can do in a crock-pot also.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place apples in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle over these (mixed together):
sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Put on topping made of oatmeal, flour, brown sugar, soda, baking powder and melted butter.
Blend until crumbly.
Bake 40 minutes in moderate oven.

title: cornflake holly
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows over low heat (you can do this in the microwave; melt a few minutes at a time, stirring occasionally).
Add 3/4 teaspoon green food coloring and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Stir in cornflakes. Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper. Decorate with candies for holly berries.
Work fast.
The cookies set quickly! Children can do the decorating!

title: fruit magic
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling in an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Combine cake mix and nuts in a bowl.
Add softened margarine and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over the top of the pie filling.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: white chili
directions: Cook chicken breast in soup pan.
Remove chicken when tender and chop into bite-size pieces.
Put back into broth; add beans and onions.
Cook until onions are tender.
Add chilies and simmer.

title: hard to make crust apple pie
directions: In small bowl, combine 1 cup flour, oil, milk and 1/4 cup oatmeal.
Stir until well blended.
Press onto sides and bottom of a 9-inch pie pan.
Do not press onto rim.
Toss apple with pudding mix to coat thoroughly; pour into crust.

title: apple brown bake
directions: Bake in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Spray with cooking spray.
Sprinkle bottom with bread crumbs to coat surface; reserve remaining bread crumbs.
Squeeze 1 tablespoon lemon juice; set aside.
Combine lemon, sugar and cinnamon.
Peel and core apples and cut them into thin slices.
In a dish, layer 1/3 apples, 1/3 bread crumbs and 1/3 sugar mixture.
Dot with margarine.
Repeat 2 more layers.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: esther's rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Add next 1 cup water, egg and flour.
Let rise in warm area.
Punch down.
Make into rolls or may be refrigerated for later use.
Let rise a second time.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: delicious dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well. Chill overnight. Serve with fresh carrots, celery sticks, broccoli, squash, cauliflower or other vegetables for dipping.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes to cook in water until done. Drain.
Using electric mixer, cream the potatoes while adding the 1 stick of butter, eggs and 1 cup sugar.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add rest and stir until mixed (do not beat).
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute all 1/2 to 1-inch thick pieces of vegetables in margarine.
Add liquid and simmer, but don't boil away liquid. Add dash of cayenne and white pepper. Cook until soft.
Mix ingredients and add liquid in a blender until smooth.
Add 4 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese while blending.
Return puree to pot and add 1 pint half and half to mix.
Heat through.

title: pasta and sausage salad
directions: Cook pasta; rinse with cold water and drain.
Cool completely and turn into a large bowl.
Add pepper, onions and olives.
In a small bowl, whisk until smooth the salad dressing, sour cream and milk.
Add cheese, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add all of the preceding to the pasta and toss well.
Let marinate.
Just before serving, add the meat.
Serves 6.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water and butter; bring to a boil.
Stir in flour for 1 minute.
Take off heat.
Drop eggs in mix until it forms a ball. Place 1 teaspoon of batter at a time on cookie sheet.
Makes about 24 Cream Puffs.
Heat at 400° for about 35 minutes.
After cooling, cut puffs in half and fill with instant pudding.

title: company fruit salad
directions: Combine all the fruit in a large bowl.

title: tamale pie(for the microwave)
directions: Brown and crumple beef in 2-quart casserole.
Drain and add taco spices, tomato sauce, corn (with liquid), 1 cup water, raisins and olives.
Heat to simmer (about 10 minutes on high).
Sprinkle an even layer of cornmeal over the top.
Gently pour 1/2 cup water over to moisten cornmeal.
Cover and microwave 5 to 8 minutes.

title: sesame pork and broccoli
directions: In a small bowl, combine broth, cornstarch and soy sauce; mix well.
Stir in onions and set aside.
Cut pork into bite-sized strips.
Heat oil in wok or nonstick skillet on medium heat.
Add pork and garlic; stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until pork is tender. Remove pork; keep warm.
Add broccoli and broth to wok; simmer 8 minutes.
Add cooked pork and pimento; cook just until hot.
Stir frequently.
Sprinkle with sesame seed and serve.
Makes 6 servings.
Contains 165 calories per serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Place chicken in an oblong sprayed baking dish.
Lay 1/2 slice of bacon on top of each piece of chicken.
Combine soup, sour cream and wine; pour mixture over chicken.
Bake 3 hours at 275°, uncovered.
Serve on rice.

title: baked eggplant and crabmeat
directions: Boil eggplant until tender; drain and let cool. Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine. Then add eggplant. Combine the well beaten eggs with the crabmeat and season to taste. Pour into a greased baking dish. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs. Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes. Can be frozen.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put rice in greased casserole.
Place pork chops on top.
Add onion slices on chops.
Slice tomatoes on onions.
Slice pepper on tomatoes.
Add beef bouillon.
Cover with foil and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well.
Makes 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bayou sauce piquante
directions: Make a roux with oil and flour; when dark, add onions, celery, parsley and cook until wilted.
Add tomato sauce and tomato juice; cook about one hour.
Add crab meat and catfish and cook another hour, stirring frequently; add shrimp and cook 10 minutes longer. Serve over cooked rice.
Serves approximately 8.

title: wall lake trout
directions: Make a crimp tent of foil for fish; cook 15 minutes at 400°. Saute mushrooms, grapes, pecans, wine, butter and olive oil. Start fish and saute same time.
Squeeze lemon on fish just before serving.
Cover fish with sauteed combination.

title: pickled grapes
directions: Halve and seed grapes.
Place grape halves in a bowl and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Let stand at room temperature for about 1 hour, toss often.
Sprinkle with vinegar, toss and refrigerate, covered, until ready to serve.
Divide grapes among 6 individual bowls or goblets.
Pour about 1/2 cup wine into each bowl and serve.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Mix jello, marshmallows, cream cheese and 7-Up in saucepan over low heat (melt).
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice and pineapple; mix.
Set in fridge for 3 hours.
Remove.
Fold in nuts and Cool Whip on low speed.
Put in mold and chill.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Cook until thickens; then add 1/2 cup of Hellmann's mayonnaise.
Makes 1 pint.

title: 6 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and cream together until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add flour mixture with milk and flavorings, ending with flour.
Bake in a large greased tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cake from pan 2 to 3 minutes after removing from oven.

title: orange chicken pasta salad
directions: Mix dressing, juice and seasonings in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavoring and flour a little at a time; beat well.
Fold in small 7-Up.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: After chicken
has
been cooked, take out all the bones and put back into large pot.
Add cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom
soup
and
water.
Add garden peas, salt, pepper, onion and
milk.	Cook
all
this
together for a few minutes. Prepare casserole
dish by melting 1 stick of butter or margarine.	When melted,
add 1/2 package Pepperidge Farm dressing mix.
Pour chicken
mixture over dressing and add the rest of dressing on top.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: candied nuts
directions: Add salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Mix in pecans until they are well coated.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush Oreos.
Set aside 3/4 cup crumbs for top.
Mix butter with remaining crumbs.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix pudding with milk and softened ice cream.
Pour over Oreos; chill.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle with crumbs and chill.

title: fish casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender. Drain. Add fish, mushroom soup, liquid and salt. Blend and pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle top with bread crumbs moistened with butter. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes. Serve hot.

title: philadelphia cream cheese salad
directions: Prepare orange jello with 1 1/2 cups boiling water and add marshmallows, stir (melt).
Add pineapple, cheese and salad dressing while still warm.
Chill, when cool fold in whipped cream. Let set (overnight).
Prepare lime jello with 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Put layer of lime jello on top.
Should be made the day before serving.
Makes 16 servings.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce.
No dressing needed.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Mix in eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, salt and soda; add to cream mixture. Stir in oats, nuts and raisins.
Roll
into small balls, place on greased cookie sheet. Flatten
with
a
fork.
Bake
at
for
10 to 12 minutes or until golden.

title: upside-down surprise cake
directions: Mix together the Ricotta cheese, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Set aside.

Make yellow cake mix according to package directions. Pour cake mix into a greased extra large loaf pan. Spread Ricotta cheese mixture on top of cake. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: spicy pecans
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves; set aside. Melt butter in a pan. In a small bowl, beat egg white and water until frothy; add pecans and coat well. Place coated pecans in pan with melted butter. Bake at 250° until done.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut the eggs in halves.
Put the yellows of the eggs in a bowl.
Mash with a fork.
Add the mustard, mayonnaise and milk. Mix well.
Spoon the mixture back into the egg whites.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in plenty of water until just tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.
Let stand until cool enough to handle, then peel.
Cut into 1/4-inch thick slices and place in salad bowl.
In skillet, fry bacon until crisp; remove and crumble, then add to potatoes.
To fat in skillet, add chopped onion and cook until transparent.
Then add vinegar, salt, pepper, sugar, bouillon cubes and water.
Bring to boil while stirring and dissolving cubes.
Pour, with salad oil, over potatoes; toss together lightly.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve warm.

title: faye's lobster salad
directions: Sprinkle lobster meat with lemon juice.
Add celery, onion and pickle relish.
Moisten with mayonnaise.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fold in egg slices.
Serve over lettuce.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Soak peppers, tomatoes, onions and salt overnight in water to cover.
Drain and wash off.
In a pot, place sugar, vinegar, turmeric and spices tied in cheesecloth.
Bring to a boil.
Add the drained vegetables.
Return to a boil.
Spoon into jars and seal.
Yields 6 pints.

title: candy sweet potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Place in 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.

title: wild rice with mushrooms
directions: Cook mushrooms and onion in 1/4 cup butter in skillet until mushrooms are lightly browned.
Combine mushrooms, wild rice and melted butter; toss gently until mushrooms and butter are evenly distributed throughout rice.
Serves 8.
Serve with roast pheasant.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Brown sausage and drain.
Stir in all other ingredients, except rice, and simmer until veggies are tender.
Add rice; mix well.

title: baked rice
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in butter, adding a little more butter if needed, until soft.
Mix together rice, water and consomme with other ingredients in a casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: *You can substitute fat-free mayonnaise and sour cream.

title: fruit chicken-macaroni salad
directions: Mix chicken, grapes and water chestnuts.
Mix mayo and salt; toss with chicken mixture.
Add pasta.
Last, toss in oranges. Refrigerate.

title: kahlua
directions: Lightly boil water, sugar and coffee for 1 hour (do not boil over).
Let cool; add quart of vodka and vanilla.
Makes 1 quart plus one fifth.

title: new potato bake
directions: In large bowl, combine soup, sour cream and hot pepper sauce. Add potatoes and onions; toss to coat well.

title: oven barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Pour all ingredients mixed over pork chops. Cover and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: brussels sprouts with cashews
directions: Wash sprouts.
Combine water and bouillon cubes and bring to a boil.
Add sprouts and simmer 15 minutes or until done.
Drain well and place in serving bowl.
Melt butter in small skillet, then add cashews and seasonings.
Cook on low heat 3 to 4 minutes. Pour over sprouts and serve.

title: medivnyk (honey cake)
directions: Bring honey just to a boil.
Cool.
Cream together brown sugar and butter.
Slowly beat in egg yolks, then honey.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger.
Blend into honey mixture alternately with sour cream.
Fold in walnuts and raisins. Turn batter into greased 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for one hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; turn out on wire rack to cool completely. Sprinkle with icing sugar.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cover chicken with water and cook until tender.
Drain fat from broth and save broth.
Tear or chop chicken in small pieces and return to broth.
Add corn, tomato juice, bean dip, onion, potatoes, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Simmer until onions and potatoes are done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In mixing bowl, cut the peanut butter into the powdered sugar until crumbly; set aside.

title: potato cheese quiche
directions: Put thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat down on bottom and sides.
Brush with melted butter or margarine.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and add cheese and ham.
Beat half and half, eggs and seasoned salt.
Pour over cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
May substitute cheeses of your choice.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine and beat well the cake mix, eggs, salad oil and pudding mix.
Add, beating well, bottle of 7-Up.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 45 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat; add 1 teaspoon salt and the pepper.
Add spaghetti sauce to meat.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles in water with the remaining salt for 15 minutes.
Drain.
Pour half of tomato sauce into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place 2 noodles side by side in pan.
Cover with meat mixture.
Add another layer of noodles. Cover with cottage cheese and
half of Swiss cheese.
Add more noodles and meat sauce and remaining tomato sauce.
Sprinkle Swiss cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: creamy au gratin potatoes
directions: In saucepan, cook onion until tender.
Add soup and cream cheese; stir constantly until smooth and hot.
In greased baking dish, layer with frozen hash browns and cream sauce.
Make sure you end in cream sauce.
Cover and bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: fresh apple bundt cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat on high speed sugar, orange juice, oil, vanilla and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder,
and salt; blending into orange juice mixture.
Fold in nuts.
In a separate bowl, combine apples, cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Pour half of dough mixture into a greased bundt pan; add half of apple mixture. Layer remaining ingredients in same order; ending with dough mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 55 to 60 minutes. Remove from pan after 5 minutes.
Cool on rack and glaze with your favorite glaze.

title: creamed eggs
directions: Hard boil eggs; peel.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add flour and seasonings.
Stir until well blended.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly. Cook until smooth.
Add coarsely chopped eggs.
Serve on buttered toast.

title: beef paprika with rice
directions: Sprinkle meat with paprika, salt and pepper.
In large skillet, cook beef and onions in oil over high heat for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring.
Remove meat; set aside.
Blend broth, wine and cornstarch.
Add to skillet.
Cook, stirring until clear and thickened.
Stir peppers and reserved meat into skillet.
Simmer for 5 minutes or until peppers are tender-crisp.
Serve over rice. Serves 6.

title: port fino
directions: Dissolve jello and cranberries in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold or 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill until set.

title: 10 bean soup
directions: Wash thoroughly beans and place in large kettle.
Cover with water and then add salt.
Soak overnight.
In the morning drain. Add water.
Add ham or
ham hocks.
Bring to a boil.
Stir occasionally.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Then add onion, tomatoes, pepper or chili powder, lemon juice and salt and pepper.
Simmer another 30 minutes.
Serves 12.
Better made a day or two ahead.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: *Substitution:
Use 1 can evaporated milk and use no water.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add crushed pineapple and blueberry filling; stir well.
Congeal in a shallow 9 x 12-inch pan.
When set, stir together the cream cheese, sour cream and sugar and spread over the Jell-O.
Top with chopped nuts.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Place butter or margarine in pan and saute chopped onion until golden.
Take off heat and add cream cheese (can use 1/2 Ricotta and 1/2 cream cheese if you want).
Put in pan with onion until melted.
Make spinach and strain.
Add to spinach bread crumbs and Italian cheese.
Pour cream cheese mixture into the spinach and mix well.
Put mixture in buttered casserole and fold in eggs.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: mom's pepper jelly
directions: Bring pepper, sugar and vinegar to a rolling boil.
Take off stove and let set 5 minutes.
Then stir in Certo, mixing well. Pour into glasses and seal.

title: veggie squares
directions: Bake crescent rolls at 325° for 7 to 10 minutes until golden brown; cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayo or salad dressing and dry dressing; spread on flat rolls.
Mix veggies; add Cheddar cheese to veggies.
Sprinkle on top of cheese mixture; chill. Cut
into 2 x 2 squares.

title: pink orzo with tomatoes
directions: In a Dutch oven casserole, saute orzo in oil, stirring all the while, until orzo is just beginning to take on color.
Carefully pour in (it will splatter) the chicken broth and seasonings. Cover pan and simmer mixture for 40 minutes, or until orzo is tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: butter cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy; add eggs, one at a time then add vanilla. In separate bowl, add dry ingredients and mix. Add buttermilk alternating with dry ingredient mixture to egg mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: toad-in-the-hole
directions: Heat skillet.
Butter 1 slice of favorite bread on both sides. Use the rim of a small juice glass to cut a hole in the middle of bread.
Put bread and "hole" in the skillet.
Break 1 egg and put it in the hole.
Add salt and pepper.
Turn bread when egg turns white, turn "hole" too.
Serve with "hole" as lid to cover "toad." Serve with orange or grape juice . Yields 1 serving.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all together as directed on box.
Then stir in 6 ounces chocolate tidbits.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in Bundt pan.
Remove from pan after cool.

title: 100 cookie recipe
directions: Cream sugars and margarine; add oil, egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add coconut and rolled oats.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt and add in parts to other mixture.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: brownies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar, then add eggs.
Slowly add cocoa.
Add flour, milk and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until light in color. Add nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.
Watch the last couple of minutes so the edges don't burn.

title: turkey stuffing pie
directions: Mix Stove Top as given on package.
Line sides and bottom of a 9-inch pie plate with stuffing. Flake turkey and place over stuffing mix. Add cheese. Beat eggs and milk and pour over turkey. Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Layer 1/3 of Fritos in bottom of round 2-quart casserole dish. Spread 1 can of chili over chips.
Add 1/2 of onions (optional) and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat procedure, starting with chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Put rest of chips on top.

title: blueberry jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add blueberry juice. Reserve 3/4 cup of this mixture and let set and thicken.
Place rest of jello in pans and add drained blueberries, pineapple and nuts.
Whip Cool Whip and reserved fluid and top.

title: baked kraut recipe
directions: Everything should be drained real good.
Fry bacon crisp. Drain on paper towel.
Saute chopped onion in bacon grease until light golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Drain 2 cans kraut and put in mixing bowl.
Drain whole tomatoes; cut up tomatoes before putting them in mixing bowl along with kraut, bacon and onion. Add brown sugar.
Mix all this together in the bowl so the sugar is mixed good, then put it in baking dish and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and bread cubes or potato chips.
Pile lightly into baking dish (3-quart).
Sprinkle cheese and bread cubes or potato chips on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add powdered sugar, almond extract and salt. Fold in nuts and dates.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on buttered tin. Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until delicate brown.

title: rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl, put milk, oil, warm water, sugar and salt.
Put yeast into the dry ingredients.
Mix well; roll out, cut with biscuit cutter and put in pans.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix in graham cracker crumbs and press into bottom of pan.
Sprinkle chips, nuts and coconut on top of crumbs.
Dribble can of sweetened condensed milk completely over the top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 23 minutes.

title: dinner chowder
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients in salted water until tender. Melt the oleo; add the flour and salt and stir well.
