Add 1 teaspoon of salt and milk.
Cook until thick and cheese is melted. Add potatoes.
Add Heinz 57 sauce and tomatoes after draining the juice.
Add 1/8 cup minced parsley.
Heat and serve.

title: strawberry pancakes
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Beat in buttermilk; add soda.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to egg mix, beating after each addition.
Stir in butter.
Fold in strawberries (mince in blender first).
Bake on buttered griddle until bubbles form but do not burst.
Turn.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together and then mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
If potatoes are grated ahead of time, put them in milk to avoid discoloration.
Drop pancake mix by large spoonfuls onto hot griddle.
Reduce heat. Brown on both sides and then remove to a warm dish.

title: mud slide pie
directions: Combine flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese and confectioners sugar until creamy.
Fold in 1 cup whipped topping; spread on top of crust.
Mix both packages of pudding mix with 2 cups milk.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining whipped topping.
Grate Hershey bar; sprinkle on top.

title: aunt mae's pizzelle
directions: You will need pizzelle iron.

title: instant orange-pineapple spiced tea
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Use 2 or 3 heaping teaspoons of mixture to 1 cup boiling water.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Blend mayo and mustard.
Toss gently with other ingredients. Cover and chill several hours.
Just before serving, add chow mein noodles.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese-olive balls
directions: Knead cheese and flour.
Add butter and knead again.
Take a teaspoon of dough and wrap around olive.
Freeze.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: cream cheese-capped carrot muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Generously grease or line 12 muffin cups with paper liners.
In large bowl, combine quick bread mix, water, oil, pineapple and egg; stir to moisten all ingredients.
Fill prepared muffin cups 3/4 full.
Place 1 mounded teaspoonfuls soft cream cheese on top of batter in each muffin cup.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in muffin comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: microwave candy bars
directions: Combine oats and margarine in microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave (High), uncovered, 3 to 4 minutes until heated through.
Stir in sugar and syrup until blended.
Microwave (High), uncovered, 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes, until heated and sugar is dissolved, stirring once.
Evenly press into lightly greased 8-inch square microwave-safe bowl; set aside.
Microwave chocolate bits in uncovered glass bowl, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes until soft, stirring once.
Stir until smooth.
Blend in peanut butter.
Spoon onto oat mixture.
Spreading evenly.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares or bars.

title: with and without brownies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add salt and eggs and mix well. Blend in syrup and flour.
Bake in greased and floured pan, 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 1/2-inch pan at 350° for 22 minutes.
Ice while brownies and icing are warm.

title: banana pudding
directions: In large bowl combine condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream. Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into serving bowl.
Top with wafers, bananas, and pudding.
Repeat layering, ending with pudding. Chill.
Add whipped cream and crushed vanilla wafers.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove stems from mushroom caps; set aside.
Place caps, stem-side up, on baking sheet.
Chop enough mushroom stems to measure 1/2 cup.
In medium bowl, combine chopped stems, ham, bread crumbs, bell pepper, garlic and dressing; mix well.
Spoon filling into mushroom caps, gently pressing filling into caps,
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until mushrooms are tender and filling is golden brown.
Yields 24 to 30 mushrooms.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix ingredients in skillet and cook until peanuts stop popping.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of soda and mix well.
Pour on buttered paper and cool.
Break into desired pieces.

title: eggless cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Add the sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add the warm water.
Alternate with flour, sifted with the baking powder.
Add the vanilla.
Bake at 325°.

title: sweet glazed meatballs
directions: Combine beef, 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce, breadcrumbs, egg, garlic, salt and pepper.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Add oil to skillet and swirl to cover bottom of pan.
Heat very hot.
Add meatballs, shaking pan to brown all sides.
Combine remaining Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, honey, pineapple juice, ginger and cornstarch; stir to blend.
Add to meatballs and heat, stirring, until sauce is bubbling, clear and thickened.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Brown chopped onion in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Soak bread in milk and stir to break up.
Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs, and put in large casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, sprinkle with bread crumbs that have been browned in 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lorraine's date-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, then dates.
Add dry ingredients.
(Two cups of Angel Flake coconut may be used in place of dates.)
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake!

title: corn chowder
directions: Dice and put salt pork in deep pan.
Cook slowly until fat is melted and pork bits are crisp and brown.
Add onion.
Cook slowly until light brown. Add potatoes and water.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add cream-style corn and milk.
Heat, then add butter, salt and pepper to taste.

title: peanut-chocolate squares
directions: Microwave 3/4 c. margarine and 2 ounces chocolate squares on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until melted, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir in crumbs, coconut and peanuts.
Press onto bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan baking pan.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: dill sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use to dip fresh vegetables.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Boil chicken; let cool and debone.
Cook broccoli; drain and cool.
Mix curry, soups and mayonnaise together.
Place broccoli in buttered casserole dish (oblong).
Break chicken in pieces and put on top; pour sauce over this.
Cover with cheese and bread crumbs or croutons.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: country ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Combine butter, mustard and poppy seed.
Slice buns in half and spread mustard mixture on both slices of bread.
Arrange ham and cheese in buns.
Wrap in foil.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until hot.

title: lazy day salad
directions: In a large container, drain fruit cocktail and oranges thoroughly. Mix instant (dry) puddings with the pineapple. Add this to the fruit. Stir in the Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: fresh apple squares
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil together until well blended.
Stir together dry ingredients and fold in apples.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: chocolate-peanut butter banana lollipops
directions: You also need ice cream sticks.

title: perfect boiled shrimp
directions: Fill a 5-quart pot half full of water; bring to a boil.
Add all ingredients, except shrimp, crab boil and salt; return to boil and add shrimp and crab boil.
Boil 5 minutes, then stir in salt to dissolve.
Cover.
Remove from heat and let set 30 minutes. Remove drained shrimp to a large bowl and cover with ice.
Serve right away or chilled.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Spread potatoes in bottom of 9x13 baking dish and allow to thaw completely (2-3 hours).
In a sauce pan, brown onions in 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Stir in the soups, milk, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Stir and heat until mixture reaches the first hint of a simmer.
Then pour over potatoes and mix well.
Mix corn flake crumbs with melted margarine and spread over potatoes.
Bake uncovered about 50 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12-15.
tags: frozen southern style hash brown potatoes

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Bone chicken and then add all ingredients to cooked spaghetti. Stir until cheese melts.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° until casserole bubbles.
Serve with garlic bread and green salad. Serves 8 to 10.

title: lunch box burritos
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add rest of ingredients, except tortillas and shredded cheese.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Have ready the tortillas and cheese.
Place each tortilla on a paper towel. Put about 1/4 cup meat mixture along side of tortilla.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of cheese.
Roll up.
Wrap in a paper towel and then wrap in foil.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: meat loaf for two
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cut 2 slices from onion; set aside, mince the rest.
Add with next 6 ingredients to crumbs; blend.
Shape into oval loaf on shallow pan.
Gash part way through center, spread with catsup.
Insert onion slices on top. Brush with salad oil.
Bake in moderately hot oven at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger gravy
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef until no longer pink; drain. Stir in the soup, milk, mushrooms and bouillon. Reduce heat. Simmer uncovered for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve over mashed potatoes. Makes 4 servings.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in oleo until soft (not brown), then mix everything together well in casserole.
Top with shredded cheese and bake until hot and cheese bubbles.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Combine and pour over meat and stir the cornstarch, sugar, ginger, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Clean, seed and cut into squares the peppers and onion.
Brown meat in hot oil.
Remove from pan.
Reduce heat; add peppers, onion, garlic and water. Cook to tender-crisp; stir in meat and reheat.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: beau monde dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and whip until smooth.
Pour into quart jar and refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: romanoff noodles
directions: Cook noodles in chicken broth.
When cooked, drain broth and while hot, add rest of ingredients.
Place in shallow baking dish. Cover with bread crumbs and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: florentine stuffed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a medium bowl, combine the spinach, Parmesan cheese and onion and mix thoroughly. Stuff the pocket of each chicken breast with 1/4 cup of mixture. Use a sharp knife to make pocket in side of breast. Lay stuffed breast in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and cover with sauce. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and tender. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake another 5 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: green with envy frozen pie
directions: Spoon vanilla ice cream and lime sherbet alternately into crust.
(Make layers with vanilla on top.)
Mix pistachio pudding, Cool Whip, pineapple with juice and coconut.
Put over ice cream layer.
Top with crushed pecans.
Garnish with lime.
Freeze and serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add flour to creamed mixture with bananas.
Fold in pecans.
Bake at 300° in loaf pan for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Cook fruit cocktail for 3 minutes.
Add drained pineapple and Jell-O.
Stir in cheese until smooth.
Let jell partly, then fold in whipped cream.
Chill.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions in oleo.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Put in oblong casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Slice all fruit and cut into small pieces.
Add coconut and raisins.
Put in all ingredients.
Sugar to taste.
Be careful not to get too sweet.

title: fried salmon things
directions: Drain the salmon, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Put meat into a mixing bowl, break apart well with a fork, then add the flour and slightly beaten egg.
Add pepper, if desired.
Mix well.
Add the baking powder to the reserved liquid; then beat well with fork until foamy.
Pour this into the salmon mixture, then stir until blended.
Using two teaspoons, scoop the mixture and drop into deep fryer.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove sausage from casings and cook until done.
Saute onion and garlic	in olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients and sausage. Pull
stems
from	mushrooms
and	stuff.	Bake
on lightly oiled pan at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: never fail peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk on medium heat until it reaches soft ball stage (use a candy thermometer).
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir and mix thoroughly; pour into buttered oblong cake pan.
Makes 4 1/2 pounds of fudge.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion until meat is brown and onion tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Add 1 to 3 cups water to desired consistency.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring sauce occasionally.
Serves 8.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar,
milk,
cocoa
and
stick of butter.
Put on heat and cook until boiling.
Cook 2 minutes, then remove from heat. Add
vanilla
and pinch of salt.
Add peanut butter and dry oats. Stir until mix begins to harden.
Drop by spoonfuls onto Saran Wrap.

title: dirt cake
directions: Make pudding according to directions on the box.
Add the cream cheese and whipped cream.
Crunch the cookies up in to little crumbs like dirt.
Layer the pudding and cookies one after another.
Refrigerate for 30-40 minutes or until cold.

title: beef, pork, hash
directions: Cut beef and pork roast in small chunks.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put in large pot. Cover with water and add garlic. Bring to a boil, then cook for 2 to 3 minutes or until meat will shred with a fork.
Remove from heat and shred meat and add onions.
Put pot back on heat and simmer uncovered for 1 to 2 hours. Then serve on rice or make sandwiches.
You may add barbecue sauce if you'd like. It will serve a "bunch".

title: fried mushrooms
directions: Clean
mushrooms and remove stems.
Beat egg with milk. Dip mushrooms
in
egg,
then
in flour and back in egg.
Mix Parmesan cheese,
crumbs
and garlic salt.
Roll mushrooms in crumbs and deep fry until brown.

title: no frosting zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Mix in order and pour into two loaf pans (greased).
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake for 60 minutes at 325°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: eggless lace cookies
directions: Stir together flour, sugar and baking powder. Add rest of ingredients and stir well. Drop from teaspoon about 4-inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until lightly browned, about 4 to 6 minutes.
Let stand a minute before removing to rack to cool.

title: cheese and wiener crescents
directions: Split wieners to within 1/2-inch of ends; insert 3 strips of cheese in each slit.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place a wiener at the broad end of each triangle and roll up.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, cheese side up.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill before serving.

title: polynesian chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, pineapple or grapes, carrots and almonds.
Blend mayonnaise with sour cream and other seasonings. Pour over chicken and toss lightly.
Chill thoroughly.
Arrange on salad greens and garnish with minced parsley.

title: marinated fish
directions: Mix 50-50 water and vinegar together.
Add onion, garlic and salt and pepper.
Add fish to marinade and leave for 1 hour. Remove from marinade and dry with paper towels.
Dredge in flour and cook in hot oil.

title: play dough
directions: Mix together.
Cook until stiff.
Color to desired color with food coloring.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix together and bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool and eat!

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Steam broccoli; place in casserole.
Add garlic salt.
Beat together milk and eggs; pour over broccoli.
Layer Velveeta, croutons and melted butter.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, then put in loaf pan lined with wax paper or spray pan.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: verba's oatmeal cake
directions: In small bowl, pour 1 1/4 cups boiling water over oats.
Add 1 stick butter.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes.
In another bowl, combine 1 cup sugar, brown sugar, eggs, flour, soda, salt and spices.
Stir and add oatmeal mixture.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: old marvin hotel coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage and onion.
Mix in other ingredients; put in airtight container and refrigerate.
This will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs until fluffy.
Beat in sifted dry ingredients and vanilla.
Fold in apples, walnuts and coconut. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: zucchini "apple" pie
directions: Toss together zucchini (cooked until tender-crisp and drained) with lemon juice and salt.
Mix in a bowl the sugar, cinnamon, cream of tartar, nutmeg and flour.
Add zucchini and mix well (it will be runny).
Put into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust and dot with butter.
Add top crust and bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lime pear jello salad
directions: Drain juice from pears. Boil juice and pour over lime jello. Stir until dissolved. Mash pears and mix with cream cheese and jello mixture. Fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in frying pan.
Place hamburger and onion in baking dish.
Add corn to make 2 layers.
Other vegetables can be added.
Take mashed potatoes; place on top of corn and hamburger.
Add cream of mushroom soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hoop cheese dumpling (vereneke)(makes approximately 60 dumplings and feeds approximately 15.)
directions: Grind cheese; add yolks and mix until stiff.
Season to taste.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Cook and drain egg noodles.
Add ingredients and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: salad dressing(mother's recipe)
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine all ingredients but the vinegar. Mix well and stir in the weak vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt cheese in milk and chicken soup.
Mix everything together and bake.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: divine potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in water until tender; peel and cut into chunks.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk; add Cool Whip.
Set aside.
Place a layer of crackers in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread half the pudding mixture over crackers.
Place another layer of crackers and cover with remaining pudding.
Layer crackers over this.
Set in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Spread chocolate frosting over crackers.
(Can use ready made.) Chill in refrigerator for 24 hours.
(Necessary to soften crackers.)

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together everything but ground beef thoroughly in large bowl.
Add to ground beef.
Shape into loaf or put in loaf pan. Spread ketchup over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: smoked cheese ball
directions: Allow the three cheeses to soften.
Mix well.
Add onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Roll into ball.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together and press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: In bowl, combine beans, soup, celery and milk.
Pour into greased 11 1/2 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs over mixture.
Cover and bake 10 minutes longer or until bread crumbs are brown.

title: spritzbakkelier cookies (butter)
directions: Cream butter and sugar gradually.
Add beaten eggs, then flour and flavoring.
Bake at 375° about 12 minutes or until edges are brown.

title: hermits
directions: Combine flour, soda, spices and salt.
Beat butter for 30 seconds; add brown sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating until well blended.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.

title: cranberry cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, 3/4 cup brown sugar and margarine.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture.
Press remainder firmly on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, Karo, margarine and pecans.
Pour into uncooked pie shell and cook in preheated oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apricot snowballs
directions: Grind apricots, coconut and pecans in food chopper.
Add orange juice.
Shape into small balls (size of walnuts).
Roll in granulated sugar.
Store to season in tightly covered container (about 2 weeks), but will keep for months.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil and vinegar in small bowl.
Mix sauerkraut, green pepper, celery and onion.
Pour oil mixture over sauerkraut mixture and toss.
Prepare this the night before.
Use next day; add small can pimento (drained and diced).
Can also be added night before.

title: cole slaw
directions: Process slaw in food processor for short spurts for fine slaw.
Add all other ingredients; stir well.
For best results, allow to set in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple and pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Smooth out.
Sprinkle cake mix (dry) evenly over fruit.
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Then sprinkle coconut and pecans on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve in pan.

title: rich's mom's coffee cake
directions: Pour 1/2 batter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (greased and floured). Pour 1/2 of brown sugar mixture on that, followed by the rest of the batter and then the remaining brown sugar mixture.

title: calamondin pie
directions: Mix calamondin juice with condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip. Put in graham cracker or chocolate crust.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Slice cucumbers very thin.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand for 2 hours.
Rinse in cold water and squeeze out the moisture. Mix rest of ingredients together and fold cucumbers into the sauce.
Chill before serving.

title: armenian grape-nuts custard
directions: Mix eggs, vanilla, milk and sugar together.
In bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, put a thin layer of Grape-Nuts.
Pour in the egg mixture and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.

title: spanish rice with beef
directions: Brown meat, breaking pieces and stirring, about 5 minutes. Add corn, water, tomatoes and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Stir in dry rice. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: bean and pea salad
directions: Drain the beans, corn and peas.
Add to chopped vegetables. Mix sugar, oil, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Boil and pour over vegetables.
Best if you let set overnight.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Melt in double boiler the cream cheese and mayonnaise, then add all other ingredients.
Serve hot or cold with vegetables or crackers.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Mix flour, whipping cream and cheese.
Drop by spoonful onto greased baking pan and bake at 300 degrees for about 20 minutes or until brown.
Mix garlic and melted margarine.
Baste hot biscuits with garlic mixture.

title: beer batter mix for shrimp
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add beer until a medium thin batter (a little thicker than pancake batter) and add sauce.
Enough for 2 1/2 pounds shrimp.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar and set aside.
Dissolve Jell-O and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Chill until thickened, then fold in cranberries, orange and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: turkey and pepper wedges(good way to use leftover turkey.)
directions: In a small bowl stir together biscuit mix, egg and oil just until blended.
Shape into a ball.
On a lightly floured surface, knead a few times until smooth.
Roll into a 12-inch circle and place on a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with half of the turkey, sweet peppers, tomatoes and onion.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles for 5 minutes; beat eggs, sour cream, sugar, cream cheese and melted butter together.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into greased Pyrex.
Cover with topping.
Crunch cornflakes, 1/2 c. chopped walnuts (crunched) and cinnamon. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, salt, pepper, rice and onion. Form into meatballs. Heat oil in skillet.
Brown meatballs. Add tomato puree, water, green pepper and sugar. Stir well. Cover and simmer 40 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: sausage bell peppers
directions: Brown Italian sausage; drain grease.
Add bell pepper, garlic powder, pepper, Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Cover and simmer until bell peppers are tender.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° if using glass pie plate).
In a large mixing bowl, cream together butter, brown sugar, white sugar, vanilla and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add flour, chocolate chips and 1 cup pecans and mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle 2 tablespoons pecans in a circle on top.
Bake one hour or until an inserted toothpick comes out clean, about 50 minutes at lower temperature and check before letting it bake longer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Combine flour, sugar, egg, vinegar and pineapple in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened.
Cool.
Fold in whipped topping, apples and peanuts.
Chill overnight.

title: tenia's punch
directions: Mix together in large punch bowl or put a little of each in smaller bowl.
Stir to melt some ice cream.

title: chicken stew for forty people
directions: Cook chicken with red pepper and sage; let cool.
Pick chicken off bones, making sure to remove all bones, fat, gristle and cartilage.
Break into bite size pieces and place back into broth. Bring to a slow boil.
Add 1 gallon of milk while stirring.
Bring back to a slow boil.
Mix 1 quart of milk with the flour.
Mix well and add to broth while stirring.
Salt and pepper to taste.
After each stirring, skim particles that come to the top of the broth and discard.
Do this several times.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Prepare orange pieces and drain pineapple.
Set aside. Dissolve the jello in boiling water.
Add sherbet and stir until dissolved.
Fold in the Cool Whip and mix well.
Add the pineapple and orange pieces.
Mix well and pour into a glass dish or mold and chill until firm.

title: no bake coconut pecan chews
directions: Lightly butter cookie sheet.
Mix frosting mix (dry), margarine and milk in 2-quart saucepan until moistened.
Heat to boiling over high heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to medium.
Simmer 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
(Do not overcook.)
Remove from heat.
Stir in oats.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Refrigerate.
Uncover about 30 minutes or until cool.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.
tags: Betty Crocker coconut pecan frosting mix

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cabbage and kielbasa casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pour the boiling water over the cabbage and set aside for 10 minutes to wilt.
Drain the cabbage and stir in the flour, eggs, milk, fennel seed, salt and pepper.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Pour in the cabbage mixture and press onto the sides and bottom of the plate to form a crust.

title: fresh tomato pie
directions: Butter a 9-inch pie plate and cover with all but a small amount of crumbs.
Fill with alternating layers of tomatoes, onions and cheese.
Combine seasoning and eggs and pour over layers.
Top with remaining crumbs and arrange bacon slices on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crisp.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pistachio pudding and Cool Whip in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve.
Refrigerate remaining salad.

title: gingerbread
directions: In a mixing bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs to creamed mixture.
Stir in molasses.
Alternate, adding dry ingredients and milk.
Pour in 13-inch baking pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Chop fine and combine onions, celery, peppers and pimientos. Add kraut; drain well but do not rinse.
Combine well sugar, oil and vinegar.
Pour over mixture and chill well.

title: coleslaw
directions: In large bowl, stir together first four ingredients until smooth (mayonnaise, lemon juice, sugar and salt).
Add cabbage, green pepper and onion; toss to coat well.
Cover; chill.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: tangy carrots
directions: Peel and trim carrots.
Cut them lengthwise, then in half. Place carrots and shallot in vegetable steamer.
Cover and steam 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Set aside.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Slice potatoes 1/2-inch thick and boil 15 minutes.
Turn oven to 350°.
Mix 1 pound hamburger meat with salt and pepper.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix the food coloring and Nestle Quik together and set aside. Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Beat in the eggs. Add the coloring paste and beat a long time, until smooth.
Combine the flour, salt and soda and sift 3 times.
Mix the buttermilk with the vanilla. Alternate with flour and add to the first mixture.
Add the vinegar and mix by hand.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: deer jerky with strips of meat
directions: Put contents in 1/2 gallon jar with lid.
Keep in refrigerator 15 hours, turning jar frequently.
Drain, then lay meat on paper towels and pat.
Put in dehydrator until leathery but not brittle.

title: maucia's cheese wafers
directions: Cut flour and butter together until it resembles coarse meal. Mix in cheese, pepper and salt.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Shape into wafers; bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: breakfast biscuits
directions: Spray 12 muffin cups with Pam or line with foil baking cups and spray with Pam. Separate dough into 10 biscuits. Place 1 biscuit in each sprayed cup; firmly press in bottom and up sides. Heat large nonstick skillet; spray with Pam or use oleo. Add eggs; cook until almost set, stirring occasionally. Stir in sausage pieces. Divide egg mixture evenly into dough-lined cups. Top each with 1 tablespoon cheese. Bake at 350° for 11 to 13 minutes or until edges are lightly brown.

title: sour cream peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, shortening, vanilla and egg; beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until thoroughly mixed.
Stir in 1 cup peanut butter chips.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake to light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Heat juice from pineapple and cherries.
Dissolve Jell-O in juices.
Add chopped cherries, pineapple, Cokes and pecans.
Chill for several hours until firm.
Unmold or serve from bowl.

title: smoked oyster roll
directions: On waxed paper or parchment, press cream cheese flat.
Place oysters on top and roll jelly roll fashion, starting from long side.
Roll in pecan bits to cover.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and form into a loaf.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over loaf.
Baste from time to time.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: bingen goulash
directions: Cube and brown meat in oil.
Chop and saute onion in butter using the same pan.
Add flour; stir, add broth and sauce plus 1 can of water.
Stir in sauerkraut, beef and spices.
Simmer 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Serve with dumplings.

title: chocolate chip cupcakes
directions: In a bowl, mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and chocolate chips.
In a 1-cup measuring cup, place oil, eggs and vanilla. Add enough milk to finish filling up the cup.
Add this to dry ingredients.
Pour into muffin pans.
(Sometimes I make them in mini muffin pans and I use mini chips.)
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Grease 12-inch pizza pan.
Cook and stir sausage and potatoes until sausage is fully cooked; drain.
Mix Bisquick and hot water to make dough.
Press dough onto pizza pan.
Spread sausage mixture over it.
Top with cheeses.
Bake about 12 minutes until cheese bubbles.

title: apple squares
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, 1/2 cup white sugar and cinnamon; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in walnuts. Reserve 2 cups crumb mixture; press remaining mixture into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine cream cheese and milk until well blended. Add 1/4 cup sugar, egg and vanilla; mix well. Pour over crust. Top with apples; sprinkle with crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool. Chill. Cut into squares. Store in refrigerator.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let sit 5 to 10 minutes. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Combine cake mix, walnuts and coconut in a bowl, mixing well. Layer pie fillings, then pineapple, then coconut, walnuts and cake mix in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: very berry banana smoothie
directions: Slice bananas into 1-inch chunks.
Put into a Ziploc bag with strawberries and blueberries.
Seal bag and freeze for three hours.

title: italian bread sticks
directions: Put flour, salt and sugar in bowl.
Cut in butter as you would for pie dough.
Add water and yeast.
Knead well.
Let rise about 45 minutes.
Punch down and divide dough into 4 parts.
Roll each part to about 12-inches.
Cut into 12 or 14 pieces.
Roll each piece as thin as a lead pencil.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Let rise about 20 minutes to 1/2 hour.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, add 1-inch of boiling water.
Cook broccoli 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain; set aside.

title: cherry blossoms
directions: Place 1 vanilla wafer in the bottom of 18 baking cups and place in muffin tins.

title: chili dogs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Make 3 (1/2-inch) deep cuts into each frankfurter on a diagonal.
Cut cheese slice into 36 strips , about 1 x 1/4-inch.
Insert cheese into each cut.
In an ungreased baking dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch) mix beans, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Arrange frankfurters on bean mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: fried squash fritters
directions: Wash and cut ends off of 2 or 3 yellow squash and slice.
Put in boiler, add salt, pepper and water and cook until tender. Drain and mash like mash potatoes.
Add onion, egg and enough flour to mixture, so it will be firm enough to spoon by spoonfuls into hot oil and fry until golden brown.
Makes enough for approximately 3 people.

title: raw apple cake with sauce
directions: Cream butter with white sugar; add eggs.
Add sifted flour, soda, salt, coffee and vanilla.
Fold in raw apples.
Put in angel food cake pan.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts together and sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: bacon poles
directions: Wrap bacon slices around large bread sticks (dry).
Roll in cheese.
Microwave on High for 1 minute for each pole.
Let cool until crunchy.

title: crawfish gumbo
directions: Heat shortening.
Add flour and make roux, stirring until brown.
Add onions, celery and bell pepper.
Stir until vegetables are soft or wilted.
Add fat from heads of crawfish; stir until fat comes to top.
Add water and seasonings; simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Chopped parsley and onion tops may be added.
Serve with rice.

title: alice's barbecue sauce
directions: Bring water to a boil in a nonstick pan.
Add onion and garlic, cooking until tender and water has evaporated.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour into clean, hot preserve jar; seal and store in refrigerator.

title: crock-pot meal
directions: Cook in crock-pot for 40 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Cut chicken into strips, place in a large pot; add onions, soup, sour cream and one soup can of water, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil, cooking until chicken is done.
Add cheese and cook until melted.
Spoon into tortillas shells and fold up. Using left over mix you can spoon it onto the top of your shells.

title: country fried steak
directions: Place steaks in shallow pan and cover with Italian dressing. Marinate for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Put enough flour in a bowl so the steaks can be dipped easily.
In a large frying pan, pour in cooking oil and cook steaks slowly, turning and cooking until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook noodles as directed; drain. Spray 3-quart casserole dish with Pam. Heat milk, butter and flour on stove top. Stir continuously. In dish, 1/2 cooked noodles, 2 cups cheese, other 1/2 noodles and 2 cups cheese. Pour milk mixture over top. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine ingredients in greased baking dish.
Top with bread cubes that have been moistened with melted butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Remove and discard skin from chicken.
Cook chicken in 6 cups of water until tender; remove chicken, reserving broth.
Debone and cut chicken into small pieces; set aside.
Cook rice in 2 cups chicken broth according to package directions; set aside.
Saute onion, celery and pimientos in margarine until tender.
Mix together all ingredients, except chicken.
Butter a casserole dish.
Place chicken in dish and place mixed ingredients over chicken.
Cover with broth and bake at 325° until bubbly hot.

title: marshmallow banana pudding
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water for 5 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Cool, stirring occasionally, until congealing starts.
Add egg whites; beat until very light. Add bananas; stir lightly.
Chill until set.
Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: harvest cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar; let stand 1 hour.
Stir together flour, soda and spices.
Beat eggs; add oil and vanilla.
Add apple mixture.
Combine mixture with eggs; stir in walnuts.
Bake in greased and floured angel food cake pan in 350° oven for 1 hour. Frost with plain white icing and top with sprinkled walnuts.

title: cheesecake brownies
directions: Mix brownie mix as directed on package.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla in a small bowl until blended.
Add nuts to brownie mix; grease and flour pan. Put 1/2 brownie mix in pan. Add cream cheese mixture; then add remaining brownie mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields 36 brownies.

title: impossible seafood pie
directions: Mix and place in greased pie pan.
Top with 1/4 cup shredded Cheddar.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: kool-aid playdough
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and then add oil and 2 cups boiling water.
Knead well.
Cool.
Store in Tupperware or in a sealed bag so it doesn't dry out.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 2 pie shells.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: cottage pudding
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour and milk alternately to shortening mixture, beating until smooth after each addition.
Add raspberries and mix with a wooden spoon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pina colada pudding
directions: Stir together pudding mix, milk and dessert topping mix in a small mixing bowl.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed about 30 seconds or until moistened.
Beat on high speed about 2 minutes more until thickened.
Fold in undrained pineapple.
Spoon pudding mixture into 6 dessert dishes.
Sprinkle each serving with toasted coconut.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk exactly 3 minutes (no longer).
Remove from heat and add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well and pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: pecan pie muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl with a wooden spoon.
Pour into a greased mini-muffin pan.
Fill each cup 2/3 full.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Garnish each muffin with a pecan half.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix all ingredients; spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Add beans and soup together in a greased bowl and top with onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
It is delicious with raw vegetables.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cool and peel the jackets off the beets.
Combine the vinegar, water, sugar and salt.
Cook to boiling.
Put beets in jars and pour hot syrup over them.
Process about 15 minutes in hot water bath.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all filling ingredients together.
Divide evenly and spread over tortillas.
Roll up tortillas.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap twisting ends.
Refrigerate for several hours. Unwrap; cut in slices (1/2 to 3/4-inch).
Discard ends.
Lay pinwheels flat on glass serving plate.
Serve with salsa.
Makes about 50 pinwheels.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Then mix all other ingredients and serve.

title: fruit cup
directions: Mix all fruit in a large bowl.
Spoon into small Dixie cups. Cut squares of foil to fit tops.
Place over fruit filled cups. Place in freezer.
Take out as you would like.
Best when kind of slushy.
Great for summer cooler offer.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer ingredients in the order given.
Spread mayonnaise on top.
Sprinkle sugar over all.
Let set 8 to 10 hours.
Toss and serve.

title: apricot cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar well; add eggs. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Pour into 10-inch tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Toss lightly and place on casserole.
Spread cheese and potato chips on top.
Bake uncovered about 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and bacon.
Add remaining ingredients, except Parmesan cheese.
Place in greased casserole and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mccall's south carolina seafood gumbo
directions: Heat oil in stockpot over medium heat. Add onion; saut until translucent. Whisk in flour and cook 2 minutes. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, celery and okra. Add chicken legs; cook 30 minutes over medium heat. Remove chicken and cool. Add whitefish, meat from chicken legs and shrimp. Cook 15 minutes. Stir in cooked rice. Let stand 5 minutes, covered. Tabasco as desired. Serves 10 to 12.

title: jimmy cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo or oil.
Add egg yolks and vanilla and mix well.
Add flour and baking powder alternating it with coffee or milk.
Mix in the jimmies.
Lastly, fold in the beaten egg whites.
Pour into a greased and floured spring-form (with tube attachment) or angel food pan.
Can also use two 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes and at 350° for 10 minutes.
If you use layer pans, bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Check with toothpick.
Frost with any chocolate icing.

title: cough syrup
directions: Add boiling water to rest of ingredients.
Mix and take by spoon.

title: teenie weenies
directions: In a saucepan or fondue pot, heat jelly and chili sauce until well blended.
Add meat and heat thoroughly.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place layers in a clear glass bowl.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and crumbled bacon.
Chill.

title: sugarless drop cookies
directions: Soften white raisins in hot water and drain.
Spread oats on cookie sheet and brown 5 to 8 minutes in oven at 375°.
Drain can of dietetic crushed pineapple.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Blend shortening with flour mixture . Add beaten egg, sweetener and vanilla.
Add pineapple, raisins, chopped nuts and oat mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: lemonade pies
directions: Stir cool whip and sweetened condensed milk together until blended, add lemonade and beat until smooth.
Add some lemon juice if you want the pies tart.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust and put in refrigerator for at least 2 hours before serving.
Better if overnight.

title: cesky cerny chleb(old world black bread)
directions: Combine rye flour and all-purpose flour in a large bowl; reserve 3 cups flour mixture.
Sprinkle yeast over 1/2 cup warm water; stir until dissolved.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, stir together reserved 3 cups of flour mixture, cocoa, sugar, caraway seed, salt and instant coffee.
Combine 2 cups water, vinegar, dark corn syrup and butter or margarine in a medium saucepan.
Heat over low heat just until warm.
(Butter or margarine does not need to be completely melted.)
Add to cocoa mixture and blend well; add dissolved yeast and stir until thoroughly combined.
Stir in enough additional flour mixture, 1 cup at a time, until dough no longer clings to side of bowl.
Turn onto a lightly floured board; cover and let rest for 10 minutes.

title: speedy roll dough
directions: Combine water, sugar and yeast (with water).
Stir until thoroughly dissolved.
Add 2 cups flour.
Beat 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Add eggs, Crisco and salt.
Beat 1 more minute. Add rest of flour and knead well.
Let mixture stand 20 minutes. Make into desired rolls and let stand about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° until nicely browned.
These never fail.

title: berry cream strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie crust and cool.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually add sugar and almond extract.
Whip the whipping cream and fold into cream cheese mixture.
Spoon into cooled pie shell. Chill mixture 2 hours.
Slice 2 cups strawberries and arrange on top of pie.
Drizzle with hot fudge topping and serve.

title: breakfast bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream honey, brown sugar, egg whites and vanilla.
Set aside.

title: deviled eggs(easy, beginners)
directions: Place eggs in pot of salted water.
Bring to a boil and let eggs cook in boiling water 10-15 minutes.
Drain water and cool.

title: almond honey rugelach
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until fluffy. Add 3 tbsp. honey and mix well. Mix in flour until dough holds together. Form into a ball, wrap and refrigerate 2 hours or longer.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and cook in salt water until tender. Drain. Place a layer of potatoes in a greased casserole dish. Add half of the onions and half of the celery.
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream together and pour half of the mixture over, alternating with another layer. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with cheese.
Place back in oven for about 10 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Roll into balls.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: night before chicken(prepare the night before serving)
directions: Mix soup, milk and rice.
Pour half on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place 8 pieces of chicken breast on top, then pour rest of soup, milk and rice on top of that.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over top. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 2 hours.
Do not peek!
Some prefer to cook an additional 30 minutes.

title: swedish spicy meat balls
directions: Roll first 4 ingredients into small balls.
Brown in skillet and drain grease.
In kettle, add chili sauce and jelly.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: 44 calories per cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill well before serving.
Keeps well up to a week, refrigerated.

title: creamy salad
directions: Heat crushed pineapple until it boils, stirring constantly. Add jello and let stand until it thickens.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill and serve.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Mix together.
Spread in pie plate.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325 for 35 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: danish apple horns
directions: Melt butter and Spry; add sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Mix in egg, salt and yeast, dissolved in milk.
Beat in flour.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Let rise.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Roll each into a 9-inch circle.
Spread with melted butter; sprinkle with apples and dates.
Cut into 8 pie shaped pieces.
Beginning at rounded edge, roll up.
Place on baking sheet point down.
Let rise about 2 1/2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost.

title: grandma janie's bread pudding
directions: Toast the bread until slightly hardened, cube and set aside.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook together onion, green pepper and margarine until tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole dish for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: orange julius(makes 3 cups)
directions: Mix in blender until smooth, about 30 seconds.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Pour melted oleo in baking dish.
Spread rice on top of oleo. Lay chicken on top of rice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake 45 minutes to an hour at 375°.
Pork chops are also good.

title: cranberry sorbet
directions: Will also need holly leaves for garnish.

title: english scones
directions: Mix like you would for biscuits.
Add butter to flour which has been sifted with baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter until it looks like biscuits.
Add eggs or egg and milk.
Stir until it goes together and leaves sides of bowl.
Roll out on floured board into a circle; cut into wedges (fairly thick wedges).
Bake at 375° to 400° until just done.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, flour and vanilla. Add food coloring for Christmas cookies.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: roode kaol(red cabbage; from gramma buma's holland cookbook)
directions: Chop cabbage very fine.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add just enough water to prevent sticking, about 1/2 cup.
Cook until the water is all gone, about one-half hour.
Remove cloves and peppercorns.
Add butter and serve.

title: peanut butter brownie cups
directions: Mix brownie batter according to directions on box.
Fill baking cups 2/3 full.
Put peanut butter cup in center of each brownie and press down until batter meets top edge of candy.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield: 1 1/2 dozen.

title: party potatoes
directions: Partially thaw hash browns.
Place in a large bowl.
Add sour cream, milk and onions.
Salt and pepper liberally.
Shred cheese.
Mix in with potato mixture, reserving about 1/2 cup to sprinkle on top.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated for a day or two.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.
Great reheated or can be frozen after baked.

title: chicken or veal cutlets
directions: Mix bread crumbs, cheese, basil, salt and pepper.
Roll cutlets in crumb mixture.
Dip in egg, then in bread crumbs.

title: cream cheese corn
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese in a baking dish.
Add corn. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake in three 9-inch pans for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: stir-fry pork and pineapple
directions: Cut pork in slices; set aside.
Cut pineapple (drain; save juice).
In bowl, combine orange juice, soy sauce, honey, bouillon, garlic, pepper and reserved pineapple juice.
In wok, stir-fry pork and pepper squares in hot oil for about 2 to 3 minutes, or until meat is browned.
Remove.
Pour juice mixture into wok.
Add pineapple.
Cover and cook 2 minutes.
Remove and put on platter.
Return pepper and pork to wok; stir together cornstarch and water.
Add to wok.
Cook and stir until bubbly. Spoon on pineapple spears.

title: eggnog
directions: Cook
over
medium
heat in a double boiler.
Stir constantly to	keep
from
lumping.
Gradually
add beaten eggs. Stir	in nutmeg, vanilla and salt.
Mix cornstarch in a little milk,
add to	eggnog.
Cook
stirring
until smooth.	If not thick enough, add more cornstarch.
Remove from heat and cool. Chill and serve.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix soups, onion, cheese and sour cream.
Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture over top.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Bake longer if more than 1 pan is in the oven.
Put 1 can French fried onions on the top (if desired) the last few minutes of baking.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs.
Add milk alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into greased shallow pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: tortilla pizza
directions: Brush tortillas with olive oil on both sides, especially the edges. Saute hamburger, mushrooms, garlic, green chili sauce and salt together. Spread mixture on tortillas. Top with onion, green pepper, olives and cheese. Bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes, or until desired crispness.

title: lemon tea muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In large bowl, beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks; beat until light.
Gradually stir in lemon juice alternately with dry ingredients (do not overmix).
In small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold 1/3 egg whites into batter; fold in remaining egg whites.
Fill paper lined muffin cups 3/4 full.
In another bowl, combine nuts, brown sugar and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over muffins evenly.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Makes about 18 muffins.

title: butterscotch spice roll
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Grease pan.
Place eggs and salt in bowl over hot water.
Beat until the eggs are thick and lemon colored.
Beat sugar in gradually.
Remove from the heat. Stir flour before measuring.
Resift with baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Fold in the sifted ingredients and vanilla.
Bake the batter for about 13 minutes.
When removed from the oven, loosen the edges.
Reverse the pan onto a clean towel that has been dusted with confectioners sugar.
Roll the cake while still hot, with the towel and place on a rack to cool.

title: spanish tomato rice
directions: Cut tomatoes in half.
Brush cut surfaces with diet Italian dressing.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and basil.
Place cut side up on foil or greased grill over hot coals about 10 minutes or until hot through.
Do not turn.

title: green chive dip
directions: In blender or food processor, combine cream cheese, yogurt, garlic, chives, parsley and pepper to taste.
Process until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours to let flavors blend.
Yield:
1 cup.

title: easy tropical smokie link appetizers
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: colonial gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Beat all ingredients in large bowl at low speed until blended. Increase speed to medium and beat for 3 minutes.
Pour batter into pan and bake 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: hot cheese
directions: Grind together peppers, cheese and onions. Salt to taste. Add mayonnaise. Let stand overnight and serve with crackers or Melba toast. BE SURE TO REMOVE PEPPER SEEDS.

title: irish creme liqueur
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Refrigerate in tightly covered container.
Shake well; serve cold.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 pints.

title: crab delights
directions: Mix ingredients (except biscuits) until spreading consistency. Bake biscuits lightly; cool.
Slice in half.
Spread mixture on biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: All vegetables should be finely chopped.
Press crescent rolls in pizza pan to form crust.
Bake as directed on can until golden brown.
Mix cream cheese, garlic and paprika and spread on cooled crust.
Top with finely chopped vegetables.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Cut and serve.

title: gumbo burgers
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and green pepper.
Drain hamburger and add mustard, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Mix and add undiluted soup.
Simmer slowly, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes. Serve on buns.

title: reese cup cookies
directions: Cut roll of dough into 1/4 inch slices.
Put each slice into tart pan lined with mini muffin cups.

title: sausage, onion, peppers and potatoes
directions: In a large roasting pan, mix the following:
sausages (cut up to bite size), onion (sliced into strips), peppers (cut into strips), potatoes (cut bite size) and Italian seasoning.
Bake at 400° until potatoes are cooked.
Stir 1/2 through cooking time.

title: chicken casserole #3
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour rice in pan.
Place chicken over rice.
Sprinkle soup mix over chicken.
Mix soup and water together; pour over chicken breasts and soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake 90 minutes at 350°.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Sift together flour, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Melt butter. Remove from heat. Stir in sugar. Add eggs and vanilla and stir. Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture. Spread in pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cut in bars while warm.

title: zucchini and smoked sausage
directions: Overlap half of squash slices in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with half of celery, onion, green pepper, tomatoes, sausage and seasonings.
Repeat layers.
Place strips of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: beef turnovers
directions: About 25 minutes before serving:
Preheat broiler per manufacturer's directions.
In medium bowl, mix all ingredients except mustard and fillings.
On waxed paper, pat 1/4 of meat mixture into a 6-inch circle; spread 1/2 teaspoon of mustard on half of the circle.
Spread 1/2 tablespoon of desired filling over mustard.
Fold plain meat side over filling, crimping edge with a fork.
Repeat with remaining meat and filling.
Place turnovers on rack in broiling pan; broil 8 minutes or until browned, turning once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dilly biscuits
directions: Cream together and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 24.

title: crunchy salad
directions: Saute noodles in vegetable oil until lightly brown (don't burn).
Bake almonds and sesame seed at 350° about 5 minutes. Combine lettuce, onions, noodles, almonds and sesame seed.
Mix thoroughly the oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper and pour over salad when ready to serve.

title: marshmallow frosting
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugar and water.
Bring to a boil until sugar is melted.
In medium bowl, beat 2 egg whites and salt until foamy.
Fold in sugar mixture.
Then add cream of tartar and beat until soft peaks form when beater is lifted upright.
Then add vanilla and corn syrup.
Beat for 1 more minute.
Makes enough for 2 layer cakes.

title: five bean casserole
directions: Drain beans, except for the pork and beans.
Saute onion, celery and sausage meat.
Add all remaining ingredients, except the bacon.
Stir together and pour into casserole dish.
Put bacon strips on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scallop stir-fry(for two)
directions: Thaw scallops, if frozen.
Cut large scallops in half; set aside.
For sauce, stir together water, lemon juice, cornstarch, sugar, bouillon granules, black pepper and crushed red pepper. Set aside.

title: hamburg potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and then sprinkle cornflakes on top.
Bake 45 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: italian barbecue
directions: Remove sausage from casings.
Break sausage and minute steaks into pieces and cook until done.
Drain.
In separate pan cook peppers and onion until tender.
Add onion and peppers to meat mixture and add drained mushrooms, tomato puree, Italian dressing mix and cheese.
Mix and simmer 1 hour.
Good for crock-pot.

title: bev's chicken italiano
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish in 350° oven.
Wash chicken. Dip in beaten egg until well coated.
Mix bread crumbs, garlic powder, Italian seasoning and pepper; roll chicken in mixture until well coated.
Place in baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce over the chicken; sprinkle with onions and green peppers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with cheese.
Continue baking for 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs real good.
Add Crisco oil, vanilla, crushed pineapple (undrained) and bananas; mix well.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients; do not beat.
Mix just enough to wet dry ingredients.
Makes 3 (9-inch) layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy; add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and vanilla.
Stir in cherries, coconut and nuts.
Grease a tube pan and line bottom with brown paper.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours and 15 minutes.

title: margaret's oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together first 6 ingredients. Combine remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Stir.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes.

title: black forest torte
directions: Mix together cookies and margarine and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 1/2 cup.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar and add 8 ounces whipped topping.
Put on crust.
Top that with pie filling and then 8 ounces whipped topping.
Cover with reserved crumbs.

title: shrimp or crayfish fettucine
directions: Melt margarine and cook down onion, bell pepper and garlic (about 15 minutes).
Add half and half and both kinds of cheese until completely melted.
Add shrimp or crayfish and cook until they turn pink.
Add cooked fettucine and mix completely.
Pour into pan or baking dish.
Sprinkle barbecue seasoning over entire top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: a pirate's party for boys
directions: Notes:
Design
your
own
"treasure
map" invitations, include the party information on the map.
Roll the map up and tie with a piece of yarn;
better yet, put the map in an empty bottle and hand deliver!
A favorite activity of pirates is a treasure hunt
to find hidden party favors, such as gold coin chocolate candies!
Make
sure
you
supply your pirates with their very own black eye patch.

title: favorite layer bars
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press onto bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: orange roughy with creamy mushroom sauce
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add the next 3 ingredients; saute for 3 minutes.
Set aside and cool.
Combine mushroom mixture, cheese and yogurt in a bowl; stir well.
Place fillets in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with mushroom mixture; sprinkle with breadcrumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes, or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Garnish with paprika and parsley, if desired.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk together.
Melt butter and pour in baking dish.
Pour sugar, milk and flour mixture over melted butter.
Pour peaches over mixture and bake at 325° until brown.

title: wine cooler
directions: Thaw all of the concentrates.
In a small airtight container mix all together.
Cover; chill up to 2 weeks.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix gelatin and water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Heat pineapple, lemon juice and sugar in a saucepan until sugar dissolves.
Stir in gelatin while pineapple mixture is still hot.
Pour mixture in a 9 x 9-inch dish and put in freezer until the mixture starts to harden around the corners.
If it sets up too much, salad will be lumpy.
Add whipped cream and grated cheese.
Stir everything together and then smooth the surface with a spatula.
The salad will congeal into a firm, creamy dish.
Cut and serve.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into chunks; set aside.
Saute onion in margarine until tender, not brown.
Stir in flour; blend in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add potatoes.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.

title: t.g.i.f.  casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and onions.
Spray casserole dish with Pam. Layer dish with tortillas, then meat and onions, then beans, then grated cheese.
Mix tomatoes and soup together; pour over top. Add tortillas for top crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot dog topping
directions: Shred 1/2 head cabbage.
Next place mayonnaise in a bowl.
Add just enough milk to thin (not too thin).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add mixture to cabbage.
(This is your slaw.)

title: cracker jack syrup for popcorn
directions: Mix all ingredients in large kettle.
Boil to hard stage (a little syrup dropped in cup of cold water becomes a hard ball). When done, pour about 4 quarts of popped corn into syrup mixture and stir over fire until all popcorn is coated.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: four-cup ambrosia
directions: Mix together in medium bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Butter bread slices, then cut into cubes and line a greased casserole dish.
Cover bread with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut sirloin in thin strips.
Heat oil in large skillet. Dredge sirloin in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
To heated oil, add garlic, then sirloin. When steak is lightly browned, add onion and mushrooms. Saute approximately 5 minutes. Add beef broth.
Lower heat to simmer. Cover and cook for 1 hour. Remove cover and add sour cream. Heat through. Serve over noodles. Serves 4.

title: vegetable chowder(low-fat)
directions: In large pan, saute onion, pepper and garlic.
Add broth, potatoes and dill.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes until tender.
Use back of spoon to mash (some) about half of the potatoes; add drained beans to potatoes.
In separate bowl, mix sour cream (or yogurt), flour, pepper and salt.
Stir into potato mixture; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly, about 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with salad and hard bread.
Contains 280 calories per serving.

title: granola baked apples
directions: Core apples.
Cut out center of apples to leave 1/2-inch shell.
Chop 1/2 cup apple from the center and reserve.
Cut a strip of peel 1/2-inch wide around top of apple.
In medium bowl, mix granola, reserved 1/2 cup chopped apple and brown sugar.
Fill scooped out apple.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Add 1/4-inch water.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes, or until apples are tender.
Serve with sour cream, if desired.

title: quick lemon or lime pie
directions: Whip Dream Whip according to package directions.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar with milk until smooth.
Mix together with whipped Dream Whip.
Add frozen juice to mixture.
Pour in 2 pie shells.
Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, syrup and sugar.
Microwave in a glass bowl until sugar dissolves (3 or 4 minutes).
Cool.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Pour filling into unbaked pie shell.
Top with pecans. Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Combine all ingredients except grated cheeses.
Line greased 9 x 13-inch pan with noodles.
Top with half of seafood mixture. Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove; top with grated cheeses and bake for 45 minutes longer.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: mary's never-fail meringue
directions: In a saucepan, combine water, sugar and cornstarch.
Heat, stirring, until thick and clear.
Cool slightly.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, if you like it.
In a large bowl, whip egg whites with a pinch of salt until droopy peaks form.
Continue whipping as you slowly pour in the sugar-water mixture.
Whip until peaks will stand up straight.
Spread over warm filling, pushing the meringue against the crust.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 7 minutes or until nicely browned.
Cool on rack out of the way of drafts and do not refrigerate until completely cooled.

title: cream style casserole
directions: Fry hamburger, onion and celery until done.
Drain all grease out.
Stir into corn that has been poured into a casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Eat while hot.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning with refried beans. Spread in bottom of square glass pan. Add in order: onion dip, sour cream, ripe olives, tomatoes, green chiles and Monterey Jack cheese. Use large Fritos to dip.

title: shrimp puffs
directions: Trim crusts from white bread; cut into quarters.
Place on cookie sheet; top with shrimp.
Top shrimp with mixture of grated cheese and mayonnaise.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: light buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine beaten eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Bake on moderately hot griddle.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients with 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Fill pie crust with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Put cheese on top and bake 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into a large bowl.
Place milk, oil, egg, sugar, carrots and orange rind into blender and blend well together.
Pour over dry ingredients and stir only until moistened.
Spoon mixture into greased, lined muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: west virginia greens dip
directions: Cut top of bread and scoop out inside.
Break bread into pieces and use for dippers.
Combine mixed chopped greens with other ingredients.
Mix well and place in center of bread loaf. (This gets better if it sets a bit before serving.)

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Mix all ingredients together, adding broth to make moist.
Pour in crock-pot, cook on low 4 hours or on high 2 hours.
Easy recipe for Thanksgiving day.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and top with croutons.
Bake in shallow dish for 20-25 minutes at 350 degrees.
Serve with Triscuits or other crackers.

title: old fashioned cabbage
directions: Cut slices from top of cabbage and cut out inside of cabbage, leaving 3/4-inch shell.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir ground beef until light brown; drain.
Stir in 1/2 cup tomato sauce, tomatoes, stuffing mix, onion, garlic and salt; breaking up tomatoes.
Fill cabbage with beef mixture.
Place in Dutch oven. Mix remaining tomato sauce, water and any remaining meat mixture into Dutch oven around cabbage.
Cover and bake 45 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Remove cabbage from Dutch oven, cut into wedges, spoon sauce over wedges and sprinkle with cheese.

title: chili dip
directions: Layer cream cheese, then chili and top with cheese in microwave dish.
Heat until melted.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini until barely tender.
Drain.
Saute beef and onion.
Add rice, oregano and salt, mixing well.
Place 1/2 zucchini in bottom of 5 1/2-quart shallow casserole.
Cover with beef mixture.
Spoon over cottage cheese.
Add remaining zucchini. Spread soup over all.
Top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Cook 1/2 stick butter and 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese until cheese dissolves.
Put broccoli in greased casserole dish.
Pour cheese sauce over broccoli.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with 1/2 stick melted butter.
Spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients thoroughly with mixer in bowl. Pour into pie crusts and refrigerate. If you like, you can sprinkle coconut, shave chocolate pieces and sprinkle on top.

title: simmered wieners
directions: Place wieners in small pan, after punching holes in them. Cover with half water and half barbecue sauce.
Set at back of grill and let simmer while barbecuing.

title: potato bargain
directions: Sounds like a full meal.
I wonder if Potato Bargain is a purely Cape Cod dish?
I have never eaten it anywhere else and it makes my mouth water just to write about it.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in heavy saucepan.
Bring to full rolling boil.
Stir constantly.
Boil 5 minutes at medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until melted.
Add marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch buttered pan. Cool and cut into squares.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: In mixing bowl mix together cornmeal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
In separate bowl beat eggs lightly and stir in milk and cooking oil.
Add liquid to cornmeal mixture and stir in Mexican corn, jalapeno peppers, chopped onion and cheese.
Pour batter into well greased baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bethal bars
directions: Melt butter in pan, 14 x 11-inch.
Add to this the following in layers: graham cracker crumbs, grated coconuts, chocolate bits, butterscotch bits and condensed milk.
Drizzle over and add walnuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut in small squares, 1 1/2, while still warm.
Then cool.

title: bean dip
directions: Spread beans in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top (layer) with sour cream, picante sauce and onions.
Sprinkle cheeses on top.
Top with tomatoes.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken breasts; bring to a boil.
Remove chicken from bone.
Prepare the rice.
Cook green pepper and onion in oil in a skillet over low heat until tender, but not brown.
Blend cornstarch with small amount of chicken broth.
Add remaining broth and soy sauce and gently stir chicken and vegetables in together.
Stir until sauce is clear and thickened.
Add tomatoes and mushrooms and serve over rice.

title: pot roast beef
directions: Put roast in large kettle and cover with water.
Cook for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until it pulls apart easily.
Add all other ingredients; stir or mix well.
Cook until potatoes are soft. Remove from heat.
Add salt to taste, then serve.

title: apple muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups.
Mix all ingredients except apple and raisins.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Fold in apple and raisins.
Divide evenly among cups. Bake until light brown for 20 to 23 minutes.
Cool a few minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil frying chicken (cut up) with onion, celery and green pepper. Cool chicken and debone.
Pull into chunks.
Cover the bottom of a baking dish with this mixture.
Melt 1 stick margarine and add dry cornbread stuffing mix.
Layer all of the chicken over the stuffing.
Combine the soups and 2 cans of broth.
Pour soup mixture over top of the chicken. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut with biscuit cutter and brush top with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes.
You must allow biscuits to rise before baking.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Mix sliced and peeled apples with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; place in an unbaked pie shell.
Top with crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° until apples are tender; usually takes 45 to 50 minutes.

title: dainty ham rolls
directions: Mix grated ham, cheese and onion together.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spread on Dainty rolls.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Combine both with pizza sauce.
Spread in a 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over.
Add peppers, onions and drained mushrooms. Place pepperoni on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl beat eggs until they are frothy; beat in sugar, vegetable oil and vanilla until thick and lemon colored. Stir in zucchini, flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Fold in nuts.
Pour mixture into 2 oiled and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until toothpick comes out clean.

title: streusel topping
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter with knives until mixture resembles small pebbles.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and oatmeal.
Blend thoroughly.
Use as a topping for coffee cake or sweet rolls.

title: chinese green pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into bite size pieces.
Heat oil in a large skillet at medium heat.
Saute garlic, salt, ginger and pepper until garlic is golden.
Add steak and cook 5 minutes or until browned.
Remove meat.
Add sliced onion and cook 5 minutes.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg whites stiff, gradually adding sugar and salt.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Spoon onto cookie pans. Turn off oven.
Put cookies in oven quickly.
Do not open oven for at least 6 hours, overnight is better.

title: wild rice, sausage and oyster stuffing
directions: Cook wild rice according to package directions and drain. Drain oysters and reserve 1/2 cup liquid.
Coarsely chop oysters. Cook sausage in large skillet over medium-high heat until browned, stirring occasionally to break meat into small pieces.
Drain thoroughly.
In same skillet, melt butter over medium-high heat. Add celery, carrots and onion; cook and stir 5 to 7 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Stir in mushrooms, brandy, oysters and reserved liquid.
Cook and stir 10 minutes more until liquid has evaporated.

title: snitz pie
directions: Soak apples overnight in water.
Cook them in the water they soaked in.
When soft, put through colander.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Turn into pastry lined pan and cover with top crust. Bake 10 minutes at 425°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: hash and egg brunch
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine corned beef, potatoes, soup, 1/2 can onions and the pepper.
Spoon evenly into 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Using back of spoon, make 6 wells in hash mixture.
Break 1 egg into each well.
Bake, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes or until eggs are cooked to desired doneness.
Sprinkle cheese down center of dish and top with remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 1 to 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown. Serves 6.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, first sifting flour with soda and spices.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes (don't overbake).

title: wild rice fish cakes
directions: Bring fish and water to a boil in a 12 inch nonstick skillet. Reduce heat and simmer fillets 8 to 10 minutes until cooked through.
If fillets are thick turn halfway through cooking. Drain on paper towels, cool.
Flake fish into small pieces with fork. Combine rice,
mayonnaise,	bread crumbs, Old Bay Seasoning, egg, salt, pepper, and dry mustard in bowl.
