Stir in fish and refrigerate one hour or overnight.	Line jelly roll pan with waxed paper.
Sprinkle with one tbsp. cornmeal.
Shape fish into 8 1/2 inch patties,
place on pan and sprinkle tops with one tbsp. cornmeal.	Melt 2 tbsp. butter in large nonstick skillet over medium heat, cook 3 minutes.
Add 1 tbsp. butter, turn cakes and cook 3 more minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookie pie
directions: Microwave marshmallows and 2 tablespoons milk in medium microwavable bowl on High 45
seconds.
Stir.
(Marshmallows will be partially melted.)
Refrigerate 15 minutes to cool.
Stir in 1 cup of the whipped topping.

title: friendship cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with wooden spoon.
Do not use electric mixer.
Bake in greased Bundt pan/loaf pan or small aluminum pans at 300° for 50 to 70 minutes or until brown.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and bacon in a large skillet, add onion and cook until tender.
Pour off excess drippings.
Add brown sugar, catsup, mustard, vinegar, salt and pepper:
mix well.
Stir in beans.
Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 45 min. 6-8 servings.

title: stacked mexican bake
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil. Stir in remaining ingredients except tortillas and cheese.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
In greased 2-quart casserole, layer.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: green jello salad
directions: Fix green jello as directed on package.
Chill until slightly thick.
Remove from refrigerator and blend in softened cream cheese and Cool Whip with blender.
Add nuts and stir.
Pour into mold, if desired.
Chill for 30 minutes to an hour.

title: smothered rabbit and onions
directions: Clean and cut into pieces the rabbit.
Season with salt and paprika.
Then roll in flour.
Saute the rabbit in margarine until it is well browned.
Cover it thickly with sliced onion and salt. Spread 1 cup of sour cream over all.
Cover the skillet and simmer the rabbit for 1 hour or place the pan in an oven and bake for 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and cut into bite-size pieces.
Combine broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon and put in bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar in small bowl.
Refrigerate all ingredients until 1 hour before serving in their separate bowls, then toss together. Recipe from Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: corn pone
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a 10 x 13 pan, combine water, corn meal, and margarine.
Let cool.
In a bowl mix eggs, sugar and milk.
Add to 10 x 13 pan.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: bertha bradshaw's apple cake
directions: Peel and slice apples in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, brown sugar, white sugar, oil, vanilla and nuts.
Stir well.
Add soda, salt, baking powder and flour.
Stir well.
Pour batter in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serve with cream.

title: skillet beef and corn
directions: In skillet, brown meat, onion and thyme in oil. Season with pepper, if desired.
Stir in wine.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered, over medium heat, about 7 minutes or until liquid is gone. Add tomatoes. Reduce heat.
Cover and cook 15 minutes or until meat is tender. Uncover and cook 5 minutes more. Garnish with sliced green onions, if desired.
Makes 4 servings. Contains 305 calories.
Preparation time:
5 minutes.
Cooking time:
35 minutes.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a a time, and beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture a little at a time, along with the milk.
Beat well, until all is gone.
Add flavorings.
Beat for about 2 minutes.
Spray tube pan. Pour into pan.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour.
Let cool before removing from pan.
Use your favorite icing if desired.
Enjoy.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent roll dough into pizza pan.
Brown in oven; cool.
Beat until smooth the cream cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise.
Spread on crust.
Mix all vegetables (shredded or chopped fine).
Press on top of dressing.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put rhubarb pieces in bottom and spread out.
Sprinkle with Jell-O and sugar.
Spread dry cake mix evenly and drizzle melted margarine over the top.
Pour water over evenly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zippy onion dip
directions: Peel onion, leaving root end intact.
Cut onion vertically into quarters, cutting to within 1/2-inch of root end.
Cut each quarter vertically into thirds.
Place onion in boiling water 1 minute; remove and place in ice water 5 minutes.
Loosen petals if necessary.
Drain onion, cut side down.
Place flour in a zip-top plastic bag; add onion, shaking to coat.
Dip onion in egg.
Place cracker crumbs in plastic bag; add onion, tossing to coat.
Chill 1 hour.
Pour oil to depth of
3 inches into an electric fryer or heavy saucepan and heat to 375°.
Fry onion 5 to 7 minutes or until golden brown; drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt, if desired.
Serve onion with dark honey-mustard or
Ranch Style salad dressing.
Yield:
2 appetizer servings.

title: roasted potato wedges
directions: Cook on High in oil the salt, paprika and garlic clove, until garlic softens.
Stir in brown sauce.
Add potatoes; stir to cover all sides.
Microwave, covered, on High for 13 to 15 minutes.
Turn and rearrange; do this twice.
Toss out rest of oil mix.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and
peaches.
Mix
juice with pudding, using wire whisk.
Pour over fruit and chill.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to
sugar,
oil and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Stir in carrots and nuts. Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 300° for one hour.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Cook butter and onion in large saucepan for 5 to 7 minutes over medium heat.
Add water; bring to a boil.
Add shrimp; cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove shrimp to bowl.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper; simmer 4 to 6 minutes.
Add milk and half and half.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese and parsley.
Let stand until cheese melts.
Stir in shrimp and serve.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Dice up chicken and saute in a skillet coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Be sure not to fry.
When done, set aside.
Make the bouillon cube.
Measure out 3/4 cup and add 1/4 cup of the mushroom liquid.
Set aside.
In another skillet, melt butter or margarine.
Add flour, stirring constantly.
Make sure not to burn.
Remove from heat.
Add the cream and chicken broth with the mushroom liquid added.
Simmer on a medium heat, stirring occasionally, making sure not to scorch.
It takes a little while to thicken.
Once thickened, add the chicken.
Serve over the puff pastry.

title: grandma's economy dish
directions: Wash beans; add water, meat, onion and seasoning.

title: good gooey chicken
directions: Combine dressing, preserves and onion soup mix in bowl and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt and pepper.
Place chicken, skin side down, in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, basting occasionally.
Turn chicken over and baste.
Bake for 35 minutes more, basting occasionally. Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange julius
directions: Some women keep their husbands constantly in hot water. Some let
them
freeze by carelessness and indifference.
Some keep them in a stew by irritating ways, while others keep them in a pickle
all their lives.
See that the linen in which you wrap him in
is
nicely
washed
and
mended.
Tie
him with a strong silken
cord
called comfort.
Make a clear steady fire of love, neatness and cheerfulness.
Set your husband as near this as seems to
agree with him.
If he sputters and fizzes, don't be anxious. Some
do
this
until they are done.
Add a little sugar
called "kisses",
but
very
little
vinegar or pepper, if
any.
A little
spice
might
be
nice.
Stir him gently.
You cannot fail
to
know
when he is done.
He will keep indefinitely, unless he is set in too cool a place.

title: arroz dulce(rice pudding)
directions: Combine the rice, water and salt in a large saucepan.
Bring the water to a boil at high heat.
Cover saucepan.
Reduce heat to low and continue to cook for 12 to 15 minutes or until the water is absorbed.
Combine milk, sugar and egg yolks and add to rice.
Add raisins, vanilla and cinnamon and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold into the rice. Chill and garnish with nutmeg before serving.

title: hasty hots
directions: Stir together onions, cheese, crabmeat and mayonnaise.
Toast the cocktail slices and spread the cheese mix on top.
Arrange on baking sheet and place in broiler. Broil until the cheese melts and becomes bubbly and browned, about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Add sealegs and poach gently for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add sherry; gently simmer.
Add cream, except for 2 tablespoons; simmer. Add 2 tablespoons of cream to beaten egg yolks and mix into hot sauce.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Spoon over hot rice.

title: apple crisp
directions: Blend flour, brown sugar and butter.
Pack flour mixture on top of apples.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: spinach stuffed shells
directions: Boil shells the night before; wash, drain and chill 24 hours. Brown ground beef.
Mix ground beef, spinach, Ricotta, egg, chopped green onions and seasonings in large bowl.
In a large buttered pan, place stuffed shells with mix.
On top, put 1st layer of sauce, then add chopped tomatoes, then a 2nd layer of sauce.
Add Mozzarella cheese on top and let sit for 30 minutes. Drain excess water.
Cook in oven at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit trifle
directions: Cook pudding as directed; cool and stir raisins and 3/4 whipped topping into pudding.
Cut cake into 1-inch cubes; pour 1 cup pudding into 3-quart casserole bowl.
Top with 1/2 each of cake, jam, pineapple, undrained tropical fruit, nuts and bananas. Repeat layers.
Garnish.
Chill 20 minutes or overnight.

title: baked stuffed pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown onion, celery and apple in margarine.
Combine with bread cubes, seasonings and bouillon. Stuff each chop with 1/4 of the mixture.
Bake in covered baking pan for 1 hour.
Uncover and continue baking 30 minutes to brown.

title: 3 week coleslaw
directions: *I sometimes use a little pickling spice as well.

title: corned beef oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs, milk and seasoned salt.
Tear corned beef into small pieces into egg mixture.
Stir in cheese and onion.
Pour into 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch greased baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes or until omelet is set and top is golden brown.

title: bisquick banana muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spray muffin tin with Pam.
Fill cups 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with a little cinnamon and sugar mixture before baking, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or Doritos.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour sugar, flour and milk on top of margarine.
Add fruit last.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until brown.

title: ground beef and noodles
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Add beef, soup, water, pepper and onion.
Mix together and top with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Soften chocolate chips in a double boiler or in a microwave oven.
Add eggs, butter and vanilla.
Beat with mixer on high speed until creamy and easy for spreading.
Frost cake.
(Optional: Sprinkle top with chopped nuts.)

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Fry bacon until crisp; add onion and cook 1 minute.
Blend flour, salt, sugar and pepper with bacon and onion.
Stir in vinegar and water.
Cook 10 minutes; stir occasionally.
Pour mixture over warm potatoes.
Serve warm.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze.

title: southwest stew
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Grind the bottom round and pork together twice.
Soak the bread in milk.
Mix all together.
Wet hands.
Make mixture the size of small walnut; shape into a ball.
Fry, stirring often, or bake at 400°, draining off liquids and shaking pan every 10 minutes until well done.
Note:
Three pounds meat makes 48 meatballs.
Six pounds meat makes 96 meatballs.
Nine pounds meat makes 144 meatballs.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and strain.
Also macaroni and cheese.
Add together along with mushroom soup.
Simmer and serve.

title: potatoes poupon
directions: In medium saucepan over medium heat, cook onion in 1 tablespoon butter or margarine until tender.
Stir in cream, mustard and remaining butter or margarine.
Simmer 5 minutes. Reduce heat to low; add 1/2 cup cheese and basil and stir until cheese melts.
In a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, alternately layer potatoes and cream sauce.
On top, sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 55 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Garnish with almonds before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: *Or 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice.

title: mother's pound cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, milk and butter until well blended.
Add flour; mix well.
Add flavoring and pour into cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes, turn oven up to 350° and bake until done.

title: pizza
directions: Crumble yeast in lukewarm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Pour boiling water over shortening and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast.
Add 1/2 of flour; beat until smooth.
Remaining flour may now be added; beat until smooth.
Divide dough in half for a thin pizza; use all the dough for a thicker one.
Place on floured board; pat gently into 1 (13-inch) or 2 (11-inch) rounds.
Make edge slightly thicker.
This keeps filling from running over during baking.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Let rise in warm place (85°) until dough doubles in thickness.
Arrange filling on top.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until crust is golden brown.

title: trout almandine
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with Pam.
Place trout in pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice; dot with margarine and sprinkle with paprika. Bake, covered, about 5 minutes.
Uncover and bake until the fish is opaque, about 5 minutes more.
Sprinkle with the parsley and almonds.
Serve garnished with the lemon.

title: pfeffernuesse
directions: Blend sugars, molasses, milk, shortening, soda, egg and spices. Divide batter into two portions.
Mix an extra 1/2 cup flour slowly with each portion until you have a fairly stiff dough; chill.
Roll into ropes a little thicker than a finger, then use a butter knife. Cut into pieces 1-inch long.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 200 little cookies.

title: christmas tea
directions: Melt candies in cider in pot #1.
Bring water to boil in pot #2.
Add tea.
After tea has fully steeped, add sugar and lemon juice.
Take the tea bags out first.
Mix both together in pot #3. It better be a big one.
Serve hot, stirring occasionally with a big spoon.

title: beef jerky
directions: Cut steak into thin strips approximately 2 inches long and no wider than 1/4 inch.
(Be sure to cut with grain of steak.)
Mix all ingredients together until well mixed.
Coat steaks with mixture thoroughly and let stand for one hour. Preheat oven to 450°.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Place steaks on lined cookie sheet. Be sure to space each steak.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.
Turn oven off then let sit in oven 20 minutes more. Ready to eat or refrigerate.

title: apples and cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg. Mix with apples in large bowl. Then add lemon juice.

title: kansas cucumber salad
directions: In a large bowl combine mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, dill weed and salt.
Mix well.
Add cucumbers and onions, toss to coat.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring the first 6 ingredients to a boil; let cool.
Combine all the remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour cooled dressing over vegetables and mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: emma williams' filling
directions: Peel and cook potatoes in water with 1 teaspoon of salt to cover potatoes.
Cut celery and onion in small pieces.
Cook in butter until done.
When potatoes are done, pour potato water over the cubed bread.
Mash potatoes; add a little milk to make smoother.
Combine the mashed potatoes, onion, celery and beaten eggs to the bread.
Mix well together.
Grease casserole with butter.
Put filling in and put pieces of butter on top.
Add a pinch of thyme or marjoram to filling (optional).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: japanese chicken salad
directions: Bake chicken breasts in soy sauce. Cool and dice. Dice 1/2 head cabbage and chop green onions. Mix all this together in a large bowl.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Boil 4 quarts water. Wash and core peppers. Put peppers in boiling water for about 2 minutes. Brown ground chuck; drain off grease. Add cooked rice and tomato sauce; simmer for 5 minutes. Drain peppers; put in baking dish and fill with rice mixture. If any left over, put around peppers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: stir-fried beef and vegetables
directions: Cut steak into thin slices.
Set aside.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and jello in saucepan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add lukewarm water and cook 10 minutes until thick.
Let set until cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: jalapeno cheese log
directions: You will need a 1 gallon Ziploc Baggie.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Heat sugar and pineapple; add Jell-O.
Cool.
Add all of the other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: pineapple orange whip
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water. Add 1/2 cup cold water. Let cream cheese set until soft, then add and dissolve in Jell-O. Blend with fork. If necessary blend with mixer at low speed. Set in refrigerator until partially congealed. Add pineapple (juice and all) to mixture. Follow the directions on Dream Whip and fold into mixture. Return to refrigerator.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well. Beat eggs with oil and add grated zucchini to egg-oil mixture. Saut onion until golden, about 5 minutes on medium heat. Add to zucchini mixture. Pour into Bisquick mixture and stir thoroughly, but do not beat. Pour into well-greased 10-inch pie plate or 9-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until knife inserted into pie comes out clean.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together sugar and eggs.
Mix in and blend in with oil. Then blend in vinegar and buttermilk, add soda and cake flour.
Add flavoring and food coloring.
As you add the different ingredients be sure you are blending each together very well.
Put into well greased and floured pans and bake 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Time depends on size of pans.
For frosting mix together 8 ounces cream cheese, 1 stick margarine, 1 box 4x sugar, 1 tsp. vanilla and 1 c. chopped nuts.
Cream together well and put on cooled cake.

title: amazing raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch baking pans.
Mix first 10 ingredients 2 minutes at low speed or 300 strokes by hand.
Spoon in apples, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Frost with 2 cups whipped cream.

title: crock-pot pot roast
directions: Cook rump roast in crock-pot until almost done, using only about 4 cups of water or more if needed.
Add onion, pepper, salt, carrots and potatoes.
Finish cooking until done.
Add your tomatoes last; let simmer for 15 minutes and enjoy!

title: ground meat casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
(Drain fat.)
Mix soup and beans together with meat.
Put in 3-quart ovenproof bowl.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Cut dates, add water and soda and allow to cool.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; add melted butter and well beaten egg.
Last, add dates and water mixture.
Then add nuts and vanilla.
A loaf pan (4 x 13-inch) should be used.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: When cooking, heat oven to 350°.
Grease 10 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix shredded cheeses together.
Layer 1/2 the cheese in dish.
Top with chilies.
Then add remaining cheese.
Beat eggs, evaporated milk and spices together.
Pour over cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 40 minutes.
Take out and top with tomato sauce, bake 10 more minutes.
Slice in squares.

title: coffee cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Beat on medium for 2 minutes.
Mix in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt alternately with sour cream.

title: pork chops and apple in wine sauce
directions: Arrange pork chops in shallow baking pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake in 400° oven until brown on both sides.
Place apple slices on chops and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Pour 1/4 cup wine over chops and apple slices.
Bake 10 minutes.
Add remaining wine and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer. Baste chops from time to time with sauce in baking pan.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper in skillet.
Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Simmer 10 minutes. Pour into buttered 2 quart casserole and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Add cheese and bake 10 minutes more.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Cream and blend all ingredients.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter until brown.
Add soups, Ro-Tel and chicken; simmer until heated.
Grease large casserole dish and line with chips.
Pour mixture over chips.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with Durkee onions.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and melted.

title: nathan's tortilla pizza
directions: Cover tortilla with pizza sauce and sprinkle with cheese. Cook in microwave until cheese is melted.

title: eggless cocoa cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, soda, cocoa and salt. Add milk, shortening and vanilla.
Beat and bake in a loaf pan 30 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate cherry cupcakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cake mix, water, oil and eggs; mix well.
Spoon batter by 1/4 cupfuls into paper-lined muffin cups. Spoon a rounded teaspoon of pie filling into the center of each cupcake.
Set remaining pie filling aside.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted on an angle toward the center comes out clean.
Remove to a wire rack to cool completely. Frost cupcakes; top with one cherry from pie filling.
Serve additional pie filling with cupcakes or refrigerate for another use.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix as given. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 large loaf pans or you can use several small loaf pans and tin cans of various sizes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, peppers, carrots and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.
Drain.
Tie spices in a bag.
Combine spice bag, vinegar and sugar in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add vegetables.
Boil gently, stirring often, 15 to 20 minutes or until desired consistency.
Pack into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Screw metal bands on tightly.
Process in a boiling water bath for 15 minutes.
Yield: About 6 pints.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate, butter and salt.
Add the sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, stirring as you add.
Add the evaporated milk, a little at a time, and continue stirring until well mixed.
Serve hot over ice cream.
Store in refrigerator.

title: meatballs in sauce
directions: Mix first six ingredients and form into meatballs.
Place into baking dish.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Cut up and cook potatoes until done; put into a large mixing bowl and beat well.
Add cream cheese and margarine.
Add sour cream and salt to taste.
Whip until light and creamy.

title: ham log
directions: Combine ALL ingredients. Mix well. Shape into a ball and roll in pecans. Good on crackers!

title: krunchy cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortenings, egg, vanilla and milk. Sift flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar and add to ingredients. Add remaining ingredients and drop by teaspoon onto baking sheet (ungreased). Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Yields 100 cookies.

title: pork and apricot salad
directions: Drain apricots, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
Place pork, apricot halves, broccoli and celery in a large bowl.

title: easy caramel frosting
directions: Mix first four ingredients together in saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Cool and stir in vanilla. Gradually add powdered sugar.
Beat until creamy after each addition of sugar.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and serve.

title: zucchini (or banana) bread(yields 2 loaves)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients, except the flour, and mix well. Add flour last and mix together.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Turn out onto cooling rack or breadboard while still HOT or else you'll have a mess.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 345° for 45 minutes.

title: herbed melba toast
directions: Mix all but bread and spread thinly on bread on both sides. Slice diagonally into quarters. Dry in 250° oven 1 1/2 hours or until completely crisp.

title: classic tuna casserole
directions: First you make a white sauce.
In a medium saucepan, melt butter on low heat.
When butter is completely melted, add flour and a dash of salt and pepper.
Whisk together; when mixture begins to sizzle slightly in the pan, add milk and stir.
Raise heat slightly and continue to stir until mixture thickens.
When sauce has reached thickness of gravy, lower heat and set aside until needed.
Cook egg noodles as directed on package.
Drain thoroughly.
In a large casserole dish, empty both cans of tuna and mushrooms, well-drained.
Mix these ingredients in casserole. Put in drained cooked egg noodles, grated Cheddar cheese and white sauce.
Mix together until completely creamed.
Top with Italian bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sunburst stir-fry
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup for sauce.
Cut chicken into chunks.
In large skillet, stir fry chicken with garlic and ginger in oil for 2 minutes.
Add pineapple, carrots, and bell pepper. Cover, steam 2 or 3 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender. Stir in spaghetti.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook and stir hamburger and onion in 10-inch skillet until hamburger is light brown.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except buns.
Cover and cook over low heat just until vegetables are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Fill buns with beef mixture.
Makes 5 sandwiches.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice and sherry; mix well.
Stir in crab meat and parsley.
Serve on crackers.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Slice or dice the potatoes.
Slice the leeks thinly, being careful to wash off any dirt or sand.
Simmer the potatoes and leeks together with the chicken stock, salt and pepper for 40 to 50 minutes.
Mash the vegetables or puree them in a food processor.
Check the seasonings and reheat, adding the cream or milk.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts or 6 servings with 297 calories per serving.
A dash of nutmeg is delicious!!

title: tomato salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a quart jar; shake well.
This is delicious on head of lettuce or cabbage or any green salad.
Keep covered and refrigerated.

title: praline sticks
directions: Place single layer of crackers in pan.
Heat margarine and sugar to boiling.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add pecans.
Then, spread over crackers and bake for 5 minutes at 400°.
Finally, cut into strips when cool.
Makes 40 pieces.

title: judy's hearty potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes; cut in 1/2-inch cubes.
In large saucepan melt butter over medium heat.
Add leeks and celery.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add broth; bring to boil.
Stir in potatoes and carrot.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Mash potatoes slightly to thicken soup.
Stir milk, parsley and thyme in.
Cook until heated thoroughly.
Do not boil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Garnish with Cheddar cheese and crumbled bacon.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Save broth.
Remove chicken from bone in small pieces.
Melt margarine and prepared dressing as indicated on box.
In a baking dish put layer of crumbs and a layer of chicken.
Empty soups into separate bowls.
Thin each with 1/2 can of broth that was saved.
Blend well.
Pour the celery (or onion) soup over the layers of crumbs and chicken.
Add another layer of crumbs and chicken.
Pour cream of chicken over this layer.
Add a final layer of crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.

title: baked cheddar tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes on greased baking sheet and sprinkle salt, pepper and sugar over each half.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese; place equal amounts on each tomato half.
Drizzle each tomato with butter and bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until cheese melts.
Remove from oven and serve.
Serves 6.

title: catherine's shrimp dip
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese together.
Add chili sauce and gently stir in shrimp.
Place in serving bowl and refrigerate. Serve with potato chips or raw vegetables.

title: rodeo special macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Stir in butter and reserve for later use.
Brown ground beef; add green pepper and onion.
Drain excess grease.
Add tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Simmer uncovered for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; add macaroni.
Serve hot. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chili
directions: Sprinkle meat with chili powder, salt and pepper.
Finely chop onions and garlic together.
Brown garlic, onion and meat in a large pot.
Drain well.
Add tomatoes.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Skim off grease.
Add molasses or syrup to taste.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box in 2 layers.
Cool.
Place 1 layer of cake on bottom of punch bowl.
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Pour 1/2 pudding over cake layer in bowl.
Make thin layer of fruit on top of pudding.
Tear remaining layer up and cover layer of fruit.
Cover with rest of fruit and 1/2 coconut and rest of pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip, coconut and nuts.

title: nighty nights
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Beat egg whites until forms stiff peaks. Gradually beat in sugar. Add coloring. Fold in morsels. Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet. Place in oven and close door immediately. Then turn oven off. Leave in oven overnight without peeking. Makes 75 cookies.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream together the margarine and shortening. Add sugar.

Beat until smooth and add egg yolks. Combine flour and soda. Add the above to the creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Stir in vanilla. Beat stiffly and fold egg whites, coconut and nuts into mixture.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat, drain grease off.
Add mushrooms, onion, tomato paste, garlic powder, chili powder and salt.
Simmer and bring to a boil for 15 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all together and place in 8 x 12 x 1-inch pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: how dee's brunswick stew
directions: Prepare all and combine in a large pot and cook until done. Cook chickens and ribs awhile before adding vegetables.

title: bacon broccoli toss
directions: Mix the salad ingredients in a large bowl.

title: cranberry dessert salad
directions: Place 1 cup crushed vanilla wafers in 8 x 8-inch dish.
Mix milk, lemon juice, vanilla and chopped pecans.
Set aside.
Mix cranberries, banana and sugar; spread over layer of wafers.
Spread milk mixture over cranberry layer.
Cover with Cool Whip and top with the remaining wafers.
Chill.
Keeps 2 to 3 days.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Use 2 loaf pans and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes and remove from pans.

title: easy garden vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inch. Heat 1 inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Cook until almost tender, about 5 minutes; drain thoroughly.

title: hungarian baked chicken
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet with a cover.
Dust chicken lightly with paprika.
Brown chicken on all sides over medium heat.
Cover, reduce heat and cook chicken for 30 minutes.

title: coconut crunch
directions: Crumb flour, cocoa, oleo and brown sugar and brown in a 350° oven until golden brown.
Cool.
Place half of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare instant vanilla pudding and pour over crumbs.
Put the rest of the crumbs on top of the pudding.
Spread the Cool Whip on top.

title: drop doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoonfuls in hot, deep fat.
Drain on paper towels and dust with confectioners sugar if desired.

title: chuck's fried cornbread
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and egg.
Beat until fairly thick, about 1 minute.
Add diced onions.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese with flour and salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add flour.
Shape in small balls.
Roll in crumbs.
Fry in deep fat and drain on brown paper.
Excellent served with fruit or vegetable salad.
Serve immediately after cooking.

title: chow chow relish
directions: Combine the chopped vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand about 6 hours.
Drain.
Mix vinegar, sugar and spices and simmer 10 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Bring to a boil and pack, boiling hot, into hot, sterilized jars.
Leave 1/8 inch of headspace.
Adjust caps.
Yields 4 pints.

title: french fried sweet potatoes
directions: Soak potato
strips
in
cold
water
for
minutes. Drain; then dry very well.
Fry in hot (375°) fat or oil until brown, about
3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with salt.

title: tillamook squash
directions: Cut up zucchini and cook in small amount of water until tender and nearly dry.
Mash and mix with other ingredients.
Place in well-greased casserole and top with additional grated cheese and bake at 375° until puffed and golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: special day casserole
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, seasonings, sour cream, milk and oats; set aside.
Combine tomato sauce, tomato paste and water. Pour 1/3 of the sauce into Dutch oven.
Place 1/2 of the cabbage over sauce.
Spread beef mixture over cabbage.
Cover with remaining cabbage.
Pour remaining sauce over cabbage.
Cover tightly.
Simmer for 1 hour or until cabbage is tender and beef mixture is done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook both broccoli and rice according to directions on package and then mix together in casserole dish.
Melt butter in saucepan and add Velveeta cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add cream of mushroom soup and mix well.

title: favorite tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain well and set aside.
Saute chopped celery and onion in melted butter in a Dutch oven until tender.
Stir in cooked noodles, tuna and next 5 ingredients.
Add salt, if desired.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 2 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
To store, cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
To serve, bake, uncovered, at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Garnish, if desired.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Mix in chocolate; add meal, vinegar and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: inflation fighting chili mac
directions: Brown ground chuck and combine with all ingredients except the macaroni. Cook noodles 7 minutes and drain. Cook chili 20 minutes and serve over the macaroni.

title: green bean-buttermilk soup
directions: Cook beans in salted water until done.
Add buttermilk.
Stir often.
Bring back to a boil.
Add pepper.
Make a paste of flour dissolved in a small amount of milk.
Let boil up again.
Remove from heat.
Set aside to cool.
Soup tastes better after it is cold.

title: frying pan fudge
directions: Chop nuts and set aside. Mix sugar, margarine and milk together in a heavy frying pan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and cook 6 more minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and chopped nuts. Stir until fudge begins to form, then quickly add vanilla flavoring. Drop fudge on waxed paper with a teaspoon. Let cool and store in an airtight container.

title: biscuits supreme
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine, using pastry blender, until consistency is like coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once. Stir with fork only until mixture follows fork around the bowl. Turn out onto lightly floured counter; knead 1/2 minute or about 10 to 12 times.
With rolling pin, roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter or use a small glass.
Bake on foil-lined ungreased cookie sheet at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: freezer delite
directions: Blend in order given.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or plastic container and cover.
Place in freezer and freeze.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix with dry jello; add water and eggs; beat 3 minutes.
Add oil and beat 3 additional minutes.
Bake in 9x13x2-inch pan in 350° oven for 35-37 minutes or until done. While cake is still warm (not hot) loosen cake from sides.
Poke holes (pencil size) in cake every 2-inches.
Leave cake in baking pan.

title: layered taco dip
directions: 1st Layer: Spread 2 average size cans Old El Paso refried beans in dish.

title: easy casserole
directions: Bone and skin chicken thighs.
Beat until about 2-inches thick. Put in 1 strip of half fried bacon and strips of cheese to suit your taste.
Roll up; put toothpick in to hold together.
Make dip of egg whites and lemon juice; roll chicken.
Put flour and lemon pepper in bag and shake.
Fry slowly until well done.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Chop these ingredients and toss together to distribute evenly over the crust and cheese mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap and press the veggie mix into the cheese mix.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Cut into bars.
Yields 36 bars.
Serve.

title: granny's baked custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla. Gradually stir in cooled milk.
Pour into custard cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place cups in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour hot water into pan within 1/2 inch of cups.
Bake about 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove cups from water.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Put yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Mash potatoes; add Criso, sugar, beaten eggs, milk and yeast.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Knead in 4 cups self-rising flour.
Let rise; then knead again and put in icebox or bake.
Sometimes it takes a little more flour to make out your rolls.
I pinch off and put my rolls in muffin tins and make clover leaf rolls.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Prepare dough for rolled biscuits as directed on package of biscuit mix.
Roll out dough into a 12 x 12-inch oblong shape. Cut into strips 4 inches long and 3 inches wide.
Wrap around each hot dog.
The end of the hot dog will peek out of the biscuit (blanket).
Heat oven to 450°.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: mustard-grilled shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp, together.
Add shrimp to mixture.
Chill several hours, stirring often.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Grill over medium coals for 6 to 8 minutes. Turn and baste twice with marinade.

title: pickle dill okra
directions: Put in bottom of each jar 1 clove garlic, 2 tablespoons dill weed or seed and 1/4 of hot dried red pepper.
Add whole okra to jar.
Heat to boil vinegar, water and salt.
Pour hot vinegar over the okra and seal.

title: sugar-free cherry coke salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and cherries; add water to juice to make 2 cups.
Heat liquid to dissolve jello, then add Coke, cherries and pineapple.
Chill.
When mixture is thick, cover with a layer of cream cheese and chopped nuts.
Continue to refrigerate until firm.

title: pink salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and cherry juice.
Drain pineapple.
Cut cherries in half, if desired. Cut marshmallows in 1/3 or 1/4 using scissors dipped in hot water.
Mix all together and refrigerate until just before needed. Whip cream and fold in.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potato chips.
Crush potato chips and put on top; add melted margarine (1 stick) on top of chips. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pork cutlets(dinner)
directions: Cut pork into cubes.
Heat in olive oil (in Dutch oven) until brown.
Using a slotted spoon, remove meat onto plate.
Saute onions in the oil for 12 minutes.
Add garlic; cook 3 minutes. Add tomatoes, meat juices, chicken broth, white wine, thyme and oregano.
Put into casserole and bake, covered, for 1 hour.
Add olives and green beans; stir and cook for another 45 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.
Serve with hot rolls and a salad.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Boil onion, water, tomatoes, tomato puree or sauce, garlic powder, oregano, and pepper in saucepan for 10 minutes to simmer for flavors.
Place chicken in frying pan.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cook, covered, over low heat until chicken is tender, about 45 minutes.
Uncover and cook 15 minutes more to thicken tomato sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: french epicurean peas(14 to 16 servings)
directions: Fry bacon; remove and drain grease.
Chop into small pieces. Fry onion until yellow; remove.
Add mushrooms (if fresh mushrooms, saute).
Make a cream sauce with butter, flour and evaporated milk.
When thick, add chopped bacon, onion, mushrooms and peas.

title: fantasy freeze pie
directions: Combine the cream cheese and Marshmallow Fluff, mixing with electric mixer until well blended.
Add sherbet, mixing well. Fold in Cool Whip and almonds.
Add food coloring if desired. Pour into pie shell.
Freeze until firm.

title: tomato-cracker salad
directions: Make as many layers as necessary to fill a 1 1/2-quart casserole or container which is at least 4 inches deep.
Begin with crackers, then tomatoes, seasonings, mayonnaise, eggs and seasonings.
Refrigerate.
Use within a day or two, as the salad will become soggy.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well. Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to butter, milk and vanilla. Roll raisins in remaining flour.
Divide batter in half.
Add raisins and spices to two layers and leave two layers plain.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: turkey soup
directions: Place bones compactly in kettle.
Add the next five ingredients.
Cover.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours.
Strain.
You may add the meat back to the broth, or serve without.
Add dried parsley and soup noodles back to the broth, cooking until done.

title: fried chocolate pies
directions: In a pan, combine sugar, flour and cocoa.
Stir in 1 cup milk and butter.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Cook 1 minute more.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool.
Combine biscuit mix and 1/3 cup plus 2 tablespoons milk.
On floured surface, roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut 20 (4-inch) circles.
Place 1 tablespoon filling in center of each circle.
Fold over and press with fork.
Fry in oil until brown.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.
